53#define PT_LOAD Elf32_Phdr::PT_LOAD /* 64-bit PT_LOAD is the same */

69/*static*/ const unsigned char PackLinuxElf::o_shstrtab[] = { \
70/*start*/ '\0',
71/*offset 1*/ '.','n','o','t','e','.','g','n','u','.','b','u','i','l','d','-','i','d','\0',
72/*offset 20*/ '.','s','h','s','t','r','t','a','b','\0'
73};

75static unsigned
76up4(unsigned x)
77{
78 return ~3u & (3+ x);
79}
80
81static unsigned
82up8(unsigned x)
83{
84 return ~7u & (7+ x);
85}
86
87static off_t
88fpadN(OutputFile *fo, unsigned len)
89{
90 if (len) {
91 MemBuffer pad(len); pad.clear();
92 fo->write(pad, len);
93 }
94 return fo->st_size();
95}
96
97static off_t
98fpad4(OutputFile *fo, unsigned pos)
99{
100 (void)pos; // debug: compare 'pos' with "shell grep pos /proc/PID/fdinfo/FD"
101 if (!fo) { // --test, --list
102 return 0;
103 }
104 off_t len = fo->st_size();
105 unsigned d = 3u & (0 - len);
106 if (d) {
107 unsigned zero = 0;
108 fo->write(&zero, d);
109 }
110 return d + len;
111}
112
113static off_t
114fpad8(OutputFile *fo, unsigned pos)
115{
116 (void)pos; // debug: compare 'pos' with "shell grep pos /proc/PID/fdinfo/FD"
117 if (!fo) { // --test, --list
118 return 0;
119 }
120 off_t len = fo->st_size();
121 unsigned d = 7u & (0 - len);
122 if (d) {
123 upx_uint64_t zero = 0;
124 fo->write(&zero, d);
125 }
126 return d + len;
127}
128
129static unsigned
130funpad4(InputFile *fi)
131{
132 unsigned d = 3u & (0 - fi->tell());
133 if (d)
134 fi->seek(d, SEEK_CUR);
135 return d;
136}
137
138static void alloc_file_image(MemBuffer &mb, off_t size)
139{
140 assert(mem_size_valid_bytes(size));
141 if (mb.getVoidPtr() == nullptr) {
142 mb.alloc(size);
143 } else {
144 assert((u32_t)size <= mb.getSize());
145 }
146}

148int
149PackLinuxElf32::checkEhdr(Elf32_Ehdr const *ehdr) const
150{
151 const unsigned char * const buf = ehdr->e_ident;
152
153 if (0!=memcmp(buf, "\x7f\x45\x4c\x46", 4) // "\177ELF"
154 || buf[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_CLASS]!=ei_class
155 || buf[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_DATA] !=ei_data
156 ) {
157 return -1;
158 }
159 if (!memcmp(buf+8, "FreeBSD", 7)) // branded
160 return 1;
161
162 int const type = get_te16(&ehdr->e_type);
163 if (type != Elf32_Ehdr::ET_EXEC && type != Elf32_Ehdr::ET_DYN)
164 return 2;
165 if (get_te16(&ehdr->e_machine) != (unsigned) e_machine)
166 return 3;
167 if (get_te32(&ehdr->e_version) != Elf32_Ehdr::EV_CURRENT)
168 return 4;
169 if (e_phnum < 1)
170 return 5;
171 if (get_te16(&ehdr->e_phentsize) != sizeof(Elf32_Phdr))
172 return 6;
173
174 if (type == Elf32_Ehdr::ET_EXEC) {
175 // check for Linux kernels
176 unsigned const entry = get_te32(&ehdr->e_entry);
177 if (entry == 0xC0100000) // uncompressed vmlinux
178 return 1000;
179 if (entry == 0x00001000) // compressed vmlinux
180 return 1001;
181 if (entry == 0x00100000) // compressed bvmlinux
182 return 1002;
183 }
184
185 // FIXME: add more checks for kernels
186
187 // FIXME: add special checks for other ELF i386 formats, like
188 // NetBSD, OpenBSD, Solaris, ....
189
190 // success
191 return 0;
192}
193
194int
195PackLinuxElf64::checkEhdr(Elf64_Ehdr const *ehdr) const
196{
197 const unsigned char * const buf = ehdr->e_ident;
198 unsigned char osabi0 = buf[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI];
199 if (0==osabi0) {
200 osabi0 = opt->o_unix.osabi0;
201 }
202
203 if (0!=memcmp(buf, "\x7f\x45\x4c\x46", 4) // "\177ELF"
204 || buf[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_CLASS]!=ei_class
205 || buf[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_DATA] !=ei_data
206 || osabi0!=ei_osabi
207 ) {
208 return -1;
209 }
210 if (!memcmp(buf+8, "FreeBSD", 7)) // branded
211 return 1;
212
213 int const type = get_te16(&ehdr->e_type);
214 if (type != Elf64_Ehdr::ET_EXEC && type != Elf64_Ehdr::ET_DYN)
215 return 2;
216 if (get_te16(&ehdr->e_machine) != (unsigned) e_machine)
217 return 3;
218 if (get_te32(&ehdr->e_version) != Elf64_Ehdr::EV_CURRENT)
219 return 4;
220 if (e_phnum < 1)
221 return 5;
222 if (get_te16(&ehdr->e_phentsize) != sizeof(Elf64_Phdr))
223 return 6;
224
225 if (type == Elf64_Ehdr::ET_EXEC) {
226 // check for Linux kernels
227 upx_uint64_t const entry = get_te64(&ehdr->e_entry);
228 if (entry == 0xC0100000) // uncompressed vmlinux
229 return 1000;
230 if (entry == 0x00001000) // compressed vmlinux
231 return 1001;
232 if (entry == 0x00100000) // compressed bvmlinux
233 return 1002;
234 }
235
236 // FIXME: add more checks for kernels
237
238 // FIXME: add special checks for other ELF i386 formats, like
239 // NetBSD, OpenBSD, Solaris, ....
240
241 // success
242 return 0;
243}

245PackLinuxElf::PackLinuxElf(InputFile *f)
246 : super(f), e_phnum(0), dynstr(nullptr),
247 sz_phdrs(0), sz_elf_hdrs(0), sz_pack2(0), sz_pack2a(0),
248 lg2_page(12), page_size(1u<<lg2_page), is_pie(0), is_asl(0),
249 xct_off(0), o_binfo(0), so_slide(0), xct_va(0), jni_onload_va(0),
250 user_init_va(0), user_init_off(0),
251 e_machine(0), ei_class(0), ei_data(0), ei_osabi(0), osabi_note(nullptr),
252 shstrtab(nullptr),
253 o_elf_shnum(0)
254{
255 memset(dt_table, 0, sizeof(dt_table));
256 symnum_max = 0;
257 user_init_rp = nullptr;
258}

264int PackLinuxElf32::is_LOAD(Elf32_Phdr const *phdr) const
265{
266 // (1+ PT_LOPROC) can confuse!
267 return PT_LOAD == get_te32(&phdr->p_type);
268}

270int PackLinuxElf64::is_LOAD(Elf64_Phdr const *phdr) const
271{
272 // (1+ PT_LOPROC) can confuse!
273 return PT_LOAD == get_te32(&phdr->p_type);
274}

276void
277PackLinuxElf32::PackLinuxElf32help1(InputFile *f)
278{
279 e_type = get_te16(&ehdri.e_type);
280 e_phnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum);
281 e_shnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_shnum);
282 unsigned const e_phentsize = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phentsize);
283 if (memcmp((char const *)&ehdri, "\x7f\x45\x4c\x46", 4) // "\177ELF"
284 || ehdri.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_CLASS]!=Elf32_Ehdr::ELFCLASS32
285 || sizeof(Elf32_Phdr) != e_phentsize
286 || (Elf32_Ehdr::ELFDATA2MSB == ehdri.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_DATA]
287 && &N_BELE_RTP::be_policy != bele)
288 || (Elf32_Ehdr::ELFDATA2LSB == ehdri.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_DATA]
289 && &N_BELE_RTP::le_policy != bele)) {
290 e_phoff = 0;
291 e_shoff = 0;
292 sz_phdrs = 0;
293 return;
294 }
295 if (0==e_phnum) throwCantUnpack("0==e_phnum");
296 e_phoff = get_te32(&ehdri.e_phoff);
297 unsigned const last_Phdr = e_phoff + e_phnum * usizeof(Elf32_Phdr);
298 if (last_Phdr < e_phoff // wrap-around
299 || e_phoff != sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) // must be contiguous
300 || (unsigned long)file_size < last_Phdr) {
301 throwCantUnpack("bad e_phoff %#x", e_phoff);
302 }
303 e_shoff = get_te32(&ehdri.e_shoff);
304 e_shstrndx = get_te16(&ehdri.e_shstrndx);
305 unsigned const last_Shdr = e_shoff + e_shnum * usizeof(Elf32_Shdr);
306 if (last_Shdr < e_shoff // wrap-around
307 || (e_shnum && e_shoff < last_Phdr)
308 || (unsigned long)file_size < last_Shdr) {
309 if (opt->cmd == CMD_COMPRESS) {
310 throwCantUnpack("bad e_shoff %#x", e_shoff);
311 }
312 }
313 sz_phdrs = e_phnum * e_phentsize;
314 sz_elf_hdrs = sz_phdrs + sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) +
315 n_phdrx * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr); // phdrx bodies later: ::generateElfHdr
316
317 if (f && Elf32_Ehdr::ET_DYN!=e_type) {
318 unsigned const len = file_size; // (sz_phdrs + e_phoff) except --preserve-build-id
319 alloc_file_image(file_image, len);
320 f->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
321 f->readx(file_image, len);
322 phdri= (Elf32_Phdr *)(e_phoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
323 }
324 if (f && Elf32_Ehdr::ET_DYN==e_type) {
325 // The DT_SYMTAB has no designated length. Read the whole file.
326 alloc_file_image(file_image, file_size);
327 f->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
328 f->readx(file_image, file_size);
329 phdri= (Elf32_Phdr *)(e_phoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
330 if (opt->cmd != CMD_COMPRESS || !e_shoff || file_size < e_shoff) {
331 shdri = nullptr;
332 }
333 else { // FIXME: copy from file_image ?
334 fi->seek(e_shoff, SEEK_SET);
335 if (mb_shdr.getSize() != sizeof(Elf32_Shdr) * e_shnum) {
336 mb_shdr.alloc( sizeof(Elf32_Shdr) * e_shnum);
337 }
338 shdri = (Elf32_Shdr *)mb_shdr.getVoidPtr();
339 fi->readx(shdri, sizeof(Elf32_Shdr) * e_shnum);
340 }
341 sec_dynsym = elf_find_section_type(Elf32_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
342 if (sec_dynsym) {
343 unsigned t = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_link);
344 if (e_shnum <= t)
345 throwCantPack("bad dynsym->sh_link");
346 sec_dynstr = &shdri[t];
347 }
348
349 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr= phdri;
350 for (int j = e_phnum; --j>=0; ++phdr)
351 if (Elf32_Phdr::PT_DYNAMIC==get_te32(&phdr->p_type)) {
352 unsigned offset = check_pt_dynamic(phdr);
353 dynseg= (Elf32_Dyn *)(offset + file_image);
354 invert_pt_dynamic(dynseg,
355 umin(get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz), (unsigned)(file_size_u - offset)));
356 }
357 else if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
358 check_pt_load(phdr);
359 }
360 // elf_find_dynamic() returns 0 if 0==dynseg.
361 dynstr = (char const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
362 dynsym = (Elf32_Sym /*const*/ *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB);
363 gashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
364 hashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_HASH);
365 if (3& ((upx_uintptr_t)dynsym | (upx_uintptr_t)gashtab | (upx_uintptr_t)hashtab)) {
366 throwCantPack("unaligned DT_SYMTAB, DT_GNU_HASH, or DT_HASH/n");
367 }
368 jni_onload_sym = elf_lookup("JNI_OnLoad");
369 if (jni_onload_sym) {
370 jni_onload_va = get_te32(&jni_onload_sym->st_value);
371 jni_onload_va = 0; // FIXME not understood; need example
372 }
373 }
374}
375
376#define WANT_EHDR_ENUM
377#define WANT_REL_ENUM
378#include "p_elf_enum.h"
379#undef WANT_REL_ENUM
380#undef WANT_EHDR_ENUM
381
382off_t PackLinuxElf::pack3(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft) // return length of output
383{
384 if (!fo) {
385 return 0;
386 }
387 unsigned disp;
388 unsigned len = sz_pack2a; // after headers and all PT_LOAD
389
390 unsigned const t = (4 & len) ^ ((!!xct_off)<<2); // 0 or 4
391 if (t) {
392 if (fo) {
393 unsigned const zero = 0;
394 fo->write(&zero, t);
395 }
396 len += t; // force sz_pack2 (0 mod 8) [see below]
397 }
398
399 set_te32(&disp, sz_elf_hdrs + usizeof(p_info) + usizeof(l_info) +
400 (!!xct_off & !!opt->o_unix.android_shlib)); // |1 iff android shlib
401 fo->write(&disp, sizeof(disp)); // offset(b_info)
402 // FIXME: If is_shlib then that is useful only for the is_asl bit.
403 // Better info is the word below with (overlay_offset - sizeof(linfo)).
404
405 len += sizeof(disp);
406 set_te32(&disp, len); // distance back to beginning (detect dynamic reloc)
407 fo->write(&disp, sizeof(disp));
408 len += sizeof(disp);
409
410 if (xct_off) { // is_shlib
411 upx_uint64_t const firstpc_va = (jni_onload_va
412 ? jni_onload_va
413 : user_init_va);
414 set_te32(&disp, firstpc_va - load_va);
415 fo->write(&disp, sizeof(disp)); // DT_INIT.d_val or DT_INIT_ARRAY[0]
416 len += sizeof(disp);
417
418 set_te32(&disp, xct_off);
419 fo->write(&disp, sizeof(disp)); // offset(lowest_executable_instr)
420 len += sizeof(disp);
421
422 if (opt->o_unix.android_shlib) {
423 xct_off += asl_delta; // the extra page
424 }
425 set_te32(&disp, overlay_offset - sizeof(linfo));
426 fo->write(&disp, sizeof(disp)); // &{l_info; p_info; b_info}
427 len += sizeof(disp);
428 }
429 total_out += len - sz_pack2a;
430 sz_pack2 = len; // 0 mod 8 [see above]
431
432 // FIXME: debugging aid: entry to decompressor
433 if (lowmem.getSize()) {
434 Elf32_Ehdr *const ehdr = (Elf32_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0];
435 set_te32(&ehdr->e_entry, sz_pack2); // hint for decompressor
436 }
437 // end debugging aid
438
439 super::pack3(fo, ft); // append the decompressor
440 set_te16(&linfo.l_lsize, up4( // MATCH03: up4
441 get_te16(&linfo.l_lsize) + len - sz_pack2a));
442 total_out = fpad4(fo, total_out); // MATCH03
443 return total_out;
444}
445
446static unsigned
447is_pow2(u64_t x)
448{
449 return !((-1+ x) & x);
450}
451
452Elf32_Phdr const *
453PackLinuxElf32::elf_find_Phdr_for_va(upx_uint32_t addr, Elf32_Phdr const *phdr, unsigned phnum)
454{
455 for (unsigned j = 0; j < phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
456 u32_t align = get_te32(&phdr->p_align);
457 if (is_LOAD(phdr)
458 && is_pow2(align) && !((-1+ align) &
459 (get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr) ^ get_te32(&phdr->p_offset)))
460 && (addr - get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr)) < get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz)) {
461 return phdr;
462 }
463 }
464 return nullptr;
465}
466
467Elf64_Phdr const *
468PackLinuxElf64::elf_find_Phdr_for_va(upx_uint64_t addr, Elf64_Phdr const *phdr, unsigned phnum)
469{
470 for (unsigned j = 0; j < phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
471 u64_t align = get_te64(&phdr->p_align);
472 if (is_LOAD(phdr)
473 && is_pow2(align) && !((-1+ align) &
474 (get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr) ^ get_te64(&phdr->p_offset)))
475 && (addr - get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr)) < get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz)) {
476 return phdr;
477 }
478 }
479 return nullptr;
480}
481
482void
483PackLinuxElf32::asl_slide_Shdrs()
484{
485 Elf32_Shdr *shdr = shdro;
486 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_shnum; ++shdr, ++j) {
487 unsigned sh_offset = get_te32(&shdr->sh_offset);
488 if (xct_off < sh_offset) {
489 set_te32(&shdr->sh_offset, so_slide + sh_offset);
490 }
491 }
492}
493
494// C_BASE covers the convex hull of the PT_LOAD of the uncompressed module.
495// It has (PF_W & .p_flags), and is ".bss": empty (0==.p_filesz, except a bug
496// in Linux kernel forces 0x1000==.p_filesz) with .p_memsz equal to the brk(0).
497// It is first in order to reserve all // pages, in particular so that if
498// (64K == .p_align) but at runtime (4K == PAGE_SIZE) then the Linux kernel
499// does not put [vdso] and [vvar] into alignment holes that the UPX runtime stub
500// will overwrite.
501//
502// Note that C_TEXT[.p_vaddr, +.p_memsz) is a subset of C_BASE.
503// This requires that the kernel process the ELFxx_Phdr in ascending order,
504// and does not mind the overlap. The UPX runtime stub will "re-program"
505// the memory regions anyway.
506enum { // ordinals in ELFxx_Phdr[] of compressed output
507 C_BASE = 0 // reserve address space
508 , C_TEXT = 1 // compressed data and stub
509 , C_NOTE = 2 // PT_NOTE copied from input
510 , C_GSTK = 3 // PT_GNU_STACK; will be 2 if no PT_NOTE
511};
512
513off_t PackLinuxElf32::pack3(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft)
514{
515 if (!overlay_offset) {
516 overlay_offset = sizeof(linfo) + (xct_off ? xct_off : sz_elf_hdrs);
517 }
518
519 total_out = super::pack3(fo, ft); // loader follows compressed PT_LOADs
520 if (fo && xct_off && Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT != upx_dt_init) { // patch user_init_rp
521 // init_array[0] must have R_$(ARCH)_RELATIVE relocation.
522 fo->seek((char *)user_init_rp - (char *)&file_image[0], SEEK_SET);
523 Elf32_Rel rel(*(Elf32_Rel const *)user_init_rp);
524 u32_t r_info = get_te32(&((Elf32_Rel const *)user_init_rp)->r_info);
525 u32_t r_type = (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386 == e_machine) ? R_386_RELATIVE
526 : (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine) ? R_ARM_RELATIVE
527 : (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC == e_machine) ? R_PPC_RELATIVE
528 : (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS == e_machine) ? R_MIPS_32
529 : 0;
530 set_te32(&rel.r_info, ELF32_R_INFO(ELF32_R_SYM(r_info), r_type));
531 fo->rewrite(&rel, sizeof(rel));
532 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
533
534 // Value of init_array[0] will be changed later.
535 // See write() of 'cpr_entry' below.
536 }
537 // NOTE: PackLinuxElf::pack3 adjusted xct_off for the extra page
538
539 // Then compressed gaps (including debuginfo.)
540 for (unsigned k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k) {
541 Extent x;
542 x.size = find_LOAD_gap(phdri, k, e_phnum);
543 if (x.size) {
544 x.offset = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_offset) +
545 get_te32(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
546 packExtent(x, nullptr, fo);
547 }
548 }
549 // write block end marker (uncompressed size 0)
550 b_info hdr; memset(&hdr, 0, sizeof(hdr));
551 set_le32(&hdr.sz_cpr, UPX_MAGIC_LE32);
552 fo->write(&hdr, sizeof(hdr));
553 total_out = fpad4(fo, total_out);
554
555 if (0==xct_off) { // not shared library
556 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_align, 0u - page_mask);
557 elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_paddr = elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
558 elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_offset = 0;
559 unsigned abrk = getbrk(phdri, e_phnum);
560 // vbase handles ET_EXEC. FIXME: pre-linking?
561 unsigned vbase = get_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr);
562 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_filesz, 0x1000); // Linux kernel SIGSEGV if (0==.p_filesz)
563 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_memsz, abrk - vbase);
564 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_W|Elf32_Phdr::PF_R);
565 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
566 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_memsz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
567 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr, abrk= (page_mask & (~page_mask + abrk)));
568 elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_paddr = elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr;
569 set_te32(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry, abrk + get_te32(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry) - vbase);
570 }
571 if (0!=xct_off) { // shared library
572 unsigned const cpr_entry = load_va + sz_pack2;
573 set_te32(&file_image[user_init_off], cpr_entry); // set the hook
574
575 if (user_init_rp) { // decompressor needs hint for DT_INIT_ARRAY
576 Elf32_Dyn *dynp = (Elf32_Dyn *)elf_find_dynptr(Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL);
577 set_te32(&dynp->d_val, (char *)user_init_rp - (char *)&file_image[0]);
578 }
579
580 Elf32_Phdr *const phdr0 = (Elf32_Phdr *)lowmem.subref(
581 "bad e_phoff", e_phoff, e_phnum * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
582 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = phdr0;
583 upx_off_t off = fo->st_size(); // 64 bits
584 so_slide = 0;
585 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
586 // p_vaddr and p_paddr do not change!
587 unsigned const len = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
588 unsigned const ioff = get_te32(&phdri[j].p_offset); // without asl_delta
589 unsigned align= get_te32(&phdr->p_align);
590 unsigned const type = get_te32(&phdr->p_type);
591 if (Elf32_Phdr::PT_INTERP==type) {
592 // Rotate to highest position, so it can be lopped
593 // by decrementing e_phnum.
594 memcpy((unsigned char *)ibuf, phdr, sizeof(*phdr)); // extract
595 memmove(phdr, 1+phdr, (e_phnum - (1+ j))*sizeof(*phdr)); // overlapping
596 memcpy(&phdr[e_phnum - (1+ j)], (unsigned char *)ibuf, sizeof(*phdr)); // to top
597 --phdr; --e_phnum;
598 set_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum, e_phnum);
599 set_te16(&((Elf32_Ehdr *)(unsigned char *)lowmem)->e_phnum, e_phnum);
600 continue;
601 }
602 if (PT_LOAD == type) {
603 if (!ioff) { // first PT_LOAD must contain everything written so far
604 set_te32(&phdr->p_filesz, sz_pack2 + lsize); // is this correct?
605 set_te32(&phdr->p_memsz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
606 }
607 else if ((xct_off - ioff) < len) { // Change length of compressed PT_LOAD.
608 set_te32(&phdr->p_filesz, total_out - ioff); // FIXME (sz_pack2 + lsize - ioff) ?
609 set_te32(&phdr->p_memsz, total_out - ioff);
610 if (user_init_off < xct_off) { // MIPS puts PT_DYNAMIC here
611 // Allow for DT_INIT in a new [stolen] slot
612 unsigned off2 = user_init_off - sizeof(unsigned);
613 fo->seek(off2, SEEK_SET);
614 fo->rewrite(&file_image[off2], 2*sizeof(unsigned));
615 }
616 }
617 else if (xct_off < ioff) { // Slide subsequent PT_LOAD.
618 if ((1u<<12) < align
619 && ( Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386 == e_machine
620 || Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine) // FIXME: other $ARCH ?
621 ) {
622 align = 1u<<12;
623 set_te32(&phdr->p_align, align);
624 }
625 off = fpadN(fo, (-1 + align) & (ioff - off));
626 if (!so_slide) {
627 so_slide = off - ((is_asl ? asl_delta : 0) + ioff);
628 //asl_slide_Shdrs();
629 }
630 set_te32(&phdr->p_offset, off);
631 fo->seek(off, SEEK_SET);
632 fo->write(&file_image[ioff], len);
633 off += len;
634 total_out = off;
635
636 if ((user_init_off - ioff) < len) {
637 fo->seek(user_init_off + so_slide, SEEK_SET);
638 unsigned word = cpr_entry;
639 set_te32(&word, cpr_entry);
640 fo->rewrite(&word, sizeof(word));
641 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
642 }
643 }
644 continue; // all done with this PT_LOAD
645 }
646 if (xct_off < ioff) {
647 set_te32(&phdr->p_offset, so_slide + (is_asl ? asl_delta : 0) + ioff);
648 }
649 } // end each Phdr
650
651 if (sec_arm_attr || is_asl) { // must update Shdr.sh_offset for so_slide
652 Elf32_Shdr *shdr = shdri;
653 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_shnum; ++shdr, ++j) {
654 unsigned sh_type = get_te32(&shdr->sh_type);
655 if (Elf32_Shdr::SHT_REL == sh_type
656 && n_jmp_slot // FIXME who sets this?
657 && !strcmp(".rel.plt", get_te32(&shdr->sh_name) + shstrtab)) {
658 unsigned va = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_PLTGOT)
659 - (is_asl ? asl_delta : 0);
660 // Now use the old Phdrs (phdri)
661 Elf32_Phdr const *phva;
662 phva = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(va, phdri, e_phnum);
663 unsigned old_off = (va - get_te32(&phva->p_vaddr))
664 + get_te32(&phva->p_offset);
665
666 // Now use the new Phdrs (phdr0)
667 va += (is_asl ? asl_delta : 0);
668 phva = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(va, phdr0, e_phnum);
669 unsigned new_off = (va - get_te32(&phva->p_vaddr))
670 + get_te32(&phva->p_offset);
671
672 if (fo && n_jmp_slot) {
673 fo->seek(new_off, SEEK_SET);
674 fo->rewrite(&file_image[old_off], n_jmp_slot * 4);
675 }
676 }
677 if (j && shdr->sh_addr == 0
678 && get_te32(&shdr->sh_offset) < xct_off) {
679 // Try to be nice by sliding; but still fails if compressed.
680 // So don't do it unless appending plain text of shstrtab.
681 unsigned sh_off = get_te32(&shdr->sh_offset);
682 if (xct_off < sh_off) {
683 set_te32(&shdr->sh_offset, sh_off + so_slide);
684 }
685 }
686 }
687 // Maybe: append plain text of shstrtab strings?
688 fo->seek(total_out, SEEK_SET);
689 if (xct_off < e_shoff) {
690 set_te32(&((Elf32_Ehdr *)lowmem.getVoidPtr())->e_shoff, total_out);
691 if (fo) {
692 fo->write(shdri, e_shnum * sizeof(*shdr));
693 total_out += e_shnum * sizeof(*shdr);
694 }
695 }
696 }
697 else { // output has no Shdr
698 ehdri.e_shnum = 0;
699 ehdri.e_shoff = 0;
700 ehdri.e_shstrndx = 0;
701 }
702 }
703 return total_out;
704}
705
706off_t PackLinuxElf64::pack3(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft)
707{
708 if (!overlay_offset) {
709 overlay_offset = sizeof(linfo) + (xct_off ? xct_off : sz_elf_hdrs);
710 }
711
712 total_out = super::pack3(fo, ft); // loader follows compressed PT_LOADs
713 if (fo && xct_off && Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT != upx_dt_init) { // patch user_init_rp
714 fo->seek((char *)user_init_rp - (char *)&file_image[0], SEEK_SET);
715 Elf64_Rela rela(*(Elf64_Rela const *)user_init_rp);
716 //u64_t r_info = get_te64(&((Elf64_Rela const *)user_init_rp)->r_info);
717 u32_t r_type = (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64 == e_machine) ? R_AARCH64_RELATIVE
718 : (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64 == e_machine) ? R_X86_64_RELATIVE
719 : (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64 == e_machine) ? R_PPC64_RELATIVE
720 : 0;
721 set_te64(&rela.r_info, ELF64_R_INFO(0 /*ELF64_R_SYM(r_info)*/, r_type));
722 set_te64(&rela.r_addend, sz_pack2); // entry to decompressor
723 fo->rewrite(&rela, sizeof(rela));
724
725 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
726 }
727 // NOTE: PackLinuxElf::pack3 adjusted xct_off for the extra page
728
729 // Then compressed gaps (including debuginfo.)
730 for (unsigned k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k) {
731 Extent x;
732 x.size = find_LOAD_gap(phdri, k, e_phnum);
733 if (x.size) {
734 x.offset = get_te64(&phdri[k].p_offset) +
735 get_te64(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
736 packExtent(x, nullptr, fo);
737 }
738 }
739 // write block end marker (uncompressed size 0)
740 b_info hdr; memset(&hdr, 0, sizeof(hdr));
741 set_le32(&hdr.sz_cpr, UPX_MAGIC_LE32);
742 fo->write(&hdr, sizeof(hdr));
743 total_out = fpad4(fo, total_out);
744
745 if (0==xct_off) { // not shared library
746 set_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_align, ((u64_t)0) - page_mask);
747 elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_paddr = elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
748 elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_offset = 0;
749 u64_t abrk = getbrk(phdri, e_phnum);
750 // vbase handles ET_EXEC. FIXME: pre-linking?
751 u64_t const vbase = get_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr);
752 set_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_filesz, 0x1000); // Linux kernel SIGSEGV if (0==.p_filesz)
753 set_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_memsz, abrk - vbase);
754 set_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_BASE].p_flags, Elf64_Phdr::PF_W|Elf64_Phdr::PF_R);
755 set_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
756 set_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_memsz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
757 set_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr, abrk= (page_mask & (~page_mask + abrk)));
758 elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_paddr = elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr;
759 set_te64(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry, abrk + get_te64(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry) - vbase);
760 }
761 if (0!=xct_off) { // shared library
762 u64_t const cpr_entry = load_va + sz_pack2;
763 set_te64(&file_image[user_init_off], cpr_entry); // set the hook
764
765 if (user_init_rp) { // decompressor needs hint for DT_INIT_ARRAY
766 Elf64_Dyn *dynp = (Elf64_Dyn *)elf_find_dynptr(Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL);
767 set_te64(&dynp->d_val, (char *)user_init_rp - (char *)&file_image[0]);
768 }
769
770 Elf64_Phdr *const phdr0 = (Elf64_Phdr *)lowmem.subref(
771 "bad e_phoff", e_phoff, e_phnum * sizeof(Elf64_Phdr));
772 Elf64_Phdr *phdr = phdr0;
773 upx_off_t off = fo->st_size(); // 64 bits
774 so_slide = 0;
775 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
776 // p_vaddr and p_paddr do not change!
777 u64_t const len = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
778 u64_t const ioff = get_te64(&phdri[j].p_offset); // without asl_delta
779 u64_t align= get_te64(&phdr->p_align);
780 unsigned const type = get_te32(&phdr->p_type);
781 if (Elf64_Phdr::PT_INTERP==type) {
782 // Rotate to highest position, so it can be lopped
783 // by decrementing e_phnum.
784 memcpy((unsigned char *)ibuf, phdr, sizeof(*phdr)); // extract
785 memmove(phdr, 1+phdr, (e_phnum - (1+ j))*sizeof(*phdr)); // overlapping
786 memcpy(&phdr[e_phnum - (1+ j)], (unsigned char *)ibuf, sizeof(*phdr)); // to top
787 --phdr; --e_phnum;
788 set_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum, e_phnum);
789 set_te16(&((Elf64_Ehdr *)(unsigned char *)lowmem)->e_phnum, e_phnum);
790 continue;
791 }
792 if (PT_LOAD == type) {
793 if (!ioff) { // first PT_LOAD must contain everything written so far
794 set_te64(&phdr->p_filesz, sz_pack2 + lsize); // is this correct?
795 set_te64(&phdr->p_memsz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
796 }
797 else if ((xct_off - ioff) < len) { // Change length of compressed PT_LOAD.
798 set_te64(&phdr->p_filesz, total_out - ioff); // FIXME (sz_pack2 + lsize - ioff) ?
799 set_te64(&phdr->p_memsz, total_out - ioff);
800 if (user_init_off < xct_off) { // MIPS puts PT_DYNAMIC here
801 // Allow for DT_INIT in a new [stolen] slot
802 unsigned off2 = user_init_off - sizeof(u64_t);
803 fo->seek(off2, SEEK_SET);
804 fo->rewrite(&file_image[off2], 2*sizeof(u64_t));
805 }
806 }
807 else if (xct_off < ioff) { // Slide subsequent PT_LOAD.
808 if ((1u<<12) < align
809 && Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64 == e_machine // FIXME: other $ARCH ?
810 ) {
811 align = 1u<<12;
812 set_te64(&phdr->p_align, align);
813 }
814 off = fpadN(fo, (-1 + align) & (ioff - off));
815 if (!so_slide) {
816 so_slide = off - ((is_asl ? asl_delta : 0) + ioff);
817 //asl_slide_Shdrs();
818 }
819 set_te64(&phdr->p_offset, off);
820 fo->seek(off, SEEK_SET);
821 fo->write(&file_image[ioff], len);
822 off += len;
823 total_out = off;
824
825 if ((user_init_off - ioff) < len) {
826 fo->seek(user_init_off + so_slide, SEEK_SET);
827 u64_t word = cpr_entry;
828 set_te64(&word, cpr_entry);
829 fo->rewrite(&word, sizeof(word));
830 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
831 }
832 }
833 continue; // all done with this PT_LOAD
834 }
835 if (xct_off < ioff) {
836 set_te64(&phdr->p_offset, so_slide + (is_asl ? asl_delta : 0) + ioff);
837 }
838 } // end each Phdr
839
840 if (sec_arm_attr || is_asl) { // must update Shdr.sh_offset for so_slide
841 // Update {DYNAMIC}.sh_offset by so_slide.
842 Elf64_Shdr *shdr = (Elf64_Shdr *)lowmem.subref( // FIXME: use shdri ?
843 "bad e_shoff", xct_off - (is_asl ? asl_delta : 0), e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
844 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_shnum; ++shdr, ++j) {
845 unsigned sh_type = get_te32(&shdr->sh_type);
846 unsigned sh_flags = get_te64(&shdr->sh_flags); // all SHF_ are 32-bit anyway
847 unsigned sh_offset = get_te64(&shdr->sh_offset); // already asl_delta
848 if (Elf64_Shdr::SHF_ALLOC & sh_flags
849 && Elf64_Shdr::SHF_WRITE & sh_flags
850 && xct_off < sh_offset) {
851 set_te64(&shdr->sh_offset, so_slide + sh_offset);
852 }
853 if (Elf64_Shdr::SHT_RELA == sh_type
854 && n_jmp_slot // FIXME: does this apply to SHT_RELA ?
855 && !strcmp(".rel.plt", get_te32(&shdr->sh_name) + shstrtab)) {
856 u64_t va = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_PLTGOT) - (is_asl ? asl_delta : 0);
857 // Now use the old Phdrs (phdri)
858 Elf64_Phdr const *phva;
859 phva = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(va, phdri, e_phnum);
860 u64_t old_off = (va - get_te64(&phva->p_vaddr))
861 + get_te64(&phva->p_offset);
862
863 // Now use the new Phdrs (phdr0)
864 va += (is_asl ? asl_delta : 0);
865 phva = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(va, phdr0, e_phnum);
866 u64_t new_off = (va - get_te64(&phva->p_vaddr))
867 + get_te64(&phva->p_offset);
868
869 if (fo && n_jmp_slot) {
870 fo->seek(new_off, SEEK_SET);
871 fo->rewrite(&file_image[old_off], n_jmp_slot * 8);
872 }
873 }
874 if (j && shdr->sh_addr == 0
875 && get_te64_32(&shdr->sh_offset) < xct_off) { // UPX_RSIZE_MAX_MEM protects us
876 // Try to be nice by sliding; but still fails if compressed.
877 // So don't do it unless appending plain text of shstrtab.
878 unsigned sh_off = get_te64_32(&shdr->sh_offset); // UPX_RSIZE_MAX_MEM protects us
879 if (xct_off < sh_off) {
880 set_te64(&shdr->sh_offset, sh_off + so_slide);
881 }
882 }
883 }
884 // Maybe: append plain text of shstrtab strings?
885 fo->seek(total_out, SEEK_SET);
886 if (xct_off < e_shoff) {
887 set_te32(&((Elf32_Ehdr *)lowmem.getVoidPtr())->e_shoff, total_out);
888 if (fo) {
889 fo->write(shdri, e_shnum * sizeof(*shdr));
890 total_out += e_shnum * sizeof(*shdr);
891 }
892 }
893 }
894 else { // output has no Shdr
895 ehdri.e_shnum = 0;
896 ehdri.e_shoff = 0;
897 ehdri.e_shstrndx = 0;
898 }
899 }
900 return total_out;
901}
902
903void
904PackLinuxElf::addStubEntrySections(Filter const *, unsigned m_decompr)
905{
906 (void)m_decompr; // FIXME
907 if (hasLoaderSection("ELFMAINX")) {
908 addLoader("ELFMAINX", nullptr);
909 }
910 if (hasLoaderSection("ELFMAINXu")) {
911 // brk() trouble if static
912 addLoader("ELFMAINXu", nullptr);
913 }
914 addLoader(
915 ( M_IS_NRV2E(ph_forced_method(ph.method)) ? "NRV_HEAD,NRV2E,NRV_TAIL"
916 : M_IS_NRV2D(ph_forced_method(ph.method)) ? "NRV_HEAD,NRV2D,NRV_TAIL"
917 : M_IS_NRV2B(ph_forced_method(ph.method)) ? "NRV_HEAD,NRV2B,NRV_TAIL"
918 : M_IS_LZMA(ph_forced_method(ph.method)) ? "LZMA_ELF00,LZMA_DEC20,LZMA_DEC30"
919 : nullptr), nullptr);
920 if (hasLoaderSection("CFLUSH"))
921 addLoader("CFLUSH");
922 addLoader("ELFMAINY,IDENTSTR", nullptr);
923 if (hasLoaderSection("ELFMAINZe")) { // ppc64 big-endian only
924 addLoader("ELFMAINZe", nullptr);
925 }
926 addLoader("+40,ELFMAINZ", nullptr);
927 if (hasLoaderSection("ANDMAJNZ")) { // Android trouble with args to DT_INIT
928 if (opt->o_unix.android_shlib) {
929 addLoader("ANDMAJNZ", nullptr); // constant PAGE_SIZE
930 }
931 else {
932 addLoader("ELFMAJNZ", nullptr); // PAGE_SIZE from AT_PAGESZ
933 }
934 addLoader("ELFMAKNZ", nullptr);
935 }
936 if (hasLoaderSection("ELFMAINZu")) {
937 addLoader("ELFMAINZu", nullptr);
938 }
939 addLoader("FOLDEXEC", nullptr);
940}

943void PackLinuxElf::defineSymbols(Filter const *)
944{
945 linker->defineSymbol("O_BINFO", o_binfo
946 | ((!!opt->o_unix.is_ptinterp) << 0)
947 | ((!!opt->o_unix.unmap_all_pages) << 1) );
948}

951{
952 PackLinuxElf::defineSymbols(ft);
953}

955void PackLinuxElf64::defineSymbols(Filter const *ft)

957 PackLinuxElf::defineSymbols(ft);

959
960PackLinuxElf32::PackLinuxElf32(InputFile *f)
961 : super(f), phdri(nullptr), shdri(nullptr),
962 n_phdrx(0), sz_phdrx(0),
963 page_mask(~0u<<lg2_page),
964 dynseg(nullptr), hashtab(nullptr), hashend(nullptr),
965 gashtab(nullptr), gashend(nullptr), dynsym(nullptr),
966 jni_onload_sym(nullptr),
967 sec_strndx(nullptr), sec_dynsym(nullptr), sec_dynstr(nullptr)
968 , sec_arm_attr(nullptr)
969{
970 memset(&ehdri, 0, sizeof(ehdri));
971 n_jmp_slot = 0;
972 if (f) {
973 f->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
974 f->readx(&ehdri, sizeof(ehdri));
975 }
976}

982void PackLinuxElf32::add_phdrx(Elf32_Phdr const *phdr)
983{
984 if (END_PHDRX <= n_phdrx) {
985 throwCantPack("too many Phdr %u", (unsigned)(phdr - phdri));
986 }
987 phdrx[n_phdrx++] = phdr;
988}

995 gashtab(nullptr), gashend(nullptr), dynsym(nullptr),
996 jni_onload_sym(nullptr),
997 sec_strndx(nullptr), sec_dynsym(nullptr), sec_dynstr(nullptr)

999{

1003 f->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
1004 f->readx(&ehdri, sizeof(ehdri));
1005 }

1019
1020// FIXME: should be templated with PackLinuxElf32help1
1021void
1022PackLinuxElf64::PackLinuxElf64help1(InputFile *f)
1023{
1024 e_type = get_te16(&ehdri.e_type);
1025 e_phnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum);
1026 e_shnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_shnum);
1027 unsigned const e_phentsize = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phentsize);
1028 if (memcmp((char const *)&ehdri, "\x7f\x45\x4c\x46", 4) // "\177ELF"
1029 || ehdri.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_CLASS]!=Elf64_Ehdr::ELFCLASS64
1030 || sizeof(Elf64_Phdr) != e_phentsize
1031 || (Elf64_Ehdr::ELFDATA2MSB == ehdri.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_DATA]
1032 && &N_BELE_RTP::be_policy != bele)
1033 || (Elf64_Ehdr::ELFDATA2LSB == ehdri.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_DATA]
1034 && &N_BELE_RTP::le_policy != bele)) {
1035 e_phoff = 0;
1036 e_shoff = 0;
1037 sz_phdrs = 0;
1038 return;
1039 }
1040 if (0==e_phnum) throwCantUnpack("0==e_phnum");
1041 e_phoff = get_te64(&ehdri.e_phoff);
1042 upx_uint64_t const last_Phdr = e_phoff + e_phnum * sizeof(Elf64_Phdr);
1043 if (last_Phdr < e_phoff // wrap-around
1044 || e_phoff != sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) // must be contiguous
1045 || (unsigned long)file_size < last_Phdr) {
1046 throwCantUnpack("bad e_phoff %p", (void *)e_phoff);
1047 }
1048 e_shoff = get_te64(&ehdri.e_shoff);
1049 upx_uint64_t const last_Shdr = e_shoff + e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr);
1050 if (last_Shdr < e_shoff // wrap-around
1051 || (e_shnum && e_shoff < last_Phdr)
1052 || (unsigned long)file_size < last_Shdr) {
1053 if (opt->cmd == CMD_COMPRESS) {
1054 throwCantUnpack("bad e_shoff %p", (void *)e_shoff);
1055 }
1056 }
1057 sz_phdrs = e_phnum * e_phentsize;
1058 sz_elf_hdrs = sz_phdrs + sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) +
1059 n_phdrx * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr); // phdrx bodies later: ::generateElfHdr
1060
1061 if (f && Elf64_Ehdr::ET_DYN!=e_type) {
1062 unsigned const len = file_size; // (sz_phdrs + e_phoff) except --preserve-build-id
1063 alloc_file_image(file_image, len);
1064 f->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
1065 f->readx(file_image, len);
1066 phdri= (Elf64_Phdr *)(e_phoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
1067 }
1068 if (f && Elf64_Ehdr::ET_DYN==e_type) {
1069 // The DT_SYMTAB has no designated length. Read the whole file.
1070 alloc_file_image(file_image, file_size);
1071 f->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
1072 f->readx(file_image, file_size);
1073 phdri= (file_size <= (unsigned)e_phoff) ? nullptr : (Elf64_Phdr *)(e_phoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
1074 if (!(opt->cmd == CMD_COMPRESS && e_shoff < (upx_uint64_t)file_size && mb_shdr.getSize() == 0)) {
1075 shdri = nullptr;
1076 }
1077 else if (e_shnum && e_shoff && ehdri.e_shentsize) {
1078 fi->seek(e_shoff, SEEK_SET);
1079 mb_shdr.alloc( sizeof(Elf64_Shdr) * e_shnum);
1080 shdri = (Elf64_Shdr *)mb_shdr.getVoidPtr();
1081 fi->readx(shdri, sizeof(Elf64_Shdr) * e_shnum);
1082 }
1083 else {
1084 shdri = nullptr;
1085 }
1086 sec_dynsym = elf_find_section_type(Elf64_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
1087 if (sec_dynsym) {
1088 unsigned t = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_link);
1089 if (e_shnum <= t)
1090 throwCantPack("bad dynsym->sh_link");
1091 sec_dynstr = &shdri[t];
1092 }
1093
1094 Elf64_Phdr const *phdr= phdri;
1095 for (int j = e_phnum; --j>=0; ++phdr)
1096 if (Elf64_Phdr::PT_DYNAMIC==get_te32(&phdr->p_type)) {
1097 upx_uint64_t offset = check_pt_dynamic(phdr);
1098 dynseg= (Elf64_Dyn *)(offset + file_image);
1099 invert_pt_dynamic(dynseg,
1100 umin(get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz), file_size_u - offset));
1101 }
1102 else if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
1103 check_pt_load(phdr);
1104 }
1105 // elf_find_dynamic() returns 0 if 0==dynseg.
1106 dynstr = (char const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
1107 dynsym = (Elf64_Sym /*const*/ *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB);
1108 gashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
1109 hashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_HASH);
1110 if (3& ((upx_uintptr_t)dynsym | (upx_uintptr_t)gashtab | (upx_uintptr_t)hashtab)) {
1111 throwCantPack("unaligned DT_SYMTAB, DT_GNU_HASH, or DT_HASH/n");
1112 }
1113 jni_onload_sym = elf_lookup("JNI_OnLoad");
1114 if (jni_onload_sym) {
1115 jni_onload_va = get_te64(&jni_onload_sym->st_value);
1116 jni_onload_va = 0; // FIXME not understood; need example
1117 }
1118 }
1119}

1203void PackLinuxElf32::ARM_updateLoader(OutputFile * /*fo*/)
1204{
1205 set_te32(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry, sz_pack2 +
1206 linker->getSymbolOffset("_start") +
1207 get_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr));
1208}

1213}

1218}

1229
1230void PackLinuxElf32::updateLoader(OutputFile * /*fo*/)
1231{
1232 unsigned start = linker->getSymbolOffset("_start");
1233 unsigned vbase = get_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr);
1234 set_te32(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry, start + sz_pack2 + vbase);
1235}
1236
1237void PackLinuxElf64::updateLoader(OutputFile * /*fo*/)
1238{
1239 if (xct_off) {
1240 return; // FIXME elfout has no values at all
1241 }
1242 upx_uint64_t const vbase = get_te64(&elfout.phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr);
1243 unsigned start = linker->getSymbolOffset("_start");
1244
1245 if (get_te16(&elfout.ehdr.e_machine)==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64
1246 && elfout.ehdr.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_DATA]==Elf64_Ehdr::ELFDATA2MSB) {
1247 unsigned descr = linker->getSymbolOffset("entry_descr");
1248
1249 // External relocation of PPC64 function descriptor.
1250 upx_uint64_t dot_entry = start + sz_pack2 + vbase;
1251 upx_byte *p = getLoader();
1252
1253 set_te64(&p[descr], dot_entry);
1254 // Kernel 3.16.0 (2017-09-19) uses start, not descr
1255 set_te64(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry, start + sz_pack2 + vbase);
1256 }
1257 else {
1258 set_te64(&elfout.ehdr.e_entry, start + sz_pack2 + vbase);
1259 }
1260}

1344
1345void PackLinuxElf32x86::addStubEntrySections(Filter const *ft, unsigned m_decompr)
1346{
1347 (void)m_decompr; // FIXME
1348 int const n_mru = ft->n_mru; // FIXME: belongs to filter? packerf?
1349
1350// Rely on "+80CXXXX" [etc] in getDecompressorSections() packer_c.cpp */
1351// // Here is a quick summary of the format of the output file:
1352// linker->setLoaderAlignOffset(
1353// // Elf32_Ehdr
1354// sizeof(elfout.ehdr) +
1355// // Elf32_Phdr: 1 for exec86, 2 for sh86, 3 for elf86
1356// (get_te16(&elfout.ehdr.e_phentsize) * get_te16(&elfout.ehdr.e_phnum)) +
1357// // checksum UPX! lsize version format
1358// sizeof(l_info) +
1359// // PT_DYNAMIC with DT_NEEDED "forwarded" from original file
1360// ((get_te16(&elfout.ehdr.e_phnum)==3)
1361// ? (unsigned) get_te32(&elfout.phdr[C_NOTE].p_memsz)
1362// : 0) +
1363// // p_progid, p_filesize, p_blocksize
1364// sizeof(p_info) +
1365// // compressed data
1366// b_len + ph.c_len );
1367
1368 // entry to stub
1369 addLoader("LEXEC000", nullptr);
1370
1371 if (ft->id) {
1372 { // decompr, unfilter are separate
1373 addLoader("LXUNF000", nullptr);
1374 addLoader("LXUNF002", nullptr);
1375 if (0x80==(ft->id & 0xF0)) {
1376 if (256==n_mru) {
1377 addLoader("MRUBYTE0", nullptr);
1378 }
1379 else if (n_mru) {
1380 addLoader("LXMRU005", nullptr);
1381 }
1382 if (n_mru) {
1383 addLoader("LXMRU006", nullptr);
1384 }
1385 else {
1386 addLoader("LXMRU007", nullptr);
1387 }
1388 }
1389 else if (0x40==(ft->id & 0xF0)) {
1390 addLoader("LXUNF008", nullptr);
1391 }
1392 addLoader("LXUNF010", nullptr);
1393 }
1394 if (n_mru) {
1395 addLoader("LEXEC009", nullptr);
1396 }
1397 }
1398 addLoader("LEXEC010", nullptr);
1399 addLoader(getDecompressorSections(), nullptr);
1400 addLoader("LEXEC015", nullptr);
1401 if (ft->id) {
1402 { // decompr, unfilter are separate
1403 if (0x80!=(ft->id & 0xF0)) {
1404 addLoader("LXUNF042", nullptr);
1405 }
1406 }
1407 addFilter32(ft->id);
1408 { // decompr, unfilter are separate
1409 if (0x80==(ft->id & 0xF0)) {
1410 if (0==n_mru) {
1411 addLoader("LXMRU058", nullptr);
1412 }
1413 }
1414 addLoader("LXUNF035", nullptr);
1415 }
1416 }
1417 else {
1418 addLoader("LEXEC017", nullptr);
1419 }
1420
1421 addLoader("IDENTSTR", nullptr);
1422 addLoader("+40,LEXEC020", nullptr);
1423 addLoader("FOLDEXEC", nullptr);
1424}
1425
1426void PackLinuxElf32x86::defineSymbols(Filter const *const ft)
1427{
1428 PackLinuxElf32::defineSymbols(ft);
1429
1430 if (0x80==(ft->id & 0xF0)) {
1431 int const mru = ft->n_mru ? 1+ ft->n_mru : 0;
1432 if (mru && mru!=256) {
1433 unsigned const is_pwr2 = (0==((mru -1) & mru));
1434 linker->defineSymbol("NMRU", mru - is_pwr2);
1435 }
1436 }
1437}
1438
1439void
1440PackLinuxElf32::buildLinuxLoader(
1441 upx_byte const *const proto,
1442 unsigned const szproto,
1443 upx_byte const *const fold,
1444 unsigned const szfold,
1445 Filter const *ft
1446)
1447{
1448 MemBuffer mb_cprLoader;
1449 unsigned sz_cpr = 0;
1450 unsigned sz_unc = 0;
1451 unsigned method = 0;
1452 upx_byte const *uncLoader = nullptr;
1453
1454 if (0 < szfold) {
1455 if (xct_off // shlib
1456 && ( this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM
1457 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386)
1458 ) {
1459 initLoader(fold, szfold);
1460// Typical layout of 'sections' in compressed stub code for shared library:
1461// SO_HEAD
1462// ptr_NEXT
1463// EXP_HEAD NRV getbit(), copy
1464// NRV2B etc: daisy chain of de-compressor for each method used
1465// EXP_TAIL FIXME: unfilter
1466// SO_TAIL
1467// SO_MAIN C-language supervision based on PT_LOADs
1468 char sec[120]; memset(sec, 0, sizeof(sec)); // debug convenience
1469 int len = 0;
1470 unsigned m_decompr = methods_used | (1u << ph_forced_method(ph.method));
1471 len += snprintf(sec, sizeof(sec), "%s", "SO_HEAD,ptr_NEXT,EXP_HEAD");
1472
1473 // Start of dasiy-chain fall-through.
1474 if (((1u<<M_NRV2B_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1475 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2B");
1476 }
1477 if (((1u<<M_NRV2D_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1478 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2D");
1479 }
1480 if (((1u<<M_NRV2E_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1481 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2E");
1482 }
1483 if (((1u<<M_LZMA)) & m_decompr) {
1484 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s",
1485 "LZMA_DAISY,LZMA_ELF00,LZMA_DEC20,LZMA_DEC30");
1486 }
1487 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "EXP_TAIL");
1488 // End of daisy-chain fall-through.
1489
1490 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s",
1491 (sec_arm_attr || is_asl || opt->o_unix.android_shlib)
1492 ? "HUMF_A,UMF_ANDROID"
1493 : "HUMF_L,UMF_LINUX");
1494 if (hasLoaderSection("STRCON")) {
1495 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "STRCON");
1496 }
1497 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "SO_TAIL,SO_MAIN");
1498 (void)len; // Pacify the anal-retentive static analyzer which hates a good idiom.
1499 NO_printf("\n%s\n", sec);
1500 addLoader(sec, nullptr);
1501 relocateLoader();
1502 {
1503 int sz_unc_int;
1504 uncLoader = linker->getLoader(&sz_unc_int);
1505 sz_unc = sz_unc_int;
1506 }
1507 method = M_NRV2B_LE32; // requires unaligned fetch
1508 if (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM)
1509 method = M_NRV2B_8; //only ARM v6 and above has unaligned fetch
1510 } // end shlib (folded portion)
1511 else if (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386
1512 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM
1513 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC
1514 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS
1515 ) { // main program with ELF2 de-compressor (folded portion)
1516 initLoader(fold, szfold);
1517 char sec[120]; memset(sec, 0, sizeof(sec)); // debug convenience
1518 int len = 0;
1519 unsigned m_decompr = methods_used | (1u << ph_forced_method(ph.method));
1520 len += snprintf(sec, sizeof(sec), "%s", ".text,EXP_HEAD");
1521 if (((1u<<M_NRV2B_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1522 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2B");
1523 }
1524 if (((1u<<M_NRV2D_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1525 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2D");
1526 }
1527 if (((1u<<M_NRV2E_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1528 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2E");
1529 }
1530 if (((1u<<M_LZMA)) & m_decompr) {
1531 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s",
1532 "LZMA_DAISY,LZMA_ELF00,LZMA_DEC20,LZMA_DEC30");
1533 }
1534 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "EXP_TAIL");
1535
1536 // $ARCH-linux.elf-main2.c calls upx_mmap_and_fd, not direct memfd_create
1537 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s",
1538 (sec_arm_attr || is_asl || opt->o_unix.android_shlib)
1539 ? "HUMF_A,UMF_ANDROID"
1540 : "HUMF_L,UMF_LINUX");
1541 if (hasLoaderSection("SYSCALLS")) {
1542 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "SYSCALLS");
1543 }
1544 (void)len; // Pacify the anal-retentive static analyzer which hates a good idiom.
1545 NO_printf("\n%s\n", sec);
1546 addLoader(sec, nullptr);
1547 relocateLoader();
1548 {
1549 int sz_unc_int;
1550 uncLoader = linker->getLoader(&sz_unc_int);
1551 sz_unc = sz_unc_int;
1552 }
1553 method = M_NRV2B_LE32; // requires unaligned fetch
1554 if (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM)
1555 method = M_NRV2B_8; //only ARM v6 and above has unaligned fetch
1556 }
1557 else { // main program with ELF1 de-compressor (folded portion)
1558 cprElfHdr1 const *const hf = (cprElfHdr1 const *)fold;
1559 unsigned fold_hdrlen = usizeof(hf->ehdr) +
1560 get_te16(&hf->ehdr.e_phentsize) * get_te16(&hf->ehdr.e_phnum);
1561 if (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS) {
1562 fold_hdrlen = upx::umax(fold_hdrlen, (unsigned)0x80);
1563 }
1564 uncLoader = fold_hdrlen + fold;
1565 sz_unc = ((szfold < fold_hdrlen) ? 0 : (szfold - fold_hdrlen));
1566 method = ph.method;
1567 }
1568
1569 struct b_info h; memset(&h, 0, sizeof(h));
1570 h.b_method = method;
1571 // _Ehdr and _Phdr are NOT filtered, so Leave h.b_ftid and h.b_cto8 as zero.
1572
1573 mb_cprLoader.allocForCompression(sizeof(h) + sz_unc);
1574 unsigned char *const cprLoader = (unsigned char *)mb_cprLoader; // less typing
1575
1576 h.sz_unc = sz_unc;
1577 h.sz_cpr = mb_cprLoader.getSize(); // max that upx_compress may use
1578 {
1579 int r = upx_compress(uncLoader, sz_unc, sizeof(h) + cprLoader, &sz_cpr,
1580 nullptr, ph_forced_method(method), 10, nullptr, nullptr );
1581 h.sz_cpr = sz_cpr; // actual length used
1582 if (r != UPX_E_OK || h.sz_cpr >= h.sz_unc)
1583 throwInternalError("loader compression failed");
1584 }
1585 set_te32(&h.sz_cpr, h.sz_cpr);
1586 set_te32(&h.sz_unc, h.sz_unc);
1587 memcpy(cprLoader, &h, sizeof(h)); // cprLoader will become FOLDEXEC
1588 } // end (0 < szfold)
1589
1590 initLoader(proto, szproto, -1, sz_cpr);
1591 NO_printf("FOLDEXEC unc=%#x cpr=%#x\n", sz_unc, sz_cpr);
1592 linker->addSection("FOLDEXEC", mb_cprLoader, sizeof(b_info) + sz_cpr, 0);
1593 if (xct_off // shlib
1594 && (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_NONE
1595 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386
1596 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM
1597 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC
1598 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS
1599 )
1600 ) { // shlib with ELF2 de-compressor
1601 addLoader("ELFMAINX");
1602 addLoader((sec_arm_attr || is_asl || opt->o_unix.android_shlib)
1603 ? "HUMF_A,UMF_ANDROID"
1604 : "HUMF_L,UMF_LINUX");
1605 addLoader("ELFMAINZ,FOLDEXEC,IDENTSTR");
1606 }
1607 else if (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_NONE
1608 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386
1609 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM
1610 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC
1611 || this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS
1612 ) { // main program with ELF2 de-compressor
1613 addLoader("ELFMAINX");
1614
1615 // Only if $ARCH-linux.elf-entry.S calls upx_mmap_and_fd instead of memfd_create
1616 if (this->e_machine != Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC
1617 && this->e_machine != Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS)
1618 addLoader((sec_arm_attr || is_asl || opt->o_unix.android_shlib)
1619 ? "HUMF_A,UMF_ANDROID"
1620 : "HUMF_L,UMF_LINUX");
1621 addLoader("ELFMAINZ,FOLDEXEC,IDENTSTR");
1622 defineSymbols(ft);
1623 }
1624 else { // main program with ELF1 de-compressor
1625 addStubEntrySections(ft, methods_used | (1u << ph_forced_method(ph.method)) );
1626 if (!xct_off) { // main program
1627 defineSymbols(ft);
1628 }
1629 }
1630 relocateLoader();
1631}
1632
1633void
1634PackLinuxElf64::buildLinuxLoader(
1635 upx_byte const *const proto,
1636 unsigned const szproto,
1637 upx_byte const *const fold,
1638 unsigned const szfold,
1639 Filter const *ft
1640)
1641{
1642 MemBuffer mb_cprLoader;
1643 unsigned sz_cpr = 0;
1644 unsigned sz_unc = 0;
1645 unsigned method = 0;
1646 upx_byte const *uncLoader = nullptr;
1647
1648 if (0 < szfold) {
1649 if (xct_off // shlib
1650 && ( this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64
1651 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64)
1652 ) {
1653 initLoader(fold, szfold);
1654// Typical layout of 'sections' in compressed stub code for shared library:
1655// SO_HEAD
1656// ptr_NEXT
1657// EXP_HEAD NRV getbit(), copy
1658// NRV2B etc: daisy chain of de-compressor for each method used
1659// EXP_TAIL FIXME: unfilter
1660// SO_TAIL
1661// SO_MAIN C-language supervision based on PT_LOADs
1662 char sec[120]; memset(sec, 0, sizeof(sec)); // debug convenience
1663 int len = 0;
1664 unsigned m_decompr = methods_used | (1u << ph_forced_method(ph.method));
1665 len += snprintf(sec, sizeof(sec), "%s", "SO_HEAD,ptr_NEXT,EXP_HEAD");
1666
1667 // Start of dasiy-chain fall-through.
1668 if (((1u<<M_NRV2B_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1669 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2B");
1670 }
1671 if (((1u<<M_NRV2D_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1672 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2D");
1673 }
1674 if (((1u<<M_NRV2E_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1675 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2E");
1676 }
1677 if (((1u<<M_LZMA)) & m_decompr) {
1678 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s",
1679 "LZMA_DAISY,LZMA_ELF00,LZMA_DEC20,LZMA_DEC30");
1680 }
1681 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "EXP_TAIL");
1682 // End of daisy-chain fall-through.
1683
1684 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "HUMF_L,UMF_LINUX");
1685 if (hasLoaderSection("STRCON")) {
1686 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "STRCON");
1687 }
1688 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "SO_TAIL,SO_MAIN");
1689 (void)len; // Pacify the anal-retentive static analyzer which hates a good idiom.
1690 NO_printf("\n%s\n", sec);
1691 addLoader(sec, nullptr);
1692 relocateLoader();
1693 {
1694 int sz_unc_int;
1695 uncLoader = linker->getLoader(&sz_unc_int);
1696 sz_unc = sz_unc_int;
1697 }
1698 method = M_NRV2B_LE32; // requires unaligned fetch
1699 }
1700 else if (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_NONE
1701 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64
1702 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64
1703 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64
1704 ) { // main program with ELF2 de-compressor (folded portion)
1705 initLoader(fold, szfold);
1706 char sec[120]; memset(sec, 0, sizeof(sec)); // debug convenience
1707 int len = 0;
1708 unsigned m_decompr = methods_used | (1u << ph_forced_method(ph.method));
1709 len += snprintf(sec, sizeof(sec), "%s", ".text,EXP_HEAD");
1710 if (((1u<<M_NRV2B_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2B_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1711 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2B");
1712 }
1713 if (((1u<<M_NRV2D_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2D_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1714 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2D");
1715 }
1716 if (((1u<<M_NRV2E_LE32)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_8)|(1u<<M_NRV2E_LE16)) & m_decompr) {
1717 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "NRV2E");
1718 }
1719 if (((1u<<M_LZMA)) & m_decompr) {
1720 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s",
1721 "LZMA_DAISY,LZMA_ELF00,LZMA_DEC20,LZMA_DEC30");
1722 }
1723 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "EXP_TAIL");
1724 if (hasLoaderSection("SYSCALLS")) {
1725 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "SYSCALLS");
1726 }
1727 if (hasLoaderSection("STRCON")) {
1728 len += snprintf(&sec[len], sizeof(sec) - len, ",%s", "STRCON");
1729 }
1730 (void)len;
1731 NO_printf("\n%s\n", sec);
1732 addLoader(sec, nullptr);
1733 relocateLoader();
1734 {
1735 int sz_unc_int;
1736 uncLoader = linker->getLoader(&sz_unc_int);
1737 sz_unc = sz_unc_int;
1738 }
1739 method = M_NRV2B_LE32; // requires unaligned fetch
1740 }
1741 else { // not shlib: main program with ELF1 de-compressor
1742 cprElfHdr1 const *hf = (cprElfHdr1 const *)fold;
1743 e_type = get_te16(&hf->ehdr.e_type);
1744 if (ET_REL == e_type) {
1745 initLoader(fold, szfold);
1746 addLoader(".text", nullptr);
1747 relocateLoader();
1748 int sz_unc_int(0);
1749 uncLoader = linker->getLoader(&sz_unc_int);
1750 sz_unc = sz_unc_int;
1751 }
1752 else if (ET_EXEC == e_type) {
1753 hf = (cprElfHdr1 const *)fold;
1754 unsigned fold_hdrlen = usizeof(hf->ehdr) +
1755 get_te16(&hf->ehdr.e_phentsize) * get_te16(&hf->ehdr.e_phnum);
1756 if (this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64) {
1757 fold_hdrlen = get_te64(&hf->ehdr.e_entry);
1758 }
1759 uncLoader = &fold[fold_hdrlen];
1760 sz_unc = ((szfold < fold_hdrlen) ? 0 : (szfold - fold_hdrlen));
1761 }
1762 method = ph.method;
1763 }
1764
1765 struct b_info h; memset(&h, 0, sizeof(h));
1766 h.b_method = method;
1767 // _Ehdr and _Phdr are NOT filtered, so Leave h.b_ftid and h.b_cto8 as zero.
1768
1769 mb_cprLoader.allocForCompression(sizeof(h) + sz_unc);
1770 unsigned char *const cprLoader = (unsigned char *)mb_cprLoader; // less typing
1771
1772 h.sz_unc = sz_unc;
1773 h.sz_cpr = mb_cprLoader.getSize(); // max that upx_compress may use
1774 {
1775 int r = upx_compress(uncLoader, sz_unc, sizeof(h) + cprLoader, &sz_cpr,
1776 nullptr, ph_forced_method(method), 10, nullptr, nullptr );
1777 h.sz_cpr = sz_cpr; // actual length used
1778 if (r != UPX_E_OK || h.sz_cpr >= h.sz_unc)
1779 throwInternalError("loader compression failed");
1780 }
1781 set_te32(&h.sz_cpr, h.sz_cpr);
1782 set_te32(&h.sz_unc, h.sz_unc);
1783 memcpy(cprLoader, &h, sizeof(h)); // cprLoader will become FOLDEXEC
1784 } // end (0 < szfold)
1785
1786 initLoader(proto, szproto, -1, sz_cpr);
1787 NO_printf("FOLDEXEC unc=%#x cpr=%#x\n", sz_unc, sz_cpr);
1788 linker->addSection("FOLDEXEC", mb_cprLoader, sizeof(b_info) + sz_cpr, 0);
1789 if (xct_off
1790 && (this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_NONE
1791 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64
1792 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64
1793 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64
1794 )
1795 ) {
1796 addLoader("ELFMAINX,ELFMAINZ,FOLDEXEC,IDENTSTR");
1797 } // shlib
1798 else if (this->e_machine==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_NONE
1799 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64
1800 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64
1801 || this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64
1802 ) { // main program with ELF2 de-compressor
1803 addLoader("ELFMAINX,ELFMAINZ,FOLDEXEC,IDENTSTR");
1804 if (this->e_machine==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64
1805 && elfout.ehdr.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_DATA]==Elf64_Ehdr::ELFDATA2MSB) {
1806 addLoader("ELFMAINZe");
1807 }
1808 if (!xct_off) { // main program
1809 defineSymbols(ft);
1810 }
1811 }
1812 else { // main program with ELF1 de-compressor
1813 addStubEntrySections(ft, methods_used | (1u << ph_forced_method(ph.method)) );
1814 if (!xct_off) { // main program
1815 defineSymbols(ft);
1816 }
1817 }
1818 relocateLoader();
1819}
1820

1822PackLinuxElf64amd::defineSymbols(Filter const *ft)
1823{
1824 PackLinuxElf64::defineSymbols(ft);
1825}

1827static const CLANG_FORMAT_DUMMY_STATEMENT
1828#include "stub/i386-linux.elf-entry.h"
1829static const CLANG_FORMAT_DUMMY_STATEMENT
1830#include "stub/i386-linux.elf-so_entry.h"
1831static const CLANG_FORMAT_DUMMY_STATEMENT
1832#include "stub/i386-linux.elf-fold.h"
1833static const CLANG_FORMAT_DUMMY_STATEMENT
1834#include "stub/i386-linux.elf-so_fold.h"
1835static const CLANG_FORMAT_DUMMY_STATEMENT
1836#include "stub/i386-linux.shlib-init.h"
1837
1838void
1839PackLinuxElf32x86::buildLoader(const Filter *ft)
1840{
1841 if (0!=xct_off) { // shared library
1842 buildLinuxLoader(
1843 stub_i386_linux_elf_so_entry, sizeof(stub_i386_linux_elf_so_entry),
1844 stub_i386_linux_elf_so_fold, sizeof(stub_i386_linux_elf_so_fold), ft);
1845 return;
1846 }
1847 unsigned char tmp[sizeof(stub_i386_linux_elf_fold)];
1848 memcpy(tmp, stub_i386_linux_elf_fold, sizeof(stub_i386_linux_elf_fold));
1849 checkPatch(nullptr, 0, 0, 0); // reset
1850 if (opt->o_unix.is_ptinterp) {
1851 unsigned j;
1852 for (j = 0; j < sizeof(stub_i386_linux_elf_fold)-1; ++j) {
1853 if (0x60==tmp[ j]
1854 && 0x47==tmp[1+j] ) {
1855 /* put INC EDI before PUSHA: inhibits auxv_up for PT_INTERP */
1856 tmp[ j] = 0x47;
1857 tmp[1+j] = 0x60;
1858 break;
1859 }
1860 }
1861 }
1862 buildLinuxLoader(
1863 stub_i386_linux_elf_entry, sizeof(stub_i386_linux_elf_entry),
1864 tmp, sizeof(stub_i386_linux_elf_fold), ft );
1865}

2142
2143 // DT_HASH, DT_GNU_HASH have no explicit length (except in ElfXX_Shdr),
2144 // so it is hard to detect when the index of a hash chain is out-of-bounds.
2145 // Workaround: Assume no overlap of DT_* tables (and often contiguous.)
2146 // Then any given table ends at least as early as when another table begins.
2147 // So find the tables, and sort the offsets.
2148 // The 32-bit DT_xxxxx keys have the same values as 64-bit DT_xxxxx keys.
2149static unsigned const dt_keys[] = {
2150 Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB,
2151 Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERSYM, // not small integer
2152 Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERNEED, // not small integer
2153 Elf64_Dyn::DT_HASH,
2154 Elf64_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH, // not small integer
2155 Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB,
2156 Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERDEF, // not small integer
2157 Elf64_Dyn::DT_REL,
2158 Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELA,
2159 Elf64_Dyn::DT_FINI_ARRAY,
2160 Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY,
2161 Elf64_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY,
2162 0,
2163};
2164
2165static int __acc_cdecl_qsort
2166qcmp_unsigned(void const *const aa, void const *const bb)
2167{
2168 unsigned a = *(unsigned const *)aa;
2169 unsigned b = *(unsigned const *)bb;
2170 if (a < b) return -1;
2171 if (a > b) return 1;
2172 return 0;
2173}
2174
2175void
2176PackLinuxElf32::sort_DT32_offsets(Elf32_Dyn const *const dynp0)
2177{
2178 mb_dt_offsets.alloc(sizeof(unsigned) * sizeof(dt_keys)/sizeof(dt_keys[0]));
2179 mb_dt_offsets.clear();
2180 dt_offsets = (unsigned *)mb_dt_offsets.getVoidPtr();
2181 unsigned n_off = 0, k;
2182 for (unsigned j=0; ((k = dt_keys[j]), k); ++j) {
2183 dt_offsets[n_off] = 0; // default to "not found"
2184 u32_t rva = 0;
2185 if (k < DT_NUM) { // in range of easy table
2186 if (!dt_table[k]) {
2187 continue; // not present in input
2188 }
2189 rva = get_te32(&dynp0[-1+ dt_table[k]].d_val);
2190 }
2191 else if (file_image) { // why is this guard necessary?
2192 rva = elf_unsigned_dynamic(k); // zero if not found
2193 }
2194 if (!rva) {
2195 continue; // not present in input
2196 }
2197 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(rva, phdri, e_phnum);
2198 if (!phdr) {
2199 char msg[60]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad DT_{%#x} = %#x (no Phdr)",
2200 k, rva);
2201 throwCantPack(msg);
2202 }
2203 dt_offsets[n_off] = (rva - get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr)) + get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
2204
2205 if (file_size <= dt_offsets[n_off]) {
2206 char msg[60]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad DT_{%#x} = %#x (beyond EOF)",
2207 k, dt_offsets[n_off]);
2208 throwCantPack(msg);
2209 }
2210 n_off += !!dt_offsets[n_off];
2211 }
2212 dt_offsets[n_off++] = file_size; // sentinel
2213 upx_qsort(dt_offsets, n_off, sizeof(dt_offsets[0]), qcmp_unsigned);
2214}
2215
2216unsigned PackLinuxElf32::find_dt_ndx(unsigned rva)
2217{
2218 unsigned *const dto = (unsigned *)mb_dt_offsets.getVoidPtr();
2219 unsigned const dto_size = mb_dt_offsets.getSize() / sizeof(*dto);
2220 for (unsigned j = 0; j < dto_size && dto[j]; ++j) { // linear search of short table
2221 if (rva == dto[j]) {
2222 return j;
2223 }
2224 }
2225 return ~0u;
2226}
2227
2228unsigned PackLinuxElf32::elf_find_table_size(unsigned dt_type, unsigned sh_type)
2229{
2230 Elf32_Shdr const *sec = elf_find_section_type(sh_type);
2231 if (sec) { // Cheat the easy way: use _Shdr. (No _Shdr anyway for de-compression)
2232 return get_te32(&sec->sh_size);
2233 }
2234 // Honest hard work: use _Phdr
2235 unsigned x_rva;
2236 if (dt_type < DT_NUM) {
2237 unsigned const x_ndx = dt_table[dt_type];
2238 if (!x_ndx) { // no such entry
2239 return 0;
2240 }
2241 x_rva = get_te32(&dynseg[-1+ x_ndx].d_val);
2242 }
2243 else {
2244 x_rva = elf_unsigned_dynamic(dt_type);
2245 }
2246 Elf32_Phdr const *const x_phdr = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(x_rva, phdri, e_phnum);
2247 unsigned const d_off = x_rva - get_te32(&x_phdr->p_vaddr);
2248 unsigned const y_ndx = find_dt_ndx(d_off + get_te32(&x_phdr->p_offset));
2249 if (~0u != y_ndx) {
2250 return dt_offsets[1+ y_ndx] - dt_offsets[y_ndx];
2251 }
2252 return ~0u;
2253}
2254
2255void
2256PackLinuxElf32::invert_pt_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn const *dynp, u32_t headway)
2257{
2258 if (dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL]) {
2259 return; // not 1st time; do not change upx_dt_init
2260 }
2261 Elf32_Dyn const *const dynp0 = dynp;
2262 unsigned ndx = 0;
2263 unsigned const limit = headway / sizeof(*dynp);
2264 if (dynp)
2265 for (; ; ++ndx, ++dynp) {
2266 if (limit <= ndx) {
2267 throwCantPack("DT_NULL not found");
2268 }
2269 u32_t const d_tag = get_te32(&dynp->d_tag);
2270 if (d_tag < DT_NUM) {
2271 if (Elf32_Dyn::DT_NEEDED != d_tag
2272 && dt_table[d_tag]
2273 && get_te32(&dynp->d_val)
2274 != get_te32(&dynp0[-1+ dt_table[d_tag]].d_val)) {
2275 throwCantPack("duplicate DT_%#x: [%#x] [%#x]",
2276 (unsigned)d_tag, -1+ dt_table[d_tag], ndx);
2277 }
2278 dt_table[d_tag] = 1+ ndx;
2279 }
2280 if (Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL == d_tag) {
2281 break; // check here so that dt_table[DT_NULL] is set
2282 }
2283 }
2284 sort_DT32_offsets(dynp0);
2285
2286 upx_dt_init = 0;
2287 if (dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT]) upx_dt_init = Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT;
2288 else if (dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY]) upx_dt_init = Elf32_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY;
2289 else if (dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY]) upx_dt_init = Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY;
2290
2291 unsigned const z_str = dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRSZ];
2292 strtab_max = !z_str ? 0 : get_te32(&dynp0[-1+ z_str].d_val);
2293 unsigned const z_tab = dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRTAB];
2294 unsigned const tmp1 = get_te32(&dynp0[-1+ z_tab].d_val);
2295 if (tmp1 < sz_elf_hdrs) {
2296 throwCantPack("bad DT_STRTAB %#x", tmp1);
2297 }
2298 unsigned const strtab_beg = !z_tab ? 0 : elf_get_offset_from_address(tmp1);
2299
2300 if (!z_str || !z_tab
2301 || (this->file_size - strtab_beg) < strtab_max // strtab overlaps EOF
2302 // last string in table must have terminating NUL
2303 || '\0' != ((char *)file_image.getVoidPtr())[-1+ strtab_max + strtab_beg]
2304 ) {
2305 throwCantPack("bad DT_STRSZ %#x", strtab_max);
2306 }
2307
2308 // Find end of DT_SYMTAB
2309 unsigned const tmp2 = elf_find_table_size(Elf32_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB,
2310 Elf32_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
2311 symnum_max = (~0u == tmp2) ? 0 : tmp1 / sizeof(Elf32_Sym);
2312
2313 unsigned v_sym = dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB];
2314 if (v_sym) {
2315 v_sym = elf_get_offset_from_address(get_te32(&dynp0[-1+ v_sym].d_val));
2316 }
2317 unsigned v_hsh = dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_HASH];
2318 if (v_hsh) {
2319 v_hsh = elf_get_offset_from_address(get_te32(&dynp0[-1+ v_hsh].d_val));
2320 }
2321 if (v_hsh && file_image) {
2322 hashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_HASH);
2323 if (!hashtab) {
2324 throwCantPack("bad DT_HASH %#x", v_hsh);
2325 }
2326 // Find end of DT_HASH
2327 hashend = (unsigned const *)(void const *)(elf_find_table_size(
2328 Elf32_Dyn::DT_HASH, Elf32_Shdr::SHT_HASH) + (char const *)hashtab);
2329
2330 unsigned const nbucket = get_te32(&hashtab[0]);
2331 unsigned const *const buckets = &hashtab[2];
2332 unsigned const *const chains = &buckets[nbucket]; (void)chains;
2333 if ((unsigned)(file_size - ((char const *)buckets - (char const *)(void const *)file_image))
2334 <= sizeof(unsigned)*nbucket ) {
2335 throwCantPack("bad nbucket %#x\n", nbucket);
2336 }
2337
2338 if ((unsigned)(hashend - buckets) < nbucket
2339 || !v_sym || (unsigned)file_size <= v_sym
2340 || ((v_hsh < v_sym) && (v_sym - v_hsh) < sizeof(*buckets)*(2+ nbucket))
2341 ) {
2342 throwCantPack("bad DT_HASH nbucket=%#x len=%#x",
2343 nbucket, (v_sym - v_hsh));
2344 }
2345 unsigned chmax = 0;
2346 for (unsigned j= 0; j < nbucket; ++j) {
2347 unsigned x = get_te32(&buckets[j]);
2348 if (chmax < x) {
2349 chmax = x;
2350 }
2351 }
2352 if ((v_hsh < v_sym) && (v_sym - v_hsh) <
2353 (sizeof(*buckets)*(2+ nbucket) + sizeof(*chains)*(1+ chmax))) {
2354 throwCantPack("bad DT_HASH nbucket=%#x len=%#x",
2355 nbucket, (v_sym - v_hsh));
2356 }
2357 }
2358 unsigned const v_gsh = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
2359 if (v_gsh && file_image) {
2360 // Not similar to DT_HASH because DT_GNU_HASH is not small (0x6ffffef5).
2361 gashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
2362 if (!gashtab) {
2363 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH %#x", v_gsh);
2364 }
2365 gashend = (unsigned const *)(void const *)(elf_find_table_size(
2366 Elf32_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH, Elf32_Shdr::SHT_GNU_HASH) + (char const *)gashtab);
2367 unsigned const n_bucket = get_te32(&gashtab[0]);
2368 unsigned const symbias = get_te32(&gashtab[1]);
2369 unsigned const n_bitmask = get_te32(&gashtab[2]);
2370 unsigned const gnu_shift = get_te32(&gashtab[3]);
2371 u32_t const *const bitmask = (u32_t const *)(void const *)&gashtab[4];
2372 unsigned const *const buckets = (unsigned const *)&bitmask[n_bitmask];
2373 unsigned const *const hasharr = &buckets[n_bucket]; (void)hasharr;
2374 if (!n_bucket || (1u<<31) <= n_bucket /* fie on fuzzers */
2375 || (unsigned)(gashend - buckets) < n_bucket
2376 || (file_size + file_image) <= (void const *)hasharr) {
2377 throwCantPack("bad n_bucket %#x\n", n_bucket);
2378 }
2379 // It would be better to detect zeroes shifted into low 5 bits of:
2380 // (037 & (hash_32 >> gnu_shift))
2381 // but compilers can be stupid.
2382 if (31 < gnu_shift) {
2383 throwCantPack("bad gnu_shift %#x", gnu_shift);
2384 }
2385 // unsigned const *const gashend = &hasharr[n_bucket];
2386 // minimum, except:
2387 // Rust and Android trim unused zeroes from high end of hasharr[]
2388 unsigned bmax = 0;
2389 for (unsigned j= 0; j < n_bucket; ++j) {
2390 unsigned bj = get_te32(&buckets[j]);
2391 if (bj) {
2392 if (bj < symbias) {
2393 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH bucket[%d] < symbias{%#x}\n",
2394 bj, symbias);
2395 }
2396 if (bmax < bj) {
2397 bmax = bj;
2398 }
2399 }
2400 }
2401 if (1==n_bucket && 0==buckets[0]
2402 && 1==n_bitmask && 0==bitmask[0]) {
2403 // 2021-09-11 Rust on RaspberryPi apparently uses this to minimize space.
2404 // But then the DT_GNU_HASH symbol lookup algorithm always fails?
2405 // https://github.com/upx/upx/issues/525
2406 } else
2407 if (bmax) {
2408 if ((1+ bmax) < symbias) {
2409 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH (1+ max_bucket)=%#x < symbias=%#x",
2410 1+ bmax, symbias);
2411 }
2412 bmax -= symbias;
2413 }
2414
2415 unsigned r = 0;
2416 if (!n_bucket || !n_bitmask || !v_sym
2417 || (r=1, ((-1+ n_bitmask) & n_bitmask)) // not a power of 2
2418 || (r=2, (8*sizeof(u32_t) <= gnu_shift)) // shifted result always == 0
2419 || (r=3, (n_bucket>>30)) // fie on fuzzers
2420 || (r=4, (n_bitmask>>30))
2421 || (r=5, ((file_size/sizeof(unsigned))
2422 <= ((sizeof(*bitmask)/sizeof(unsigned))*n_bitmask + 2*n_bucket))) // FIXME: weak
2423 || (r=6, ((v_gsh < v_sym) && (v_sym - v_gsh) < (sizeof(unsigned)*4 // headers
2424 + sizeof(*bitmask)*n_bitmask // bitmask
2425 + sizeof(*buckets)*n_bucket // buckets
2426 + sizeof(*hasharr)*(!bmax ? 0 : (1+ bmax)) // hasharr
2427 )) )
2428 ) {
2429 char msg[90]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2430 "bad DT_GNU_HASH n_bucket=%#x n_bitmask=%#x len=%#lx r=%d",
2431 n_bucket, n_bitmask, (long unsigned)(v_sym - v_gsh), r);
2432 throwCantPack(msg);
2433 }
2434 }
2435 e_shstrndx = get_te16(&ehdri.e_shstrndx); // who omitted this?
2436 if (e_shnum <= e_shstrndx
2437 && !(0==e_shnum && 0==e_shstrndx) ) {
2438 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2439 "bad .e_shstrndx %d >= .e_shnum %d", e_shstrndx, e_shnum);
2440 throwCantPack(msg);
2441 }
2442}

2445PackLinuxElf32::elf_find_ptype(unsigned type, Elf32_Phdr const *phdr, unsigned phnum)
2446{
2447 for (unsigned j = 0; j < phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
2448 if (type == get_te32(&phdr->p_type)) {
2449 return phdr;
2450 }
2451 }
2452 return nullptr;
2453}

2465
2466Elf32_Shdr const *PackLinuxElf32::elf_find_section_name(
2467 char const *const name
2468) const
2469{
2470 Elf32_Shdr const *shdr = shdri;
2471 if (!shdr) {
2472 return nullptr;
2473 }
2474 int j = e_shnum;
2475 for (; 0 <=--j; ++shdr) {
2476 unsigned const sh_name = get_te32(&shdr->sh_name);
2477 if ((u32_t)file_size <= sh_name) { // FIXME: weak
2478 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2479 "bad Elf32_Shdr[%d].sh_name %#x",
2480 -1+ e_shnum -j, sh_name);
2481 throwCantPack(msg);
2482 }
2483 if (0==strcmp(name, &shstrtab[sh_name])) {
2484 return shdr;
2485 }
2486 }
2487 return nullptr;
2488}
