2566
2567bool PackLinuxElf64::calls_crt1(Elf64_Rela const *rela, int sz)
2568{
2569 if (!dynsym || !dynstr || !rela) {
2570 return false;
2571 }
2572 for (unsigned relnum= 0; 0 < sz; (sz -= sizeof(Elf64_Rela)), ++rela, ++relnum) {
2573 unsigned const symnum = get_te64(&rela->r_info) >> 32;
2574 char const *const symnam = get_dynsym_name(symnum, relnum);
2575 if (0==strcmp(symnam, "__libc_start_main") // glibc
2576 || 0==strcmp(symnam, "__libc_init") // Android
2577 || 0==strcmp(symnam, "__uClibc_main")
2578 || 0==strcmp(symnam, "__uClibc_start_main"))
2579 return true;
2580 }
2581 return false;
2582}
2583
2584char const *PackLinuxElf32::get_str_name(unsigned st_name, unsigned symnum) const
2585{
2586 if (strtab_max <= st_name) {
2587 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2588 "bad .st_name %#x in DT_SYMTAB[%d]\n", st_name, symnum);
2589 throwCantPack(msg);
2590 }
2591 return &dynstr[st_name];
2592}
2593
2594char const *PackLinuxElf32::get_dynsym_name(unsigned symnum, unsigned relnum) const
2595{
2596 if (symnum_max <= symnum) {
2597 (void)relnum;
2598 return nullptr;
2599 }
2600 return get_str_name(get_te32(&dynsym[symnum].st_name), symnum);
2601}
2602
2603bool PackLinuxElf32::calls_crt1(Elf32_Rel const *rel, int sz)
2604{
2605 if (!dynsym || !dynstr || !rel) {
2606 return false;
2607 }
2608 for (unsigned relnum= 0; 0 < sz; (sz -= sizeof(Elf32_Rel)), ++rel, ++relnum) {
2609 unsigned const symnum = get_te32(&rel->r_info) >> 8;
2610 char const *const symnam = get_dynsym_name(symnum, relnum);
2611 if (0==strcmp(symnam, "__libc_start_main") // glibc
2612 || 0==strcmp(symnam, "__libc_init") // Android
2613 || 0==strcmp(symnam, "__uClibc_main")
2614 || 0==strcmp(symnam, "__uClibc_start_main"))
2615 return true;
2616 }
2617 return false;
2618}
2619
2620tribool PackLinuxElf32::canUnpack() // bool, except -1: format known, but not packed
2621{
2622 if (checkEhdr(&ehdri)) {
2623 return false;
2624 }
2625 if (get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum) < 2) {
2626 throwCantUnpack("e_phnum must be >= 2");
2627 }
2628 if (Elf32_Ehdr::ET_DYN==get_te16(&ehdri.e_type)) {
2629 PackLinuxElf32help1(fi);
2630 }
2631 if (super::canUnpack()) {
2632 return true;
2633 }
2634 return false;
2635}
2636
2637bool // false [often throwCantPack]: some defect; true: good so far
2638PackLinuxElf32::canPackOSABI(Elf32_Ehdr const *ehdr)
2639{
2640 unsigned char osabi0 = ehdr->e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI];
2641 // The first PT_LOAD must cover the beginning of the file (0==p_offset).
2642 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr = phdri;
2643 note_size = 0;
2644 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
2645 if (j > ((MAX_ELF_HDR_32 - sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr)) / sizeof(Elf32_Phdr))) {
2646 throwCantPack("too many ElfXX_Phdr; try '--force-execve'");
2647 return false;
2648 }
2649 unsigned const p_type = get_te32(&phdr->p_type);
2650 unsigned const p_offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
2651 if (1!=exetype && PT_LOAD == p_type) { // 1st PT_LOAD
2652 exetype = 1;
2653 load_va = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr); // class data member
2654
2655 // Cast on next line is to avoid a compiler bug (incorrect complaint) in
2656 // Microsoft (R) C/C++ Optimizing Compiler Version 19.00.24215.1 for x64
2657 // error C4319: '~': zero extending 'unsigned int' to 'upx_uint64_t' of greater size
2658 unsigned const off = ~page_mask & (unsigned)load_va;
2659
2660 if (off && off == p_offset) { // specific hint
2661 throwCantPack("Go-language PT_LOAD: try hemfix.c, or try '--force-execve'");
2662 // Fixing it inside upx fails because packExtent() reads original file.
2663 return false;
2664 }
2665 if (0 != p_offset) { // 1st PT_LOAD must cover Ehdr and Phdr
2666 throwCantPack("first PT_LOAD.p_offset != 0; try '--force-execve'");
2667 return false;
2668 }
2669 hatch_off = ~3u & (3+ get_te32(&phdr->p_memsz));
2670 }
2671 if (EM_MIPS == e_machine
2672 && (Elf32_Phdr::PT_MIPS_ABIFLAGS == p_type
2673 || Elf32_Phdr::PT_MIPS_REGINFO == p_type)
2674 ) {
2675 add_phdrx(phdr); // PT_MIPS_*
2676 unsigned mask = -1+ get_te32(&phdr->p_align);
2677 sz_phdrx = ~mask & (mask + sz_phdrx);
2678 sz_phdrx += get_te32(&phdr->p_memsz);
2679
2680 }
2681 if (PT_NOTE32 == p_type) {
2682 if (osabi_note && Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_NONE==osabi0) { // Still seems to be generic.
2683 struct {
2684 struct Elf32_Nhdr nhdr;
2685 char name[8];
2686 unsigned body;
2687 } note;
2688 memset(&note, 0, sizeof(note));
2689 fi->seek(p_offset, SEEK_SET);
2690 fi->readx(&note, sizeof(note));
2691 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
2692 if (4==get_te32(&note.nhdr.descsz)
2693 && 1==get_te32(&note.nhdr.type)
2694 // && 0==note.end
2695 && (1+ strlen(osabi_note))==get_te32(&note.nhdr.namesz)
2696 && 0==strcmp(osabi_note, (char const *)&note.name[0])
2697 ) {
2698 osabi0 = ei_osabi; // Specified by PT_NOTE.
2699 }
2700 }
2701 }
2702 }
2703 if (Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_NONE ==osabi0
2704 || Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_LINUX==osabi0) { // No EI_OSBAI, no PT_NOTE.
2705 unsigned const arm_eabi = 0xff000000u & get_te32(&ehdr->e_flags);
2706 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM==e_machine
2707 && (EF_ARM_EABI_VER5==arm_eabi
2708 || EF_ARM_EABI_VER4==arm_eabi ) ) {
2709 // armel-eabi armeb-eabi ARM Linux EABI version 4 is a mess.
2710 ei_osabi = osabi0 = Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_LINUX;
2711 }
2712 else {
2713 osabi0 = opt->o_unix.osabi0; // Possibly specified by command-line.
2714 }
2715 }
2716 if (osabi0!=ei_osabi) {
2717 return false;
2718 }
2719 return true; // good so far
2720}
2721
2722#define WANT_SHDR_ENUM
2723#include "p_elf_enum.h"
2724#undef WANT_SHDR_ENUM
2725
2726upx_uint64_t PackLinuxElf32::canPack_Shdr(Elf32_Phdr const *pload_x0)
2727{
2728 Elf32_Shdr const *shdr_xva = nullptr;
2729 Elf32_Shdr const *shdr = shdri;
2730 for (int j= e_shnum; --j>=0; ++shdr) {
2731 unsigned const sh_type = get_te32(&shdr->sh_type);
2732 if (Elf32_Shdr::SHF_EXECINSTR & get_te32(&shdr->sh_flags)) {
2733 shdr_xva = shdr;
2734 xct_va = umin((unsigned) xct_va, get_te32(&shdr->sh_addr));
2735 }
2736 // Hook the first slot of DT_PREINIT_ARRAY or DT_INIT_ARRAY.
2737 if (!user_init_rp && (
2738 ( Elf32_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY==upx_dt_init
2739 && Elf32_Shdr::SHT_PREINIT_ARRAY==sh_type)
2740 || ( Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY ==upx_dt_init
2741 && Elf32_Shdr::SHT_INIT_ARRAY ==sh_type) )) {
2742 unsigned user_init_ava = get_te32(&shdr->sh_addr);
2743 user_init_off = get_te32(&shdr->sh_offset);
2744 if ((u32_t)file_size <= user_init_off) {
2745 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2746 "bad Elf32_Shdr[%d].sh_offset %#x",
2747 -1+ e_shnum - j, user_init_off);
2748 throwCantPack(msg);
2749 }
2750 // Check that &file_image[user_init_off] has
2751 // *_RELATIVE or *_ABS* relocation, and fetch user_init_va.
2752 // If Elf32_Rela then the actual value is in Rela.r_addend.
2753 int z_rel = dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_REL];
2754 int z_rsz = dt_table[Elf32_Dyn::DT_RELSZ];
2755 if (z_rel && z_rsz) {
2756 unsigned rel_off = get_te32(&dynseg[-1+ z_rel].d_val);
2757 if ((unsigned)file_size <= rel_off) {
2758 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2759 "bad Elf32_Dynamic[DT_REL] %#x\n",
2760 rel_off);
2761 throwCantPack(msg);
2762 }
2763 Elf32_Rel *rp = (Elf32_Rel *)&file_image[rel_off];
2764 unsigned relsz = get_te32(&dynseg[-1+ z_rsz].d_val);
2765 if ((unsigned)file_size <= relsz) {
2766 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2767 "bad Elf32_Dynamic[DT_RELSZ] %#x\n",
2768 relsz);
2769 throwCantPack(msg);
2770 }
2771 Elf32_Rel *last = (Elf32_Rel *)(relsz + (char *)rp);
2772 for (; rp < last; ++rp) {
2773 unsigned r_va = get_te32(&rp->r_offset);
2774 if (r_va == user_init_ava) { // found the Elf32_Rel
2775 user_init_rp = rp;
2776 unsigned r_info = get_te32(&rp->r_info);
2777 unsigned r_type = ELF32_R_TYPE(r_info);
2778 set_te32(&dynsym[0].st_name, r_va); // for decompressor
2779 set_te32(&dynsym[0].st_value, r_info);
2780 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine) {
2781 if (R_ARM_RELATIVE == r_type) {
2782 user_init_va = get_te32(&file_image[user_init_off]);
2783 }
2784 else if (R_ARM_ABS32 == r_type) {
2785 unsigned symj = ELF32_R_SYM(r_info);
2786 user_init_va = get_te32(&dynsym[symj].st_value);
2787 set_te32(&rp->r_info, ELF32_R_INFO(0, R_ARM_RELATIVE));
2788 // pack3() will set &file_image[user_init_off]
2789 }
2790 else {
2791 goto bad;
2792 }
2793 }
2794 else if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386 == e_machine) {
2795 if (R_386_RELATIVE == r_type) {
2796 user_init_va = get_te32(&file_image[user_init_off]);
2797 }
2798 else if (R_386_32 == r_type) {
2799 unsigned symj = ELF32_R_SYM(r_info);
2800 user_init_va = get_te32(&dynsym[symj].st_value);
2801 set_te32(&rp->r_info, ELF32_R_INFO(0, R_386_RELATIVE));
2802 // pack3() will set &file_image[user_init_off]
2803 }
2804 else {
2805 goto bad;
2806 }
2807 }
2808 else {
2809bad:
2810 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2811 "bad relocation %#x DT_INIT_ARRAY[0]",
2812 r_info);
2813 throwCantPack(msg);
2814 }
2815 break;
2816 }
2817 }
2818 }
2819 unsigned const p_filesz = get_te32(&pload_x0->p_filesz);
2820 if (!((user_init_va - xct_va) < p_filesz)) {
2821 // Not in executable portion of first executable PT_LOAD.
2822 if (0==user_init_va && opt->o_unix.android_shlib) {
2823 // Android allows (0 ==> skip) ?
2824 upx_dt_init = 0; // force steal of 'extra' DT_NULL
2825 // XXX: FIXME: depends on SHT_DYNAMIC coming later
2826 }
2827 else {
2828 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2829 "bad init address %#x in Elf32_Shdr[%d].%#x\n",
2830 (unsigned)user_init_va, -1+ e_shnum - j, user_init_off);
2831 throwCantPack(msg);
2832 }
2833 }
2834 }
2835 // By default /usr/bin/ld leaves 4 extra DT_NULL to support pre-linking.
2836 // Take one as a last resort.
2837 if ((Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT==upx_dt_init || !upx_dt_init)
2838 && Elf32_Shdr::SHT_DYNAMIC == sh_type) {
2839 unsigned sh_offset = get_te32(&shdr->sh_offset);
2840 unsigned sh_size = get_te32(&shdr->sh_size);
2841 if ((unsigned)file_size < sh_size
2842 || (unsigned)file_size < sh_offset
2843 || ((unsigned)file_size - sh_offset) < sh_size) {
2844 throwCantPack("bad SHT_DYNAMIC");
2845 }
2846 unsigned const n = get_te32(&shdr->sh_size) / sizeof(Elf32_Dyn);
2847 Elf32_Dyn *dynp = (Elf32_Dyn *)&file_image[get_te32(&shdr->sh_offset)];
2848 for (; Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL != dynp->d_tag; ++dynp) {
2849 if (upx_dt_init == get_te32(&dynp->d_tag)) {
2850 break; // re-found DT_INIT
2851 }
2852 }
2853 if ((1+ dynp) < (n+ dynseg)) { // not the terminator, so take it
2854 user_init_va = get_te32(&dynp->d_val); // 0 if (0==upx_dt_init)
2855 set_te32(&dynp->d_tag, upx_dt_init = Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT);
2856 user_init_off = (char const *)&dynp->d_val - (char const *)&file_image[0];
2857 }
2858 }
2859 }
2860 // If shdr_xva->sh_size is too small, then probably it won't compress.
2861 // So look for a Shdr that has PROGBITS and not SHF_WRITE, which is
2862 // much larger, and use that for the compressibility decision.
2863 if (shdr_xva->sh_size < 0x1000) {
2864 shdr = shdr_xva;
2865 while (SHT_PROGBITS == get_te32(&shdr[-1].sh_type)) --shdr; // backup
2866 for (; SHT_PROGBITS == get_te32(&shdr->sh_type)
2867 && !(SHF_WRITE & get_te32(&shdr->sh_flags)); ++shdr) {
2868 if (0x4000 <= get_te32(&shdr->sh_size)) {
2869 xct_va = get_te32(&shdr->sh_addr); // hopefully more compressible
2870 break;
2871 }
2872 }
2873 }
2874 return xct_va;
2875}
2876
2877upx_uint64_t PackLinuxElf64::canPack_Shdr(Elf64_Phdr const *pload_x0)
2878{
2879 Elf64_Shdr const *shdr_xva = nullptr;
2880 Elf64_Shdr const *shdr = shdri;
2881 for (int j= e_shnum; --j>=0; ++shdr) {
2882 unsigned const sh_type = get_te32(&shdr->sh_type);
2883 if (Elf64_Shdr::SHF_EXECINSTR & get_te64(&shdr->sh_flags)) {
2884 shdr_xva = shdr;
2885 xct_va = umin(xct_va, get_te64(&shdr->sh_addr));
2886 }
2887 // Hook the first slot of DT_PREINIT_ARRAY or DT_INIT_ARRAY.
2888 if (!user_init_rp && (
2889 ( Elf64_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY==upx_dt_init
2890 && Elf64_Shdr::SHT_PREINIT_ARRAY==sh_type)
2891 || ( Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY ==upx_dt_init
2892 && Elf64_Shdr::SHT_INIT_ARRAY ==sh_type) )) {
2893 unsigned user_init_ava = get_te64(&shdr->sh_addr);
2894 user_init_off = get_te64(&shdr->sh_offset);
2895 if ((u64_t)file_size <= user_init_off) {
2896 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2897 "bad Elf64_Shdr[%d].sh_offset %#x",
2898 -1+ e_shnum - j, user_init_off);
2899 throwCantPack(msg);
2900 }
2901 // Check that &file_image[user_init_off] has
2902 // *_RELATIVE or *_ABS* relocation, and fetch user_init_va.
2903 // If Elf_Rela then the actual value is in Rela.r_addend.
2904 int z_rel = dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELA];
2905 int z_rsz = dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELASZ];
2906 if (z_rel && z_rsz) {
2907 upx_uint64_t rel_off = get_te64(&dynseg[-1+ z_rel].d_val);
2908 if ((u64_t)file_size <= rel_off) {
2909 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2910 "bad Elf64_Dynamic[DT_RELA] %#llx\n",
2911 rel_off);
2912 throwCantPack(msg);
2913 }
2914 Elf64_Rela *rp = (Elf64_Rela *)&file_image[rel_off];
2915 upx_uint64_t relsz = get_te64(&dynseg[-1+ z_rsz].d_val);
2916 if ((u64_t)file_size <= relsz) {
2917 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2918 "bad Elf64_Dynamic[DT_RELASZ] %#llx\n",
2919 relsz);
2920 throwCantPack(msg);
2921 }
2922 Elf64_Rela *last = (Elf64_Rela *)(relsz + (char *)rp);
2923 for (; rp < last; ++rp) {
2924 upx_uint64_t r_va = get_te64(&rp->r_offset);
2925 if (r_va == user_init_ava) { // found the Elf64_Rela
2926 user_init_rp = rp;
2927 upx_uint64_t r_info = get_te64(&rp->r_info);
2928 unsigned r_type = ELF64_R_TYPE(r_info);
2929 set_te32(&dynsym[0].st_name, r_va); // for decompressor
2930 set_te64(&dynsym[0].st_value, r_info);
2931 set_te64(&dynsym[0].st_size, get_te64(&rp->r_addend));
2932 if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64 == e_machine) {
2933 if (R_AARCH64_RELATIVE == r_type) {
2934 user_init_va = get_te64(&rp->r_addend);
2935 }
2936 else if (R_AARCH64_ABS64 == r_type) {
2937 user_init_va = get_te64(&dynsym[ELF64_R_SYM(r_info)].st_value);
2938 }
2939 else {
2940 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2941 "bad relocation %#llx DT_INIT_ARRAY[0]",
2942 r_info);
2943 throwCantPack(msg);
2944 }
2945 }
2946 else if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64 == e_machine) {
2947 if (R_X86_64_RELATIVE == r_type) {
2948 user_init_va = get_te64(&rp->r_addend);
2949 }
2950 else if (R_X86_64_64 == r_type) {
2951 user_init_va = get_te64(&dynsym[ELF64_R_SYM(r_info)].st_value);
2952 }
2953 else {
2954 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2955 "bad relocation %#llx DT_INIT_ARRAY[0]",
2956 r_info);
2957 throwCantPack(msg);
2958 }
2959 }
2960 break;
2961 }
2962 }
2963 }
2964 unsigned const p_filesz = get_te64(&pload_x0->p_filesz);
2965 if (!((user_init_va - xct_va) < p_filesz)) {
2966 // Not in executable portion of first executable PT_LOAD.
2967 if (0==user_init_va && opt->o_unix.android_shlib) {
2968 // Android allows (0 ==> skip) ?
2969 upx_dt_init = 0; // force steal of 'extra' DT_NULL
2970 // XXX: FIXME: depends on SHT_DYNAMIC coming later
2971 }
2972 else {
2973 char msg[70]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
2974 "bad init address %#x in Elf64_Shdr[%d].%#x\n",
2975 (unsigned)user_init_va, -1+ e_shnum - j, user_init_off);
2976 throwCantPack(msg);
2977 }
2978 }
2979 }
2980 // By default /usr/bin/ld leaves 4 extra DT_NULL to support pre-linking.
2981 // Take one as a last resort.
2982 if ((Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT==upx_dt_init || !upx_dt_init)
2983 && Elf64_Shdr::SHT_DYNAMIC == sh_type) {
2984 upx_uint64_t sh_offset = get_te64(&shdr->sh_offset);
2985 upx_uint64_t sh_size = get_te64(&shdr->sh_size);
2986 if ((upx_uint64_t)file_size < sh_size
2987 || (upx_uint64_t)file_size < sh_offset
2988 || ((upx_uint64_t)file_size - sh_offset) < sh_size) {
2989 throwCantPack("bad SHT_DYNAMIC");
2990 }
2991 unsigned const n = sh_size / sizeof(Elf64_Dyn);
2992 Elf64_Dyn *dynp = (Elf64_Dyn *)&file_image[sh_offset];
2993 for (; Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL != dynp->d_tag; ++dynp) {
2994 if (upx_dt_init == get_te64(&dynp->d_tag)) {
2995 break; // re-found DT_INIT
2996 }
2997 }
2998 if ((1+ dynp) < (n+ dynseg)) { // not the terminator, so take it
2999 user_init_va = get_te64(&dynp->d_val); // 0 if (0==upx_dt_init)
3000 set_te64(&dynp->d_tag, upx_dt_init = Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT);
3001 user_init_off = (char const *)&dynp->d_val - (char const *)&file_image[0];
3002 }
3003 }
3004 }
3005 // If shdr_xva->sh_size is too small, then probably it won't compress.
3006 // So look for a Shdr that has PROGBITS and not SHF_WRITE, which is
3007 // much larger, and use that for the compressibility decision.
3008 if (shdr_xva->sh_size < 0x1000) {
3009 shdr = shdr_xva;
3010 while (SHT_PROGBITS == get_te32(&shdr[-1].sh_type)) --shdr; // backup
3011 for (; SHT_PROGBITS == get_te32(&shdr->sh_type)
3012 && !(SHF_WRITE & get_te64(&shdr->sh_flags)); ++shdr) {
3013 if (0x4000 <= get_te64(&shdr->sh_size)) {
3014 xct_va = get_te64(&shdr->sh_addr); // hopefully more compressible
3015 break;
3016 }
3017 }
3018 }
3019 return xct_va;
3020}
3021
3022tribool PackLinuxElf32::canPack()
3023{
3024 union {
3025 unsigned char buf[MAX_ELF_HDR_32];
3026 //struct { Elf32_Ehdr ehdr; Elf32_Phdr phdr; } e;
3027 } u;
3028 COMPILE_TIME_ASSERT(sizeof(u.buf) <= (2*512))
3029
3030// My earlier design with "extra" Shdrs in output at xct_off
3031// DOES NOT WORK because code for EM_ARM has embedded relocations
3032// that are not made visible, such as:
3033// ----- glibc-2.31/sysdeps/arm/crti.S
3034// .type call_weak_fn, %function
3035// call_weak_fn:
3036// ldr r3, .LGOT
3037// ldr r2, .LGOT+4
3038// .LPIC:
3039// add r3, pc, r3
3040// ldr r2, [r3, r2]
3041// cmp r2, #0
3042// bxeq lr
3043// b PREINIT_FUNCTION
3044// .p2align 2
3045// .LGOT:
3046// .word _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_-(.LPIC+8) // unseen reloc!
3047// .word PREINIT_FUNCTION(GOT)
3048// -----
3049// So, PackUnix::PackUnix() disables (but silently accepts) --android-shlib,
3050// and see if appending ARM_ATTRIBUTES Shdr is good enough.
3051
3052 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
3053 fi->readx(u.buf, sizeof(u.buf));
3054 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
3055 Elf32_Ehdr const *const ehdr = (Elf32_Ehdr *) u.buf;
3056
3057 // now check the ELF header
3058 if (checkEhdr(ehdr) != 0)
3059 return false;
3060
3061 // additional requirements for linux/elf386
3062 if (get_te16(&ehdr->e_ehsize) != sizeof(*ehdr)) {
3063 throwCantPack("invalid Ehdr e_ehsize; try '--force-execve'");
3064 return false;
3065 }
3066 if (e_phoff != sizeof(*ehdr)) {// Phdrs not contiguous with Ehdr
3067 throwCantPack("non-contiguous Ehdr/Phdr; try '--force-execve'");
3068 return false;
3069 }
3070
3071 if (!canPackOSABI((Elf32_Ehdr *)u.buf)) {
3072 return false;
3073 }
3074 upx_uint32_t max_LOADsz = 0, max_offset = 0;
3075 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = phdri;
3076 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
3077 if (j > ((MAX_ELF_HDR_32 - sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr)) / sizeof(Elf32_Phdr))) {
3078 throwCantPack("too many ElfXX_Phdr; try '--force-execve'");
3079 return false;
3080 }
3081 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
3082 // The first PT_LOAD must cover the beginning of the file (0==p_offset).
3083 upx_uint32_t const p_offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
3084 if (1!= exetype) {
3085 exetype = 1;
3086 load_va = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr); // class data member
3087 upx_uint32_t const off = ~page_mask & (upx_uint32_t)load_va;
3088 if (off && off == p_offset) { // specific hint
3089 throwCantPack("Go-language PT_LOAD: try hemfix.c, or try '--force-execve'");
3090 // Fixing it inside upx fails because packExtent() reads original file.
3091 return false;
3092 }
3093 if (0 != p_offset) { // 1st PT_LOAD must cover Ehdr and Phdr
3094 throwCantPack("first PT_LOAD.p_offset != 0; try '--force-execve'");
3095 return false;
3096 }
3097 // FIXME: bad for shlib!
3098 hatch_off = ~3ul & (3+ get_te32(&phdr->p_memsz));
3099 }
3100 max_LOADsz = UPX_MAX(max_LOADsz, UPX_MIN(0x200000u, get_te32(&phdr->p_align)));
3101 unsigned filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
3102 max_LOADsz = UPX_MAX(max_LOADsz, filesz);
3103 max_offset = UPX_MAX(max_offset, filesz + p_offset);
3104 }
3105 }
3106 if (canUnpack()) {
3107 throwAlreadyPacked();
3108 }
3109 // Heuristic for lopped trailing PackHeader (packed and "hacked"!)
3110 if (3 == e_phnum // not shlib: PT_LOAD.C_BASE, PT_LOAD.C_TEXT, PT_GNU_STACK
3111 && UPX_MAGIC_LE32 == get_le32(&((l_info *)&phdri[e_phnum])->l_magic)) {
3112 throwAlreadyPacked();
3113 }
3114 // We want to compress position-independent executable (gcc -pie)
3115 // main programs, but compressing a shared library must be avoided
3116 // because the result is no longer usable. In theory, there is no way
3117 // to tell them apart: both are just ET_DYN. Also in theory,
3118 // neither the presence nor the absence of any particular symbol name
3119 // can be used to tell them apart; there are counterexamples.
3120 // However, we will use the following heuristic suggested by
3121 // Peter S. Mazinger <ps.m@gmx.net> September 2005:
3122 // If a ET_DYN has __libc_start_main as a global undefined symbol,
3123 // then the file is a position-independent executable main program
3124 // (that depends on libc.so.6) and is eligible to be compressed.
3125 // Otherwise (no __libc_start_main as global undefined): skip it.
3126 // Also allow __uClibc_main and __uClibc_start_main .
3127
3128 if (Elf32_Ehdr::ET_DYN==get_te16(&ehdr->e_type)) {
3129 // The DT_SYMTAB has no designated length. Read the whole file.
3130 alloc_file_image(file_image, file_size);
3131 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
3132 fi->readx(file_image, file_size);
3133 memcpy(&ehdri, ehdr, sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr));
3134 phdri= (Elf32_Phdr *)((size_t)e_phoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
3135 shdri= (Elf32_Shdr *)((size_t)e_shoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
3136
3137 sec_strndx = nullptr;
3138 shstrtab = nullptr;
3139 if (e_shnum) {
3140 e_shstrndx = get_te16(&ehdr->e_shstrndx);
3141 if (e_shstrndx) {
3142 if (e_shnum <= e_shstrndx) {
3143 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
3144 "bad e_shstrndx %#x >= e_shnum %d", e_shstrndx, e_shnum);
3145 throwCantPack(msg);
3146 }
3147 sec_strndx = &shdri[e_shstrndx];
3148 unsigned const sh_offset = get_te32(&sec_strndx->sh_offset);
3149 if ((u32_t)file_size <= sh_offset) {
3150 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
3151 "bad .e_shstrndx->sh_offset %#x", sh_offset);
3152 throwCantPack(msg);
3153 }
3154 shstrtab = (char const *)(sh_offset + file_image);
3155 }
3156 sec_dynsym = elf_find_section_type(Elf32_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
3157 if (sec_dynsym) {
3158 unsigned const sh_link = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_link);
3159 if (e_shnum <= sh_link) {
3160 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
3161 "bad SHT_DYNSYM.sh_link %#x", sh_link);
3162 }
3163 sec_dynstr = &shdri[sh_link];
3164 }
3165
3166 if (sec_strndx) {
3167 unsigned const sh_name = get_te32(&sec_strndx->sh_name);
3168 if (Elf32_Shdr::SHT_STRTAB != get_te32(&sec_strndx->sh_type)
3169 || (u32_t)file_size <= (sizeof(".shstrtab")
3170 + sh_name + (shstrtab - (const char *)&file_image[0]))
3171 || (sh_name
3172 && 0!=strcmp((char const *)".shstrtab", &shstrtab[sh_name]))
3173 ) {
3174 throwCantPack("bad e_shstrtab");
3175 }
3176 }
3177 }
3178
3179 Elf32_Phdr const *pload_x0(nullptr); // first eXecutable PT_LOAD
3180 phdr= phdri;
3181 for (int j= e_phnum; --j>=0; ++phdr)
3182 if (Elf32_Phdr::PT_DYNAMIC==get_te32(&phdr->p_type)) {
3183 unsigned offset = check_pt_dynamic(phdr);
3184 dynseg= (Elf32_Dyn *)(offset + file_image);
3185 invert_pt_dynamic(dynseg,
3186 umin(get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz), (unsigned)(file_size_u - offset)));
3187 }
3188 else if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
3189 if (!pload_x0
3190 && Elf32_Phdr::PF_X & get_te32(&phdr->p_flags)
3191 ) {
3192 pload_x0 = phdr;
3193 }
3194 check_pt_load(phdr);
3195 }
3196 if (!pload_x0) {
3197 throwCantPack("No PT_LOAD has (p_flags & PF_X)");
3198 }
3199 // elf_find_dynamic() returns 0 if 0==dynseg.
3200 dynstr= (char const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
3201 dynsym= (Elf32_Sym /*const*/ *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB);
3202
3203 if (opt->o_unix.force_pie
3204 || Elf32_Dyn::DF_1_PIE & elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_FLAGS_1)
3205 || calls_crt1((Elf32_Rel const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_REL),
3206 (int)elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_RELSZ))
3207 || calls_crt1((Elf32_Rel const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_JMPREL),
3208 (int)elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_PLTRELSZ))) {
3209 is_pie = true; // UNUSED except to ignore is_shlib and xct_off
3210 goto proceed; // calls C library init for main program
3211 }
3212
3213 // Heuristic HACK for shared libraries (compare Darwin (MacOS) Dylib.)
3214 // If there is an existing DT_INIT, and if everything that the dynamic
3215 // linker ld-linux needs to perform relocations before calling DT_INIT
3216 // resides below the first SHT_EXECINSTR Section in one PT_LOAD, then
3217 // compress from the first executable Section to the end of that PT_LOAD.
3218 // We must not alter anything that ld-linux might touch before it calls
3219 // the DT_INIT function.
3220 //
3221 // Obviously this hack requires that the linker script put pieces
3222 // into good positions when building the original shared library,
3223 // and also requires ld-linux to behave.
3224
3225 // Apparently glibc-2.13.90 insists on 0==e_ident[EI_PAD..15],
3226 // so compressing shared libraries may be doomed anyway.
3227 // 2011-06-01: stub.shlib-init.S works around by installing hatch
3228 // at end of .text.
3229
3230 if (/*jni_onload_sym ||*/ elf_find_dynamic(upx_dt_init)) {
3231 if (this->e_machine!=Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386
3232 && this->e_machine!=Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS
3233 && this->e_machine!=Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM)
3234 goto abandon; // need stub: EM_PPC
3235 if (elf_has_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_TEXTREL)) {
3236 throwCantPack("DT_TEXTREL found; re-compile with -fPIC");
3237 goto abandon;
3238 }
3239 if (!(Elf32_Dyn::DF_1_PIE & elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_FLAGS_1))) {
3240 // not explicitly PIE main program
3241 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine // Android is common
3242 && !opt->o_unix.android_shlib // but not explicit
3243 && !saved_opt_android_shlib
3244 ) {
3245 opt->info_mode++;
3246 info("note: use --android-shlib if appropriate");
3247 opt->info_mode--;
3248 }
3249 }
3250 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS == get_te16(&ehdr->e_machine)
3251 || Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC == get_te16(&ehdr->e_machine)) {
3252 throwCantPack("This test UPX cannot pack .so for MIPS or PowerPC; coming soon.");
3253 }
3254 xct_va = ~(upx_uint64_t)0;
3255 if (e_shnum) {
3256 xct_va = canPack_Shdr(pload_x0);
3257 }
3258 else { // no Sections; use heuristics
3259 unsigned const strsz = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRSZ);
3260 unsigned const strtab = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
3261 unsigned const relsz = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_RELSZ);
3262 unsigned const rel = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_REL);
3263 unsigned const init = elf_unsigned_dynamic(upx_dt_init);
3264 if ((init == (relsz + rel ) && rel == (strsz + strtab))
3265 || (init == (strsz + strtab) && strtab == (relsz + rel ))
3266 ) {
3267 xct_va = init;
3268 user_init_va = init;
3269 user_init_off = elf_get_offset_from_address(init);
3270 }
3271 }
3272 // Rely on 0==elf_unsigned_dynamic(tag) if no such tag.
3273 unsigned const va_gash = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
3274 unsigned const va_hash = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_HASH);
3275 unsigned y = 0;
3276 if ((y=1, xct_va < va_gash) || (y=2, (0==va_gash && xct_va < va_hash))
3277 || (y=3, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRTAB))
3278 || (y=4, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB))
3279 || (y=5, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_REL))
3280 || (y=6, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_RELA))
3281 || (y=7, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_JMPREL))
3282 || (y=8, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_VERDEF))
3283 || (y=9, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_VERSYM))
3284 || (y=10, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_VERNEED)) ) {
3285 static char const *which[] = {
3286 "unknown",
3287 "DT_GNU_HASH",
3288 "DT_HASH",
3289 "DT_STRTAB",
3290 "DT_SYMTAB",
3291 "DT_REL",
3292 "DT_RELA",
3293 "DT_JMPREL",
3294 "DT_VERDEF",
3295 "DT_VERSYM",
3296 "DT_VERNEED",
3297 };
3298 char buf[30]; snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s above stub", which[y]);
3299 throwCantPack(buf);
3300 goto abandon;
3301 }
3302 xct_off = elf_get_offset_from_address(xct_va);
3303 if (opt->debug.debug_level) {
3304 fprintf(stderr, "shlib canPack: xct_va=%#lx xct_off=%#lx\n",
3305 (long)xct_va, (long)xct_off);
3306 }
3307 goto proceed; // But proper packing depends on checking xct_va.
3308 }
3309 else {
3310 throwCantPack("need DT_INIT; try \"void _init(void){}\"");
3311 }
3312abandon:
3313 return false;
3314proceed: ;
3315 }
3316 // XXX Theoretically the following test should be first,
3317 // but PackUnix::canPack() wants 0!=exetype ?
3318 if (!super::canPack())
3319 return false;
3320 assert(exetype == 1);
3321 exetype = 0;
3322
3323 // set options
3324 // this->blocksize: avoid over-allocating.
3325 // (file_size - max_offset): debug info, non-globl symbols, etc.
3326 opt->o_unix.blocksize = blocksize = UPX_MAX(max_LOADsz, (unsigned)(file_size - max_offset));
3327 return true;
3328}
3329
3330tribool PackLinuxElf64::canUnpack() // bool, except -1: format known, but not packed
3331{
3332 if (checkEhdr(&ehdri)) {
3333 return false;
3334 }
3335 if (get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum) < 2) {
3336 throwCantUnpack("e_phnum must be >= 2");
3337 }
3338 if (Elf64_Ehdr::ET_DYN==get_te16(&ehdri.e_type)) {
3339 PackLinuxElf64help1(fi);
3340 }
3341 if (super::canUnpack()) {
3342 return true;
3343 }
3344 return false;
3345}
3346
3347tribool PackLinuxElf64::canPack()
3348{
3349 union {
3350 unsigned char buf[MAX_ELF_HDR_64];
3351 //struct { Elf64_Ehdr ehdr; Elf64_Phdr phdr; } e;
3352 } u;
3353 COMPILE_TIME_ASSERT(sizeof(u) <= (2*1024))
3354
3355 fi->readx(u.buf, sizeof(u.buf));
3356 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
3357 Elf64_Ehdr const *const ehdr = (Elf64_Ehdr *) u.buf;
3358
3359 // now check the ELF header
3360 if (checkEhdr(ehdr) != 0)
3361 return false;
3362
3363 // additional requirements for linux/elf386
3364 if (get_te16(&ehdr->e_ehsize) != sizeof(*ehdr)) {
3365 throwCantPack("invalid Ehdr e_ehsize; try '--force-execve'");
3366 return false;
3367 }
3368 if (e_phoff != sizeof(*ehdr)) {// Phdrs not contiguous with Ehdr
3369 throwCantPack("non-contiguous Ehdr/Phdr; try '--force-execve'");
3370 return false;
3371 }
3372
3373 upx_uint64_t max_LOADsz = 0, max_offset = 0;
3374 Elf64_Phdr const *phdr = phdri;
3375 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
3376 if (j > ((MAX_ELF_HDR_64 - sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr)) / sizeof(Elf64_Phdr))) {
3377 throwCantPack("too many ElfXX_Phdr; try '--force-execve'");
3378 return false;
3379 }
3380 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
3381 // The first PT_LOAD must cover the beginning of the file (0==p_offset).
3382 upx_uint64_t const p_offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
3383 if (1!= exetype) {
3384 exetype = 1;
3385 load_va = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr); // class data member
3386 upx_uint64_t const off = ~page_mask & load_va;
3387 if (off && off == p_offset) { // specific hint
3388 throwCantPack("Go-language PT_LOAD: try hemfix.c, or try '--force-execve'");
3389 // Fixing it inside upx fails because packExtent() reads original file.
3390 return false;
3391 }
3392 if (0 != p_offset) { // 1st PT_LOAD must cover Ehdr and Phdr
3393 throwCantPack("first PT_LOAD.p_offset != 0; try '--force-execve'");
3394 return false;
3395 }
3396 // FIXME: bad for shlib!
3397 hatch_off = ~3ul & (3+ get_te64(&phdr->p_memsz));
3398 }
3399 upx_uint64_t align = get_te64(&phdr->p_align);
3400 if (0x200000ul < align) align = 0x200000ul; // UPX_MIN type problem
3401 max_LOADsz = UPX_MAX(max_LOADsz, align);
3402 upx_uint64_t filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
3403 max_LOADsz = UPX_MAX(max_LOADsz, filesz);
3404 max_offset = UPX_MAX(max_offset, filesz + p_offset);
3405 }
3406 }
3407 if (canUnpack()) {
3408 throwAlreadyPacked();
3409 }
3410 // Heuristic for lopped trailing PackHeader (packed and "hacked"!)
3411 if (3 == e_phnum // not shlib: PT_LOAD.C_BASE, PT_LOAD.C_TEXT, PT_GNU_STACK
3412 && UPX_MAGIC_LE32 == get_le32(&((l_info *)&phdri[e_phnum])->l_magic)) {
3413 throwAlreadyPacked();
3414 }
3415 // We want to compress position-independent executable (gcc -pie)
3416 // main programs, but compressing a shared library must be avoided
3417 // because the result is no longer usable. In theory, there is no way
3418 // to tell them apart: both are just ET_DYN. Also in theory,
3419 // neither the presence nor the absence of any particular symbol name
3420 // can be used to tell them apart; there are counterexamples.
3421 // However, we will use the following heuristic suggested by
3422 // Peter S. Mazinger <ps.m@gmx.net> September 2005:
3423 // If a ET_DYN has __libc_start_main as a global undefined symbol,
3424 // then the file is a position-independent executable main program
3425 // (that depends on libc.so.6) and is eligible to be compressed.
3426 // Otherwise (no __libc_start_main as global undefined): skip it.
3427 // Also allow __uClibc_main and __uClibc_start_main .
3428
3429 if (Elf64_Ehdr::ET_DYN==get_te16(&ehdr->e_type)) {
3430 // The DT_SYMTAB has no designated length. Read the whole file.
3431 alloc_file_image(file_image, file_size);
3432 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
3433 fi->readx(file_image, file_size);
3434 memcpy(&ehdri, ehdr, sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr));
3435 phdri= (Elf64_Phdr *)((size_t)e_phoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
3436 shdri= (Elf64_Shdr *)((size_t)e_shoff + file_image); // do not free() !!
3437
3438 sec_strndx = nullptr;
3439 shstrtab = nullptr;
3440 if (e_shnum) {
3441 e_shstrndx = get_te16(&ehdr->e_shstrndx);
3442 if (e_shstrndx) {
3443 if (e_shnum <= e_shstrndx) {
3444 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
3445 "bad e_shstrndx %#x >= e_shnum %d", e_shstrndx, e_shnum);
3446 throwCantPack(msg);
3447 }
3448 sec_strndx = &shdri[e_shstrndx];
3449 upx_uint64_t sh_offset = get_te64(&sec_strndx->sh_offset);
3450 if ((u64_t)file_size <= sh_offset) {
3451 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
3452 "bad .e_shstrndx->sh_offset %#lx", (long unsigned)sh_offset);
3453 throwCantPack(msg);
3454 }
3455 shstrtab = (char const *)(sh_offset + file_image);
3456 }
3457 sec_dynsym = elf_find_section_type(Elf64_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
3458 if (sec_dynsym) {
3459 unsigned const sh_link = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_link);
3460 if (e_shnum <= sh_link) {
3461 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
3462 "bad SHT_DYNSYM.sh_link %#x", sh_link);
3463 }
3464 sec_dynstr = &shdri[sh_link];
3465 }
3466
3467 if (sec_strndx) {
3468 unsigned const sh_name = get_te32(&sec_strndx->sh_name);
3469 if (Elf64_Shdr::SHT_STRTAB != get_te32(&sec_strndx->sh_type)
3470 || (u32_t)file_size <= (sizeof(".shstrtab")
3471 + sh_name + (shstrtab - (const char *)&file_image[0]))
3472 || (sh_name
3473 && 0!=strcmp((char const *)".shstrtab", &shstrtab[sh_name]))
3474 ) {
3475 throwCantPack("bad e_shstrtab");
3476 }
3477 }
3478 }
3479
3480 Elf64_Phdr const *pload_x0(nullptr); // first eXecutable PT_LOAD
3481 phdr= phdri;
3482 for (int j= e_phnum; --j>=0; ++phdr)
3483 if (Elf64_Phdr::PT_DYNAMIC==get_te32(&phdr->p_type)) {
3484 upx_uint64_t offset = check_pt_dynamic(phdr);
3485 dynseg= (Elf64_Dyn *)(offset + file_image);
3486 invert_pt_dynamic(dynseg,
3487 umin(get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz), file_size - offset));
3488 }
3489 else if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
3490 if (!pload_x0
3491 && Elf64_Phdr::PF_X & get_te32(&phdr->p_flags)
3492 ) {
3493 pload_x0 = phdr;
3494 }
3495 check_pt_load(phdr);
3496 }
3497 if (!pload_x0) {
3498 throwCantPack("No PT_LOAD has (p_flags & PF_X)");
3499 }
3500 // elf_find_dynamic() returns 0 if 0==dynseg.
3501 dynstr= (char const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
3502 dynsym= (Elf64_Sym /*const*/ *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB);
3503
3504 if (opt->o_unix.force_pie
3505 || Elf64_Dyn::DF_1_PIE & elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_FLAGS_1)
3506 || calls_crt1((Elf64_Rela const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELA),
3507 (int)elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELASZ))
3508 || calls_crt1((Elf64_Rela const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_JMPREL),
3509 (int)elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_PLTRELSZ))) {
3510 is_pie = true; // UNUSED except to ignore is_shlib and xct_off
3511 goto proceed; // calls C library init for main program
3512 }
3513
3514 // Heuristic HACK for shared libraries (compare Darwin (MacOS) Dylib.)
3515 // If there is an existing DT_INIT, and if everything that the dynamic
3516 // linker ld-linux needs to perform relocations before calling DT_INIT
3517 // resides below the first SHT_EXECINSTR Section in one PT_LOAD, then
3518 // compress from the first executable Section to the end of that PT_LOAD.
3519 // We must not alter anything that ld-linux might touch before it calls
3520 // the DT_INIT function.
3521 //
3522 // Obviously this hack requires that the linker script put pieces
3523 // into good positions when building the original shared library,
3524 // and also requires ld-linux to behave.
3525
3526 if (/*jni_onload_sym ||*/ elf_find_dynamic(upx_dt_init)) {
3527 if (elf_has_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_TEXTREL)) {
3528 throwCantPack("DT_TEXTREL found; re-compile with -fPIC");
3529 goto abandon;
3530 }
3531 if (!(Elf64_Dyn::DF_1_PIE & elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_FLAGS_1))) {
3532 // not explicitly PIE main program
3533 if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64 == e_machine // Android is common
3534 && !opt->o_unix.android_shlib // but not explicit
3535 && !saved_opt_android_shlib
3536 ) {
3537 opt->info_mode++;
3538 info("note: use --android-shlib if appropriate");
3539 opt->info_mode--;
3540 }
3541 }
3542 if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64 == get_te16(&ehdr->e_machine)) {
3543 throwCantPack("This test UPX cannot pack .so for PowerPC64; coming soon.");
3544 }
3545 xct_va = ~(upx_uint64_t)0;
3546 if (e_shnum) {
3547 xct_va = canPack_Shdr(pload_x0);
3548 }
3549 else { // no Sections; use heuristics
3550 upx_uint64_t const strsz = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRSZ);
3551 upx_uint64_t const strtab = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
3552 upx_uint64_t const relsz = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELSZ);
3553 upx_uint64_t const rel = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_REL);
3554 upx_uint64_t const init = elf_unsigned_dynamic(upx_dt_init);
3555 if ((init == (relsz + rel ) && rel == (strsz + strtab))
3556 || (init == (strsz + strtab) && strtab == (relsz + rel ))
3557 ) {
3558 xct_va = init;
3559 user_init_va = init;
3560 user_init_off = elf_get_offset_from_address(init);
3561 }
3562 }
3563 // Rely on 0==elf_unsigned_dynamic(tag) if no such tag.
3564 upx_uint64_t const va_gash = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
3565 upx_uint64_t const va_hash = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_HASH);
3566 unsigned y = 0;
3567 if ((y=1, xct_va < va_gash) || (y=2, (0==va_gash && xct_va < va_hash))
3568 || (y=3, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB))
3569 || (y=4, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB))
3570 || (y=5, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_REL))
3571 || (y=6, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELA))
3572 || (y=7, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_JMPREL))
3573 || (y=8, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERDEF))
3574 || (y=9, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERSYM))
3575 || (y=10, xct_va < elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERNEED)) ) {
3576 static char const *which[] = {
3577 "unknown",
3578 "DT_GNU_HASH",
3579 "DT_HASH",
3580 "DT_STRTAB",
3581 "DT_SYMTAB",
3582 "DT_REL",
3583 "DT_RELA",
3584 "DT_JMPREL",
3585 "DT_VERDEF",
3586 "DT_VERSYM",
3587 "DT_VERNEED",
3588 };
3589 char buf[30]; snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s above stub", which[y]);
3590 throwCantPack(buf);
3591 goto abandon;
3592 }
3593 xct_off = elf_get_offset_from_address(xct_va);
3594 if (opt->debug.debug_level) {
3595 fprintf(stderr, "shlib canPack: xct_va=%#lx xct_off=%#lx\n",
3596 (long)xct_va, (long)xct_off);
3597 }
3598 goto proceed; // But proper packing depends on checking xct_va.
3599 }
3600 else {
3601 throwCantPack("need DT_INIT; try \"void _init(void){}\"");
3602 }
3603abandon:
3604 return false;
3605proceed: ;
3606 }
3607 // XXX Theoretically the following test should be first,
3608 // but PackUnix::canPack() wants 0!=exetype ?
3609 if (!super::canPack())
3610 return false;
3611 assert(exetype == 1);
3612 exetype = 0;
3613
3614 // set options
3615 // this->blocksize: avoid over-allocating.
3616 // (file_size - max_offset): debug info, non-globl symbols, etc.
3617 opt->o_unix.blocksize = blocksize = UPX_MAX(max_LOADsz, file_size - max_offset);
3618 return true;
3619}
3620
3621off_t
3622PackLinuxElf32::getbrk(Elf32_Phdr const *phdr, int nph) const
3623{
3624 off_t brka = 0;
3625 for (int j = 0; j < nph; ++phdr, ++j) {
3626 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
3627 off_t b = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr) + get_te32(&phdr->p_memsz);
3628 if (b > brka)
3629 brka = b;
3630 }
3631 }
3632 return brka;
3633}
3634
3635off_t
3636PackLinuxElf32::getbase(const Elf32_Phdr *phdr, int nph) const
3637{
3638 off_t base = ~0u;
3639 for (int j = 0; j < nph; ++phdr, ++j) {
3640 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
3641 unsigned const vaddr = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
3642 if (vaddr < (unsigned) base)
3643 base = vaddr;
3644 }
3645 }
3646 if (0!=base) {
3647 return base;
3648 }
3649 return 0x12000;
3650}
3651
3652off_t
3653PackLinuxElf64::getbrk(const Elf64_Phdr *phdr, int nph) const
3654{
3655 off_t brka = 0;
3656 for (int j = 0; j < nph; ++phdr, ++j) {
3657 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
3658 off_t b = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr) + get_te64(&phdr->p_memsz);
3659 if (b > brka)
3660 brka = b;
3661 }
3662 }
3663 return brka;
3664}
3665
3666static unsigned
3667is_pow2(unsigned x)
3668{
3669 return !((-1 + x) & x);
3670}
3671
3672void
3673PackLinuxElf32::generateElfHdr(
3674 OutputFile *fo,
3675 void const *proto,
3676 unsigned const brka
3677)
3678{
3679 cprElfHdr2 *const h2 = (cprElfHdr2 *)(void *)&elfout;
3680 cprElfHdr3 *const h3 = (cprElfHdr3 *)(void *)&elfout;
3681 h3->ehdr = ((cprElfHdr3 const *)proto)->ehdr;
3682 e_type = get_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_type);
3683 if (!memcmp("\x7f\x45\x4c\x46", proto, 4) && Elf32_Ehdr::ET_EXEC == e_type
3684 && 2 <= get_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phnum)) {
3685 h3->phdr[C_BASE] = ((cprElfHdr3 const *)proto)->phdr[1]; // .data; .p_align
3686 h3->phdr[C_TEXT] = ((cprElfHdr3 const *)proto)->phdr[0]; // .text
3687 }
3688 else {
3689 memcpy(&h3->ehdr.e_ident[0], "\x7f\x45\x4c\x46", 4);
3690 h3->ehdr.e_ident[EI_CLASS] = ei_class;
3691 h3->ehdr.e_ident[EI_DATA] = ei_data;
3692 h3->ehdr.e_ident[EI_VERSION] = EV_CURRENT;
3693 h3->ehdr.e_ident[EI_OSABI] = ei_osabi;
3694 h3->ehdr.e_ident[EI_ABIVERSION] = 1; // ei_abiversion;
3695 set_te32(&h3->ehdr.e_phoff, sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr));
3696 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_ehsize,sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr));
3697 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phentsize, sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
3698 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phnum, 2);
3699 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_machine, e_machine);
3700 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_shstrndx, 0);
3701 memset(&h3->phdr[C_BASE], 0, sizeof(h3->phdr[C_BASE]));
3702 memset(&h3->phdr[C_TEXT], 0, sizeof(h3->phdr[C_TEXT]));
3703 memset(&h3->phdr[2 ], 0, sizeof(h3->phdr[2 ]));
3704 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_flags, 0);
3705 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_TEXT].p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_X| Elf32_Phdr::PF_R);
3706 if (!memcmp("\x7f\x45\x4c\x46", proto, 4) && Elf32_Ehdr::ET_REL == e_type) {
3707 }
3708 else {
3709 throwCantPack("unknown e_type %#x", e_type);
3710 }
3711 }
3712 h3->ehdr.e_type = ehdri.e_type; // ET_EXEC vs ET_DYN (gcc -pie -fPIC)
3713 memset(&h3->linfo, 0, sizeof(h3->linfo));
3714
3715 h3->ehdr.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI] = ei_osabi;
3716 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS==e_machine) { // MIPS R3000 FIXME
3717 h3->ehdr.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI] = Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_NONE;
3718 h3->ehdr.e_flags = ehdri.e_flags;
3719 }
3720
3721 if (ph.format != getFormat()) {
3722 assert(false); // unknown ph.format, PackLinuxElf32
3723 }
3724 assert(get_te32(&h2->ehdr.e_phoff) == sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr));
3725 assert(get_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_ehsize) == sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr));
3726 assert(get_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_phentsize) == sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
3727
3728 h2->ehdr.e_shoff = 0;
3729 if (o_elf_shnum) {
3730 set_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf32_Shdr));
3731 h2->ehdr.e_shnum = o_elf_shnum;
3732 h2->ehdr.e_shstrndx = o_elf_shnum - 1;
3733 }
3734 else {
3735 // https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2131609
3736 // 0==.e_shnum is a special case for libbfd
3737 // that requires 0==.e_shentsize in order to force "no Shdrs"
3738 h2->ehdr.e_shentsize = 0;
3739 h2->ehdr.e_shnum = 0;
3740 h2->ehdr.e_shstrndx = 0;
3741 }
3742
3743 unsigned phnum_o = 2 + n_phdrx; // C_BASE, C_TEXT
3744 set_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_phnum, phnum_o);
3745
3746 // Info for OS kernel to set the brk()
3747 if (brka) {
3748 // linux-2.6.14 binfmt_elf.c: SIGKILL if (0==.p_memsz) on a page boundary
3749 upx_uint32_t lo_va_user = ~0u; // infinity
3750 for (int j= e_phnum; --j>=0; ) {
3751 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[j])) {
3752 upx_uint32_t const vaddr = get_te32(&phdri[j].p_vaddr);
3753 lo_va_user = umin(lo_va_user, vaddr);
3754 }
3755 }
3756 set_te32( &h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr, lo_va_user);
3757 h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_paddr = h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
3758 h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr = h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
3759 h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_paddr = h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
3760 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_type, PT_LOAD); // be sure
3761 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_type, PT_LOAD); // be sure
3762 h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_offset = 0;
3763 h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_filesz = 0;
3764 // .p_memsz = brka; temporary until sz_pack2
3765 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_memsz, brka - lo_va_user);
3766 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_R | Elf32_Phdr::PF_W);
3767 }
3768 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_align, page_size);
3769 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_TEXT].p_align, page_size);
3770 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_flags, ~Elf32_Phdr::PF_W & get_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_flags));
3771 fo->write(h2, sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + 2* sizeof(Elf32_Phdr)); // C_BASE, C_TEXT
3772
3773 u64_t const zero_pad = 0;
3774 unsigned uva0 = get_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr);
3775 unsigned off_o = 0;
3776 for (unsigned phase = 0; phase < 2; ++phase) { // 0: Phdrs; 1: bodies
3777 off_o = sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + phnum_o * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr);
3778 for (unsigned j = 0; j < n_phdrx; ++j) {
3779 Elf32_Phdr phtmp = *phdrx[j];
3780 phtmp.p_vaddr = phtmp.p_paddr = 0;
3781 unsigned const off_i = get_te32(&phtmp.p_offset);
3782 unsigned const align = get_te32(&phtmp.p_align);
3783 unsigned const filesz = get_te32(&phtmp.p_filesz);
3784 unsigned pad = 0;
3785 if (filesz && align && is_pow2(align)) {
3786 unsigned alm1 = -1 + umin(8u, align);
3787 pad = alm1 & (0u - off_o);
3788 off_o += pad;
3789 set_te32(&phtmp.p_vaddr, off_o + uva0); phtmp.p_paddr = phtmp.p_vaddr;
3790 }
3791 if (0==phase) {
3792 set_te32(&phtmp.p_offset, (filesz ? off_o : 0));
3793 fo->write(&phtmp, sizeof(phtmp)); // Phdr
3794 }
3795 if (1==phase) {
3796 if (pad) fo->write(&zero_pad, pad);
3797 if (filesz) fo->write(&file_image[off_i], filesz); // body
3798 }
3799 off_o += filesz;
3800 }
3801 }
3802 off_o = fpad4(fo, off_o);
3803 sz_phdrx = off_o - (sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + phnum_o * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
3804 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_filesz, off_o);
3805
3806 sz_elf_hdrs = sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + phnum_o * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr) + sz_phdrx;
3807 overlay_offset = sz_elf_hdrs + sizeof(l_info);
3808 o_binfo = sz_elf_hdrs + sizeof(l_info) + sizeof(p_info);
3809
3810 l_info linfo2; memset(&linfo2, 0, sizeof(linfo2));
3811 fo->write(&linfo2, sizeof(linfo2));
3812}
3813
3814void
3815PackNetBSDElf32x86::generateElfHdr(
3816 OutputFile *fo,
3817 void const *proto,
3818 unsigned const brka
3819)
3820{
3821 cprElfHdr2 *const h2 = (cprElfHdr2 *)(void *)&elfout;
3822 super::generateElfHdr(fo, proto, brka);
3823
3824 sz_elf_hdrs = sizeof(*h2) - sizeof(linfo);
3825 unsigned note_offset = sz_elf_hdrs;
3826
3827 // Find the NetBSD PT_NOTE and the PaX PT_NOTE.
3828 Elf32_Nhdr const *np_NetBSD = nullptr; unsigned sz_NetBSD = 0;
3829 Elf32_Nhdr const *np_PaX = nullptr; unsigned sz_PaX = 0;
3830 unsigned char *cp = (unsigned char *)note_body;
3831 unsigned j;
3832 for (j=0; j < note_size; ) {
3833 Elf32_Nhdr const *const np = (Elf32_Nhdr const *)(void *)cp;
3834 int k = sizeof(*np) + up4(get_te32(&np->namesz))
3835 + up4(get_te32(&np->descsz));
3836
3837 if (NHDR_NETBSD_TAG == np->type && 7== np->namesz
3838 && NETBSD_DESCSZ == np->descsz
3839 && 0==strcmp(ELF_NOTE_NETBSD_NAME,
3840 /* &np->body */ (char const *)(1+ np))) {
3841 np_NetBSD = np;
3842 sz_NetBSD = k;
3843 }
3844 if (NHDR_PAX_TAG == np->type && 4== np->namesz
3845 && PAX_DESCSZ==np->descsz
3846 && 0==strcmp(ELF_NOTE_PAX_NAME,
3847 /* &np->body */ (char const *)(1+ np))) {
3848 np_PaX = np;
3849 sz_PaX = k;
3850 }
3851 cp += k;
3852 j += k;
3853 }
3854
3855 // Add PT_NOTE for the NetBSD note and PaX note, if any.
3856 note_offset += (np_NetBSD ? sizeof(Elf32_Phdr) : 0);
3857 note_offset += (np_PaX ? sizeof(Elf32_Phdr) : 0);
3858 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = &elfout.phdr[C_NOTE];
3859 if (np_NetBSD) {
3860 set_te32(&phdr->p_type, PT_NOTE32);
3861 set_te32(&phdr->p_offset, note_offset);
3862 set_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr, note_offset);
3863 set_te32(&phdr->p_paddr, note_offset);
3864 set_te32(&phdr->p_filesz, sz_NetBSD);
3865 set_te32(&phdr->p_memsz, sz_NetBSD);
3866 set_te32(&phdr->p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_R);
3867 set_te32(&phdr->p_align, 4);
3868
3869 sz_elf_hdrs += sz_NetBSD + sizeof(*phdr);
3870 note_offset += sz_NetBSD;
3871 ++phdr;
3872 }
3873 if (np_PaX) {
3874 set_te32(&phdr->p_type, PT_NOTE32);
3875 set_te32(&phdr->p_offset, note_offset);
3876 set_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr, note_offset);
3877 set_te32(&phdr->p_paddr, note_offset);
3878 set_te32(&phdr->p_filesz, sz_PaX);
3879 set_te32(&phdr->p_memsz, sz_PaX);
3880 set_te32(&phdr->p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_R);
3881 set_te32(&phdr->p_align, 4);
3882
3883 /* &np_PaX->body[4] */
3884 const unsigned char *p4 = &(ACC_CCAST(const unsigned char *, (1+ np_PaX)))[4];
3885 unsigned bits = get_te32(p4);
3886 bits &= ~PAX_MPROTECT;
3887 bits |= PAX_NOMPROTECT;
3888 set_te32(ACC_UNCONST_CAST(unsigned char *, p4), bits);
3889
3890 sz_elf_hdrs += sz_PaX + sizeof(*phdr);
3891 note_offset += sz_PaX;
3892 ++phdr;
3893 }
3894 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz, note_offset);
3895 h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_memsz = h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz;
3896
3897 if (ph.format==getFormat()) {
3898 set_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_phnum, !!sz_NetBSD + !!sz_PaX +
3899 get_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_phnum));
3900 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
3901 fo->rewrite(h2, sizeof(*h2) - sizeof(h2->linfo));
3902
3903 // The 'if' guards on these two calls to memcpy are required
3904 // because the C Standard Committee did not debug the Standard
3905 // before publishing. An empty region (0==size) must nevertheless
3906 // have a valid (non-nullptr) pointer.
3907 if (sz_NetBSD) memcpy(&((char *)phdr)[0], np_NetBSD, sz_NetBSD);
3908 if (sz_PaX) memcpy(&((char *)phdr)[sz_NetBSD], np_PaX, sz_PaX);
3909
3910 fo->write(&elfout.phdr[C_NOTE],
3911 &((char *)phdr)[sz_PaX + sz_NetBSD] - (char *)&elfout.phdr[C_NOTE]);
3912
3913 l_info foo; memset(&foo, 0, sizeof(foo));
3914 fo->rewrite(&foo, sizeof(foo));
3915 }
3916 else {
3917 assert(false); // unknown ph.format, PackLinuxElf32
3918 }
3919}
3920
3921void
3922PackOpenBSDElf32x86::generateElfHdr(
3923 OutputFile *fo,
3924 void const *proto,
3925 unsigned const brka
3926)
3927{
3928 cprElfHdr3 *const h3 = (cprElfHdr3 *)(void *)&elfout;
3929 memcpy(h3, proto, sizeof(*h3)); // reads beyond, but OK
3930 h3->ehdr.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI] = ei_osabi;
3931 assert(2==get_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phnum));
3932 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phnum, 3);
3933
3934 assert(get_te32(&h3->ehdr.e_phoff) == sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr));
3935 h3->ehdr.e_shoff = 0;
3936 assert(get_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_ehsize) == sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr));
3937 assert(get_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phentsize) == sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
3938 h3->ehdr.e_shentsize = 0;
3939 h3->ehdr.e_shnum = 0;
3940 h3->ehdr.e_shstrndx = 0;
3941
3942 struct {
3943 Elf32_Nhdr nhdr;
3944 char name[8];
3945 unsigned body;
3946 } elfnote;
3947
3948 unsigned const note_offset = sizeof(*h3) - sizeof(linfo);
3949 sz_elf_hdrs = sizeof(elfnote) + note_offset;
3950
3951 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_type, PT_NOTE32);
3952 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_offset, note_offset);
3953 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_vaddr, note_offset);
3954 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_paddr, note_offset);
3955 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_filesz, sizeof(elfnote));
3956 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_memsz, sizeof(elfnote));
3957 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_R);
3958 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_NOTE].p_align, 4);
3959
3960 // Q: Same as this->note_body[0 .. this->note_size-1] ?
3961 set_te32(&elfnote.nhdr.namesz, 8);
3962 set_te32(&elfnote.nhdr.descsz, OPENBSD_DESCSZ);
3963 set_te32(&elfnote.nhdr.type, NHDR_OPENBSD_TAG);
3964 memcpy(elfnote.name, "OpenBSD", sizeof(elfnote.name));
3965 elfnote.body = 0;
3966
3967 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz, sz_elf_hdrs);
3968 h3->phdr[C_TEXT].p_memsz = h3->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz;
3969
3970 unsigned const brkb = brka | ((0==(~page_mask & brka)) ? 0x20 : 0);
3971 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_type, PT_LOAD); // be sure
3972 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_offset, ~page_mask & brkb);
3973 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr, brkb);
3974 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_paddr, brkb);
3975 h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_filesz = 0;
3976 // Too many kernels have bugs when 0==.p_memsz
3977 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_memsz, 1);
3978 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_R | Elf32_Phdr::PF_W);
3979
3980 if (ph.format==getFormat()) {
3981 memset(&h3->linfo, 0, sizeof(h3->linfo));
3982 fo->write(h3, sizeof(*h3) - sizeof(h3->linfo));
3983 fo->write(&elfnote, sizeof(elfnote));
3984 fo->write(&h3->linfo, sizeof(h3->linfo));
3985 }
3986 else {
3987 assert(false); // unknown ph.format, PackLinuxElf32
3988 }
3989}
3990
3991void
3992PackLinuxElf64::generateElfHdr(
3993 OutputFile *fo,
3994 void const *proto,
3995 unsigned const brka
3996)
3997{
3998 cprElfHdr2 *const h2 = (cprElfHdr2 *)(void *)&elfout;
3999 cprElfHdr3 *const h3 = (cprElfHdr3 *)(void *)&elfout;
4000 h3->ehdr = ((cprElfHdr3 const *)proto)->ehdr;
4001 if (Elf64_Ehdr::ET_REL == get_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_type)) {
4002 set_te64(&h3->ehdr.e_phoff, sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr));
4003 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_ehsize,sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr));
4004 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phentsize, sizeof(Elf64_Phdr));
4005 set_te16(&h3->ehdr.e_phnum, 2);
4006 memset(&h3->phdr[C_BASE], 0, sizeof(h3->phdr[C_BASE]));
4007 memset(&h3->phdr[C_TEXT], 0, sizeof(h3->phdr[C_TEXT]));
4008 memset(&h3->phdr[2 ], 0, sizeof(h3->phdr[2 ]));
4009 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_flags, 0);
4010 set_te32(&h3->phdr[C_TEXT].p_flags, Elf64_Phdr::PF_X| Elf64_Phdr::PF_R);
4011 }
4012 else {
4013 h3->phdr[C_BASE] = ((cprElfHdr3 const *)proto)->phdr[1]; // .data; .p_align
4014 h3->phdr[C_TEXT] = ((cprElfHdr3 const *)proto)->phdr[0]; // .text
4015 }
4016 memset(&h3->linfo, 0, sizeof(h3->linfo));
4017
4018 h3->ehdr.e_type = ehdri.e_type; // ET_EXEC vs ET_DYN (gcc -pie -fPIC)
4019 h3->ehdr.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_OSABI] = ei_osabi;
4020 if (Elf64_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_LINUX == ei_osabi // proper
4021 && Elf64_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_NONE == ehdri.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_OSABI] // sloppy
4022 ) { // propagate sloppiness so that decompression does not complain
4023 h3->ehdr.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_OSABI] = ehdri.e_ident[Elf64_Ehdr::EI_OSABI];
4024 }
4025 if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64 == get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine)) {
4026 h3->ehdr.e_flags = ehdri.e_flags; // "0x1, abiv1" vs "0x2, abiv2"
4027 }
4028
4029 assert(get_te64(&h2->ehdr.e_phoff) == sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr));
4030 assert(get_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_ehsize) == sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr));
4031 assert(get_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_phentsize) == sizeof(Elf64_Phdr));
4032
4033 h2->ehdr.e_shoff = 0;
4034 if (o_elf_shnum) {
4035 set_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
4036 h2->ehdr.e_shnum = o_elf_shnum;
4037 h2->ehdr.e_shstrndx = o_elf_shnum - 1;
4038 }
4039 else {
4040 // https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2131609
4041 // 0==.e_shnum is a special case for libbfd
4042 // that requires 0==.e_shentsize in order to force "no Shdrs"
4043 h2->ehdr.e_shentsize = 0;
4044 h2->ehdr.e_shnum = 0;
4045 h2->ehdr.e_shstrndx = 0;
4046 }
4047
4048 unsigned const phnum_i = get_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_phnum);
4049 unsigned phnum_o = 2 + n_phdrx; // C_BASE, C_TEXT
4050 set_te16(&h2->ehdr.e_phnum, phnum_o);
4051 o_binfo = sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + sizeof(Elf64_Phdr)*phnum_o + sizeof(l_info) + sizeof(p_info);
4052 set_te64(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz, sizeof(*h2)); // + identsize;
4053 h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_memsz = h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz;
4054 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_type, PT_LOAD); // be sure
4055
4056 for (unsigned j=0; j < phnum_i; ++j) {
4057 if (is_LOAD(&h3->phdr[j])) {
4058 set_te64( &h3->phdr[j].p_align, page_size);
4059 }
4060 }
4061
4062 // Info for OS kernel to set the brk()
4063 if (brka) {
4064 // linux-2.6.14 binfmt_elf.c: SIGKILL if (0==.p_memsz) on a page boundary
4065 upx_uint64_t lo_va_user(~(upx_uint64_t)0); // infinity
4066 for (int j= e_phnum; --j>=0; ) {
4067 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[j])) {
4068 upx_uint64_t const vaddr = get_te64(&phdri[j].p_vaddr);
4069 lo_va_user = umin(lo_va_user, vaddr);
4070 }
4071 }
4072 set_te64( &h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr, lo_va_user);
4073 h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_paddr = h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
4074 h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr = h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
4075 h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_paddr = h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_vaddr;
4076 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_type, PT_LOAD); // be sure
4077 h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_offset = 0;
4078 h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_filesz = 0;
4079 // .p_memsz = brka; temporary until sz_pack2
4080 set_te64(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_memsz, brka - lo_va_user);
4081 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_flags, Elf64_Phdr::PF_R | Elf64_Phdr::PF_W);
4082 }
4083 set_te64(&h3->phdr[C_BASE].p_align, page_size);
4084 set_te64(&h3->phdr[C_TEXT].p_align, page_size);
4085 set_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_flags, ~Elf64_Phdr::PF_W & get_te32(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_flags));
4086 fo->write(h2, sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + 2* sizeof(Elf64_Phdr)); // C_BASE, C_TEXT
4087
4088 u64_t const zero_pad = 0;
4089 unsigned uva0 = get_te64(&h2->phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr);
4090 unsigned off_o = 0;
4091 for (unsigned phase = 0; phase < 2; ++phase) { // 0: Phdrs; 1: bodies
4092 off_o = sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + phnum_o * sizeof(Elf64_Phdr);
4093 for (unsigned j = 0; j < n_phdrx; ++j) {
4094 Elf64_Phdr phtmp = *phdrx[j];
4095 phtmp.p_vaddr = phtmp.p_paddr = 0;
4096 u64_t const off_i = get_te64(&phtmp.p_offset);
4097 u64_t const align = get_te64(&phtmp.p_align);
4098 u64_t const filesz = get_te64(&phtmp.p_filesz);
4099 unsigned pad = 0;
4100 if (filesz && align && is_pow2(align)) {
4101 unsigned alm1 = -1 + umin(8u, (unsigned)align);
4102 pad = alm1 & (0u - off_o);
4103 off_o += pad;
4104 set_te64(&phtmp.p_vaddr, off_o + uva0); phtmp.p_paddr = phtmp.p_vaddr;
4105 }
4106 if (0==phase) {
4107 set_te64(&phtmp.p_offset, (filesz ? off_o : 0));
4108 fo->write(&phtmp, sizeof(phtmp)); // Phdr
4109 }
4110 if (1==phase) {
4111 if (pad) fo->write(&zero_pad, pad);
4112 if (filesz) fo->write(&file_image[off_i], filesz); // body
4113 }
4114 off_o += filesz;
4115 }
4116 }
4117 off_o = fpad4(fo, off_o);
4118 sz_phdrx = off_o - (sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + phnum_o * sizeof(Elf64_Phdr));
4119 set_te64(&h2->phdr[C_BASE].p_filesz, off_o);
4120
4121 sz_elf_hdrs = sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + phnum_o * sizeof(Elf64_Phdr) + sz_phdrx;
4122 overlay_offset = sz_elf_hdrs + sizeof(l_info);
4123 o_binfo = sz_elf_hdrs + sizeof(l_info) + sizeof(p_info);
4124
4125 l_info linfo2; memset(&linfo2, 0, sizeof(linfo2));
4126 fo->write(&linfo2, sizeof(linfo2));
4127}
4128
4129// Android shlib has ABS symbols that actually are relative.
4130static char const abs_symbol_names[][14] = {
4131 "__bss_end__"
4132 , "_bss_end__"
4133 , "__bss_start"
4134 , "__bss_start__"
4135 , "_edata"
4136 , "_end"
4137 , "__end__"
4138 , ""
4139};
4140
4141int
4142PackLinuxElf32::adjABS(Elf32_Sym *sym, unsigned delta)
4143{
4144 unsigned st_name = get_te32(&sym->st_name);
4145 for (int j = 0; abs_symbol_names[j][0]; ++j) {
4146 if (!strcmp(abs_symbol_names[j], get_str_name(st_name, (unsigned)-1))) {
4147 sym->st_value += delta;
4148 return 1;
4149 }
4150 }
4151 return 0;
4152}
4153
4154int
4155PackLinuxElf64::adjABS(Elf64_Sym *sym, unsigned long delta)
4156{
4157 unsigned st_name = get_te32(&sym->st_name);
4158 for (int j = 0; abs_symbol_names[j][0]; ++j) {
4159 if (!strcmp(abs_symbol_names[j], get_str_name(st_name, (unsigned)-1))) {
4160 sym->st_value += delta;
4161 return 1;
4162 }
4163 }
4164 return 0;
4165}
4166
4167void PackLinuxElf32::pack1(OutputFile * /*fo*/, Filter &ft)
4168{
4169 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
4170 fi->readx(&ehdri, sizeof(ehdri));
4171 assert(e_phoff == sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr)); // checked by canPack()
4172 sz_phdrs = e_phnum * get_te16(&ehdri.e_phentsize);
4173
4174// We compress separate pieces (usually each PT_LOAD, plus the gaps in the file
4175// that are not covered by any PT_LOAD), but currently at run time there can be
4176// only one decompressor method.
4177// Therefore we must plan ahead because Packer::compressWithFilters tries
4178// to find the smallest result among the available methods, for one piece only.
4179// In the future we may allow more than one decompression method at run time.
4180// For now we must choose only one, and force PackUnix::packExtent
4181// (==> compressWithFilters) to use it.
4182 int nfilters = 0;
4183 {
4184 int const *fp = getFilters();
4185 while (FT_END != *fp++) {
4186 ++nfilters;
4187 }
4188 }
4189 {
4190 int npieces = 1; // tail after highest PT_LOAD
4191 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = phdri;
4192 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
4193 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
4194 unsigned const flags = get_te32(&phdr->p_flags);
4195 unsigned offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
4196 if (!xct_off // not shlib
4197 // new-style shlib: PT_LOAD[0] has symbol table
4198 // which must not be compressed, but also lacks PF_X
4199 || (Elf32_Phdr::PF_X & flags)
4200 // Read-only, non-first PT_LOAD is _assumed_ to be compressible
4201 || (!(Elf32_Phdr::PF_W & flags) && 0!=offset))
4202 {
4203 ++npieces; // will attempt compression of this PT_LOAD
4204 }
4205 }
4206 }
4207 uip->ui_total_passes += npieces;
4208 }
4209 int methods[256];
4210 unsigned nmethods = prepareMethods(methods, ph.method, getCompressionMethods(M_ALL, ph.level));
4211 if (1 < nmethods) { // Many are available, but we must choose only one
4212 uip->ui_total_passes += 1; // the batch for output
4213 uip->ui_total_passes *= nmethods * (1+ nfilters); // finding smallest total
4214 PackHeader orig_ph = ph;
4215 Filter orig_ft = ft;
4216 unsigned max_offset = 0;
4217 unsigned sz_best= ~0u;
4218 int method_best = 0;
4219 for (unsigned k = 0; k < nmethods; ++k) { // FIXME: parallelize; cost: working space
4220 unsigned sz_this = 0;
4221 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = phdri;
4222 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
4223 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
4224 unsigned const flags = get_te32(&phdr->p_flags);
4225 unsigned offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
4226 unsigned filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
4227 max_offset = UPX_MAX(max_offset, filesz + offset);
4228 if (!xct_off // not shlib
4229 // new-style shlib: PT_LOAD[0] has symbol table
4230 // which must not be compressed, but also lacks PF_X
4231 || (Elf32_Phdr::PF_X & flags)
4232 // Read-only, non-first PT_LOAD is _assumed_ to be compressible
4233 || (!(Elf32_Phdr::PF_W & flags) && 0!=offset))
4234 {
4235 if (xct_off && 0==offset) { // old-style shlib
4236 offset = xct_off;
4237 filesz -= xct_off;
4238 }
4239 fi->seek(offset, SEEK_SET);
4240 fi->readx(ibuf, filesz);
4241 ft = orig_ft;
4242 ph = orig_ph;
4243 ph.method = ph_force_method(methods[k]);
4244 ph.u_len = filesz;
4245 compressWithFilters(&ft, OVERHEAD, NULL_cconf, 10, true);
4246 sz_this += ph.c_len;
4247 }
4248 }
4249 }
4250 unsigned const sz_tail = file_size - max_offset; // debuginfo, etc.
4251 if (sz_tail) {
4252 fi->seek(max_offset, SEEK_SET);
4253 fi->readx(ibuf, sz_tail);
4254 ft = orig_ft;
4255 ph = orig_ph;
4256 ph.method = ph_force_method(methods[k]);
4257 ph.u_len = sz_tail;
4258 compressWithFilters(&ft, OVERHEAD, NULL_cconf, 10, true);
4259 sz_this += ph.c_len;
4260 }
4261 // FIXME: loader size also depends on method
4262 if (sz_best > sz_this) {
4263 sz_best = sz_this;
4264 method_best = methods[k];
4265 }
4266 }
4267 ft = orig_ft;
4268 ph = orig_ph;
4269 ph.method = ph_force_method(method_best);
4270 }
4271
4272 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = phdri;
4273 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
4274 unsigned const type = get_te32(&phdr->p_type);
4275 if (PT_GNU_STACK32 == type || PT_NOTE32 == type) {
4276 add_phdrx(phdr); // PT_GNU_STACK32, PT_NOTE32
4277 }
4278 if (PT_LOAD == type) {
4279 unsigned x = get_te32(&phdr->p_align) >> lg2_page;
4280 while (x>>=1) {
4281 ++lg2_page;
4282 }
4283 }
4284 if (PT_GNU_RELRO32 == type
4285 && 16 < lg2_page) {
4286 // x86* allows 4K, 2M, 1G
4287 // arm32 and arm64 both allow 4K, 16K, 64K; Apple Silicon uses 16K
4288 // Oracle 5.4.17-2136.314.6.2.el8uek.aarch64 demands 64K
4289 // PowerPC and PowerPC64 has 4K, 64K, 1M (?), 16M (?)
4290 // MIPS allows any power of 2 from 4K through 64K
4291
4292 // If 64K < .p_align then we assume that 4K is also accepted.
4293 // .p_align can be like 2M, which is a huge over-estimate.
4294 // RELRO ends on a page boundary: usually close to actual page_size
4295 unsigned offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
4296 unsigned filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
4297 if (!(0xfff & (filesz + offset))) { // a 4KiB boundary
4298 unsigned b = 12;
4299 while (!(~(~0u << b) & (filesz + offset))) {
4300 ++b;
4301 }
4302 lg2_page = umin(lg2_page, -1+ b);
4303 }
4304 }
4305 }
4306 page_size = 1u <<lg2_page;
4307 page_mask = ~0ull<<lg2_page;
4308
4309 progid = 0; // getRandomId(); not useful, so do not clutter
4310 sz_elf_hdrs = sizeof(ehdri) + sz_phdrs;
4311
4312 // only execute if option present
4313 if (opt->o_unix.preserve_build_id) {
4314 // set this so we can use elf_find_section_name
4315 e_shnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_shnum);
4316 if (!shdri) {
4317 mb_shdr.alloc(e_shnum * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr));
4318 shdri = (Elf32_Shdr *)mb_shdr.getVoidPtr();
4319 e_shoff = get_te32(&ehdri.e_shoff);
4320 fi->seek(e_shoff, SEEK_SET);
4321 fi->readx(shdri, e_shnum * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr));
4322 }
4323 //set the shstrtab
4324 sec_strndx = &shdri[get_te16(&ehdri.e_shstrndx)];
4325
4326 upx_uint32_t sh_size = get_te32(&sec_strndx->sh_size);
4327 mb_shstrtab.alloc(sh_size); shstrtab = (char *)mb_shstrtab.getVoidPtr();
4328 fi->seek(0,SEEK_SET);
4329 fi->seek(sec_strndx->sh_offset,SEEK_SET);
4330 fi->readx(mb_shstrtab, sh_size);
4331
4332 Elf32_Shdr const *buildid = elf_find_section_name(".note.gnu.build-id");
4333 if (buildid) {
4334 unsigned bid_sh_size = get_te32(&buildid->sh_size);
4335 buildid_data.alloc(bid_sh_size);
4336 buildid_data.clear();
4337 fi->seek(0,SEEK_SET);
4338 fi->seek(buildid->sh_offset,SEEK_SET);
4339 fi->readx((void *)buildid_data, bid_sh_size);
4340
4341 o_elf_shnum = 3;
4342 memset(&shdrout,0,sizeof(shdrout));
4343
4344 //setup the build-id
4345 memcpy(&shdrout.shdr[1], buildid, sizeof(shdrout.shdr[1]));
4346 set_te32(&shdrout.shdr[1].sh_name, 1);
4347
4348 //setup the shstrtab
4349 memcpy(&shdrout.shdr[2], sec_strndx, sizeof(shdrout.shdr[2]));
4350 set_te32(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_name, 20);
4351 set_te32(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_size, 29); //size of our static shstrtab
4352 }
4353 }
4354}

4372void PackLinuxElf32armLe::pack1(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft)
4373{
4374 super::pack1(fo, ft);
4375 if (0!=xct_off) // shared library
4376 return;
4377 unsigned const e_flags = get_te32(&ehdri.e_flags);
4378 cprElfHdr3 h3;
4379 if (Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_LINUX==ei_osabi) {
4380 memcpy(&h3, stub_arm_v5a_linux_elf_fold, sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + 2*sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
4381
4382 h3.ehdr.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_ABIVERSION] = e_flags>>24;
4383 }
4384 else {
4385 memcpy(&h3, stub_arm_v4a_linux_elf_fold, sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + 2*sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
4386 }
4387 // Fighting over .e_ident[EI_ABIVERSION]: Debian armhf is latest culprit.
4388 // So copy from input to output; but see PackLinuxElf32::generateElfHdr
4389 memcpy(&h3.ehdr.e_ident[0], &ehdri.e_ident[0], sizeof(ehdri.e_ident));
4390 set_te32(&h3.ehdr.e_flags, e_flags);
4391 generateElfHdr(fo, &h3, getbrk(phdri, e_phnum) );
4392}
