4449
4450void PackLinuxElf64::asl_pack2_Shdrs(OutputFile *fo, unsigned pre_xct_top)
4451{
4452 if (!fo) {
4453 return;
4454 }
4455 // In order to pacify the runtime linker on Android "O" ("Oreo"),
4456 // we will splice-in a 4KiB page that contains an "extra" copy
4457 // of the Shdr, any PT_NOTE above xct_off, and shstrtab.
4458 // File order: Ehdr, Phdr[], section contents below xct_off,
4459 // Shdr_copy[], PT_NOTEs.hi, shstrtab.
4460 xct_va += asl_delta;
4461 //xct_off += asl_delta; // not until ::pack3()
4462
4463 total_in = pre_xct_top;
4464
4465 // Relocate PT_DYNAMIC (in PT_LOAD with PF_W)
4466 Elf64_Dyn *dyn = const_cast<Elf64_Dyn *>(dynseg);
4467 for (; dyn->d_tag; ++dyn) {
4468 upx_uint64_t d_tag = get_te64(&dyn->d_tag);
4469 if (Elf64_Dyn::DT_FINI == d_tag
4470 || Elf64_Dyn::DT_FINI_ARRAY == d_tag
4471 || Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY == d_tag
4472 || Elf64_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY == d_tag
4473 || Elf64_Dyn::DT_PLTGOT == d_tag) {
4474 upx_uint64_t d_val = get_te64(&dyn->d_val);
4475 set_te64(&dyn->d_val, asl_delta + d_val);
4476 }
4477 }
4478 // Updated dynseg (.dynamic, in PT_DYNAMIC (PT_LOAD{PF_W})) has not been written.
4479 // dynseg is in file_image[] but not in low_mem[].
4480
4481 // Relocate dynsym (DT_SYMTAB) which is below xct_va
4482 upx_uint64_t const off_dynsym = get_te64(&sec_dynsym->sh_offset);
4483 upx_uint64_t const sz_dynsym = get_te64(&sec_dynsym->sh_size);
4484 if ((upx_uint64_t)file_size < sz_dynsym
4485 || (upx_uint64_t)file_size < off_dynsym
4486 || ((upx_uint64_t)file_size - off_dynsym) < sz_dynsym) {
4487 throwCantPack("bad DT_SYMTAB");
4488 }
4489 Elf64_Sym *dyntym = (Elf64_Sym *)lowmem.subref(
4490 "bad dynsym", off_dynsym, sz_dynsym);
4491 Elf64_Sym *sym = dyntym;
4492 for (int j = sz_dynsym / sizeof(Elf64_Sym); --j>=0; ++sym) {
4493 upx_uint64_t symval = get_te64(&sym->st_value);
4494 unsigned symsec = get_te16(&sym->st_shndx);
4495 if (Elf64_Sym::SHN_UNDEF != symsec
4496 && Elf64_Sym::SHN_ABS != symsec
4497 && xct_off <= symval) {
4498 set_te64(&sym->st_value, asl_delta + symval);
4499 }
4500 if (Elf64_Sym::SHN_ABS == symsec && xct_off <= symval) {
4501 adjABS(sym, asl_delta);
4502 }
4503 }
4504
4505 // Relocate Phdr virtual addresses, but not physical offsets and sizes
4506 unsigned char buf_notes[512]; memset(buf_notes, 0, sizeof(buf_notes));
4507 unsigned len_notes = 0;
4508 Elf64_Phdr *phdr = (Elf64_Phdr *)lowmem.subref(
4509 "bad e_phoff", e_phoff, e_phnum * sizeof(Elf64_Phdr));
4510 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
4511 upx_uint64_t offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
4512 if (xct_off <= offset) { // above the extra page
4513 {
4514 //set_te64(&phdr->p_offset, asl_delta + offset); // physical
4515 upx_uint64_t addr = get_te64(&phdr->p_paddr);
4516 set_te64(&phdr->p_paddr, asl_delta + addr);
4517 addr = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr);
4518 set_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr, asl_delta + addr);
4519 }
4520 }
4521 // .p_filesz,.p_memsz are updated in ::pack3
4522 }
4523
4524 Elf64_Ehdr *const ehdr = (Elf64_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0];
4525 upx_uint64_t e_entry = get_te64(&ehdr->e_entry);
4526 if (xct_off < e_entry) {
4527 set_te64(&ehdr->e_entry, asl_delta + e_entry);
4528 }
4529 // Relocate Shdr; and Rela, Rel (below xct_off)
4530 unsigned const pal_xct_top = up8(pre_xct_top);
4531 set_te64(&ehdr->e_shoff, up8(pal_xct_top)); // Shdr alignment
4532 memcpy(&lowmem[pal_xct_top], shdri, e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
4533 shdro = (Elf64_Shdr *)&lowmem[pal_xct_top];
4534 Elf64_Shdr *shdr = shdro;
4535 upx_uint64_t sz_shstrtab = get_te64(&sec_strndx->sh_size);
4536 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_shnum; ++j, ++shdr) {
4537 unsigned sh_type = get_te32(&shdr->sh_type);
4538 upx_uint64_t sh_size = get_te64(&shdr->sh_size);
4539 upx_uint64_t sh_offset = get_te64(&shdr->sh_offset);
4540 upx_uint64_t sh_entsize = get_te64(&shdr->sh_entsize);
4541 if ((upx_uint64_t)file_size < sh_size
4542 || (upx_uint64_t)file_size < sh_offset
4543 || (Elf64_Shdr::SHT_NOBITS != sh_type
4544 && ((upx_uint64_t)file_size - sh_offset) < sh_size) ) {
4545 throwCantPack("bad SHT_STRNDX");
4546 }
4547
4548 if (xct_off <= sh_offset) {
4549 upx_uint64_t addr = get_te64(&shdr->sh_addr);
4550 set_te64(&shdr->sh_addr, asl_delta + addr);
4551 set_te64(&shdr->sh_offset, asl_delta + sh_offset);
4552 }
4553 switch (sh_type) {
4554 default: break;
4555 case Elf64_Shdr::SHT_RELA: {
4556 if (sizeof(Elf64_Rela) != sh_entsize) {
4557 char msg[50];
4558 snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad Rela.sh_entsize %lu", (long)sh_entsize);
4559 throwCantPack(msg);
4560 }
4561 plt_va = ~0ull;
4562 Elf64_Rela *const relb = (Elf64_Rela *)lowmem.subref(
4563 "bad Rela offset", sh_offset, sh_size);
4564 Elf64_Rela *rela = relb;
4565 for (int k = sh_size / sh_entsize; --k >= 0; ++rela) {
4566 upx_uint64_t r_addend = get_te64(&rela->r_addend);
4567 upx_uint64_t r_offset = get_te64(&rela->r_offset);
4568 upx_uint64_t r_info = get_te64(&rela->r_info);
4569 unsigned r_type = ELF64_R_TYPE(r_info);
4570 if (xct_off <= r_offset) {
4571 set_te64(&rela->r_offset, asl_delta + r_offset);
4572 }
4573 if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64 == e_machine) switch (r_type) {
4574 default: {
4575 char msg[90]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
4576 "unexpected relocation %#x [%#x]",
4577 r_type, -1 + (unsigned)(sh_size / sh_entsize) - k);
4578 throwCantPack(msg);
4579 } break;
4580 case R_AARCH64_ABS64: // FALL THROUGH
4581 case R_AARCH64_GLOB_DAT: // FALL THROUGH
4582 case R_AARCH64_RELATIVE: {
4583 if (xct_off <= r_addend) {
4584 set_te64(&rela->r_addend, asl_delta + r_addend);
4585 }
4586 } break;
4587 case R_AARCH64_JUMP_SLOT: {
4588 // .rela.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
4589 if (plt_va > r_offset) {
4590 plt_va = r_offset;
4591 }
4592 upx_uint64_t d = elf_get_offset_from_address(r_offset);
4593 upx_uint64_t w = get_te64(&file_image[d]);
4594 if (xct_off <= w) {
4595 set_te64(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4596 }
4597 ++n_jmp_slot;
4598 } break;
4599 }
4600 }
4601 }; break;
4602 case Elf64_Shdr::SHT_REL: {
4603 if (sizeof(Elf64_Rel) != sh_entsize) {
4604 char msg[50];
4605 snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad Rel.sh_entsize %lu", (long)sh_entsize);
4606 throwCantPack(msg);
4607 }
4608 Elf64_Rel *rel = (Elf64_Rel *)lowmem.subref(
4609 "bad Rel sh_offset", sh_offset, sh_size);
4610 for (int k = sh_size / sh_entsize; --k >= 0; ++rel) {
4611 upx_uint64_t r_offset = get_te64(&rel->r_offset);
4612 if (xct_off <= r_offset) {
4613 set_te64(&rel->r_offset, asl_delta + r_offset);
4614 }
4615 // r_offset must be in 2nd PT_LOAD; .p_vaddr was already relocated
4616 upx_uint64_t d = elf_get_offset_from_address(asl_delta + r_offset);
4617 upx_uint64_t w = get_te64(&file_image[d]);
4618 upx_uint64_t r_info = get_te64(&rel->r_info);
4619 unsigned r_type = ELF64_R_TYPE(r_info);
4620 if (xct_off <= w
4621 && Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64 == e_machine
4622 && ( R_AARCH64_RELATIVE == r_type
4623 || R_AARCH64_JUMP_SLOT == r_type)) {
4624 set_te64(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4625 }
4626 }
4627 }; break;
4628 case Elf64_Shdr::SHT_NOTE: {
4629 if (!(Elf64_Shdr::SHF_ALLOC & get_te64(&shdr->sh_flags))) {
4630 // example: version number of 'gold' linker (static binder)
4631 if (sizeof(buf_notes) < (sh_size + len_notes)) {
4632 throwCantPack("SHT_NOTEs too big");
4633 }
4634 set_te64(&shdro[j].sh_offset,
4635 len_notes + (e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr)) + xct_off);
4636 memcpy(&buf_notes[len_notes], &file_image[sh_offset], sh_size);
4637 len_notes += sh_size;
4638 }
4639 else { // SHF_ALLOC: in PT_LOAD; but move sh_addr and sh_offset
4640 // Not sure why we need this conditional.
4641 // Anyway, some Android have multiple SHT_NOTE sections.
4642 if (xct_off <= sh_offset) {
4643 upx_uint64_t pos = xct_off + e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr);
4644 set_te64(&shdr->sh_addr, pos);
4645 set_te64(&shdr->sh_offset, pos);
4646 }
4647 }
4648 }; break;
4649 } // end switch (sh_type)
4650 }
4651 // shstrndx will move
4652 set_te64(&shdro[get_te16(&ehdri.e_shstrndx)].sh_offset,
4653 len_notes + e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr) + pal_xct_top);
4654
4655 // ("Re-")write all changes below pal_xct_top
4656 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
4657 fo->write(lowmem, pal_xct_top);
4658 total_in = pal_xct_top;
4659
4660 // New copy of Shdr
4661 Elf64_Shdr blank; memset(&blank, 0, sizeof(blank));
4662 set_te64(&blank.sh_offset, xct_off); // hint for "upx -d"
4663 fpad8(fo, total_out); // Shdr alignment
4664 fo->write(&blank, sizeof(blank));
4665 fo->write(&shdro[1], (-1+ e_shnum) * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
4666
4667 if (len_notes) {
4668 fo->write(buf_notes, len_notes);
4669 }
4670
4671 // New copy of Shdr[.e_shstrndx].[ sh_offset, +.sh_size )
4672 fo->write(shstrtab, sz_shstrtab);
4673
4674 sz_elf_hdrs = fpad8(fo, total_out);
4675 total_out = sz_elf_hdrs;
4676 //xct_off += asl_delta; // wait until ::pack3
4677 unsigned d = asl_delta + pal_xct_top - sz_elf_hdrs;
4678 fo->seek(d, SEEK_CUR);
4679 total_out += d;
4680}
4681
4682// asl (ANdroid Shared Library) creates a big mess!
4683void PackLinuxElf32::asl_pack2_Shdrs(OutputFile *fo, unsigned pre_xct_top)
4684{
4685 if (!fo) {
4686 return;
4687 }
4688 // In order to pacify the runtime linker on Android "O" ("Oreo"),
4689 // we will splice-in a 4KiB page that contains an "extra" copy
4690 // of the Shdr, any PT_NOTE above xct_off, and shstrtab.
4691 // File order: Ehdr, Phdr[], section contents below xct_off,
4692 // Shdr_copy[], PT_NOTEs.hi, shstrtab.
4693 xct_va += asl_delta;
4694 //xct_off += asl_delta; // not until ::pack3()
4695
4696 total_in = pre_xct_top;
4697
4698 // Relocate PT_DYNAMIC (in PT_LOAD with PF_W)
4699 Elf32_Dyn *dyn = const_cast<Elf32_Dyn *>(dynseg);
4700 for (; dyn->d_tag; ++dyn) {
4701 upx_uint32_t d_tag = get_te32(&dyn->d_tag);
4702 if (Elf32_Dyn::DT_FINI == d_tag
4703 || Elf32_Dyn::DT_FINI_ARRAY == d_tag
4704 || Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY == d_tag
4705 || Elf32_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY == d_tag
4706 || Elf32_Dyn::DT_PLTGOT == d_tag) {
4707 upx_uint32_t d_val = get_te32(&dyn->d_val);
4708 set_te32(&dyn->d_val, asl_delta + d_val);
4709 }
4710 }
4711 // Updated dynseg (.dynamic, in PT_DYNAMIC (PT_LOAD{PF_W})) has not been written.
4712 // dynseg is in file_image[] but not in low_mem[].
4713
4714 // Relocate dynsym (DT_SYMTAB) which is below xct_va
4715 upx_uint32_t const off_dynsym = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_offset);
4716 upx_uint32_t const sz_dynsym = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_size);
4717 if ((upx_uint32_t)file_size < sz_dynsym
4718 || (upx_uint32_t)file_size < off_dynsym
4719 || ((upx_uint32_t)file_size - off_dynsym) < sz_dynsym) {
4720 throwCantPack("bad DT_SYMTAB");
4721 }
4722 Elf32_Sym *dyntym = (Elf32_Sym *)lowmem.subref(
4723 "bad dynsym", off_dynsym, sz_dynsym);
4724 Elf32_Sym *sym = dyntym;
4725 for (int j = sz_dynsym / sizeof(Elf32_Sym); --j>=0; ++sym) {
4726 upx_uint32_t symval = get_te32(&sym->st_value);
4727 unsigned symsec = get_te16(&sym->st_shndx);
4728 if (Elf32_Sym::SHN_UNDEF != symsec
4729 && Elf32_Sym::SHN_ABS != symsec
4730 && xct_off <= symval) {
4731 set_te32(&sym->st_value, asl_delta + symval);
4732 }
4733 if (Elf32_Sym::SHN_ABS == symsec && xct_off <= symval) {
4734 adjABS(sym, asl_delta);
4735 }
4736 }
4737
4738 // Relocate Phdr virtual addresses, but not physical offsets and sizes
4739 unsigned char buf_notes[512]; memset(buf_notes, 0, sizeof(buf_notes));
4740 unsigned len_notes = 0;
4741 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = (Elf32_Phdr *)lowmem.subref(
4742 "bad e_phoff", e_phoff, e_phnum * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
4743 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
4744 upx_uint32_t offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
4745 if (xct_off <= offset) { // above the extra page
4746 {
4747 //set_te32(&phdr->p_offset, asl_delta + offset); // physical
4748 upx_uint32_t v_addr = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
4749 set_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr, asl_delta + v_addr);
4750 upx_uint32_t p_addr = get_te32(&phdr->p_paddr);
4751 set_te32(&phdr->p_paddr, asl_delta + p_addr);
4752 }
4753 }
4754 // .p_filesz,.p_memsz are updated in ::pack3
4755 }
4756
4757 Elf32_Ehdr *const ehdr = (Elf32_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0];
4758 upx_uint32_t e_entry = get_te32(&ehdr->e_entry);
4759 if (xct_off <= e_entry) { // FIXME: --android-shlib is different
4760 set_te32(&ehdr->e_entry, asl_delta + e_entry);
4761 }
4762 // Relocate Shdr; and Rela, Rel (below xct_off)
4763 unsigned const pal_xct_top = up4(pre_xct_top);
4764 set_te32(&ehdr->e_shoff, pal_xct_top); // Shdr alignment
4765 memcpy(&lowmem[pal_xct_top], shdri, e_shnum * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr));
4766 shdro = (Elf32_Shdr *)&lowmem[pal_xct_top];
4767 Elf32_Shdr *shdr = shdro;
4768 upx_uint32_t sz_shstrtab = get_te32(&sec_strndx->sh_size);
4769 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_shnum; ++j, ++shdr) {
4770 unsigned sh_type = get_te32(&shdr->sh_type);
4771 upx_uint32_t sh_size = get_te32(&shdr->sh_size);
4772 upx_uint32_t sh_offset = get_te32(&shdr->sh_offset);
4773 upx_uint32_t sh_entsize = get_te32(&shdr->sh_entsize);
4774 if ((upx_uint32_t)file_size < sh_size
4775 || (upx_uint32_t)file_size < sh_offset
4776 || (Elf32_Shdr::SHT_NOBITS != sh_type
4777 && ((upx_uint32_t)file_size - sh_offset) < sh_size) ) {
4778 throwCantPack("bad SHT_STRNDX");
4779 }
4780
4781 if (xct_off <= sh_offset && Elf32_Shdr::SHF_ALLOC & get_te32(&shdr->sh_flags)) {
4782 //upx_uint32_t addr = get_te32(&shdr->sh_addr);
4783 //set_te32(&shdr->sh_addr, asl_delta + addr);
4784 set_te32(&shdr->sh_offset, asl_delta + sh_offset);
4785 }
4786 switch (sh_type) {
4787 default: break;
4788 case Elf32_Shdr::SHT_RELA: { // 32-bit Elf_Rela is unused (by convention)
4789 if (sizeof(Elf32_Rela) != sh_entsize) {
4790 char msg[50];
4791 snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad Rela.sh_entsize %lu", (long)sh_entsize);
4792 throwCantPack(msg);
4793 }
4794 plt_va = ~0ull;
4795 Elf32_Rela *const relb = (Elf32_Rela *)lowmem.subref(
4796 "bad Rela offset", sh_offset, sh_size);
4797 Elf32_Rela *rela = relb;
4798 for (int k = sh_size / sh_entsize; --k >= 0; ++rela) {
4799 upx_uint32_t r_addend = get_te32(&rela->r_addend);
4800 upx_uint32_t r_offset = get_te32(&rela->r_offset);
4801 upx_uint32_t r_info = get_te32(&rela->r_info);
4802 unsigned r_type = ELF32_R_TYPE(r_info);
4803 if (xct_off <= r_offset) {
4804 set_te32(&rela->r_offset, asl_delta + r_offset);
4805 }
4806 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386 == e_machine) switch (r_type) {
4807 default: {
4808 char msg[90]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
4809 "unexpected relocation %#x [%#x]",
4810 r_type, -1 + (unsigned)(sh_size / sh_entsize) - k);
4811 throwCantPack(msg);
4812 } break;
4813 case R_386_32: // FALL THROUGH
4814 case R_386_GLOB_DAT: // FALL THROUGH
4815 case R_386_RELATIVE: {
4816 if (xct_off <= r_addend) {
4817 set_te32(&rela->r_addend, asl_delta + r_addend);
4818 }
4819 } break;
4820 case R_386_JMP_SLOT: {
4821 // .rela.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
4822 if (plt_va > r_offset) {
4823 plt_va = r_offset;
4824 }
4825 upx_uint32_t d = elf_get_offset_from_address(r_offset);
4826 upx_uint32_t w = get_te32(&file_image[d]);
4827 if (xct_off <= w) {
4828 set_te32(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4829 }
4830 ++n_jmp_slot;
4831 } break;
4832 } // end EM_386 r_type
4833 else if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine) switch (r_type) {
4834 default: {
4835 char msg[90]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
4836 "unexpected relocation %#x [%#x]",
4837 r_type, -1 + (unsigned)(sh_size / sh_entsize) - k);
4838 throwCantPack(msg);
4839 } break;
4840 case R_ARM_ABS32: // FALL THROUGH
4841 case R_ARM_GLOB_DAT: // FALL THROUGH
4842 case R_ARM_RELATIVE: {
4843 if (xct_off <= r_addend) {
4844 set_te32(&rela->r_addend, asl_delta + r_addend);
4845 }
4846 } break;
4847 case R_ARM_JUMP_SLOT: {
4848 // .rela.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
4849 if (plt_va > r_offset) {
4850 plt_va = r_offset;
4851 }
4852 upx_uint32_t d = elf_get_offset_from_address(r_offset);
4853 upx_uint32_t w = get_te32(&file_image[d]);
4854 if (xct_off <= w) {
4855 set_te32(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4856 }
4857 ++n_jmp_slot;
4858 } break;
4859 } // end EM_ARM r_type
4860 else {
4861 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
4862 "Unknown architecture %d", this->e_machine);
4863 throwCantPack(msg);
4864 } // end e_machine
4865 }
4866 }; break; // end Elf32_Shdr::SHT_RELA
4867 case Elf32_Shdr::SHT_REL: {
4868 if (sizeof(Elf32_Rel) != sh_entsize) {
4869 char msg[50];
4870 snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad Rel.sh_entsize %lu", (long)sh_entsize);
4871 throwCantPack(msg);
4872 }
4873 Elf32_Rel *rel = (Elf32_Rel *)lowmem.subref(
4874 "bad Rel sh_offset", sh_offset, sh_size);
4875 for (int k = sh_size / sh_entsize; --k >= 0; ++rel) {
4876 upx_uint32_t r_offset = get_te32(&rel->r_offset);
4877 if (xct_off <= r_offset) {
4878 set_te32(&rel->r_offset, asl_delta + r_offset);
4879 }
4880 // r_offset must be in 2nd PT_LOAD; .p_vaddr was already relocated
4881 if (0x9055c == r_offset || 0x9155c==r_offset) {
4882 //printf("Here!\n");
4883 }
4884 upx_uint32_t d = elf_get_offset_from_address(r_offset);
4885 upx_uint32_t w = get_te32(&file_image[d]);
4886 upx_uint32_t r_info = get_te32(&rel->r_info);
4887 unsigned r_type = ELF32_R_TYPE(r_info);
4888 //printf("d=%#x w=%#x r_info=%#x\n", d, w, r_info);
4889 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386 == e_machine) switch (r_type) {
4890 default: {
4891 char msg[90]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
4892 "unexpected relocation %#x [%#x]",
4893 r_type, -1 + (unsigned)(sh_size / sh_entsize) - k);
4894 throwCantPack(msg);
4895 } break;
4896 case R_386_32: // FALL THROUGH
4897 case R_386_GLOB_DAT: // FALL THROUGH
4898 case R_386_RELATIVE: {
4899 if (xct_off <= w) {
4900 set_te32(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4901 }
4902 } break;
4903 case R_386_JMP_SLOT: {
4904 // .rela.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
4905 if (plt_va > r_offset) {
4906 plt_va = r_offset;
4907 }
4908 if (xct_off <= w) {
4909 set_te32(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4910 }
4911 ++n_jmp_slot;
4912 } break;
4913 } // end EM_386 r_type
4914 else if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine) switch (r_type) {
4915 default: {
4916 char msg[90]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
4917 "unexpected relocation %#x [%#x]",
4918 r_type, -1 + (unsigned)(sh_size / sh_entsize) - k);
4919 throwCantPack(msg);
4920 } break;
4921 case R_ARM_ABS32: // FALL THROUGH
4922 case R_ARM_GLOB_DAT: // FALL THROUGH
4923 case R_ARM_RELATIVE: {
4924 if (xct_off <= w) {
4925 set_te32(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4926 }
4927 } break;
4928 case R_ARM_JUMP_SLOT: {
4929 // .rela.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
4930 if (plt_va > r_offset) {
4931 plt_va = r_offset;
4932 }
4933 if (xct_off <= w) {
4934 set_te32(&file_image[d], asl_delta + w);
4935 }
4936 ++n_jmp_slot;
4937 } break;
4938 } // end EM_ARM r_type
4939 else {
4940 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
4941 "Unknown architecture %d", this->e_machine);
4942 throwCantPack(msg);
4943 } // end e_machine
4944 } // end rel
4945 }; break; // end Elf32_Shdr::SHT_REL
4946 case Elf32_Shdr::SHT_NOTE: {
4947 if (!(Elf32_Shdr::SHF_ALLOC & get_te32(&shdr->sh_flags))) {
4948 // example: version number of 'gold' linker (static binder)
4949 if (sizeof(buf_notes) < (sh_size + len_notes)) {
4950 throwCantPack("SHT_NOTEs too big");
4951 }
4952 set_te32(&shdro[j].sh_offset,
4953 len_notes + (e_shnum * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr)) + xct_off);
4954 memcpy(&buf_notes[len_notes], &file_image[sh_offset], sh_size);
4955 len_notes += sh_size;
4956 }
4957 else { // SHF_ALLOC: in PT_LOAD; but move sh_addr and sh_offset
4958 // Not sure why we need this conditional.
4959 // Anyway, some Android have multiple SHT_NOTE sections.
4960 if (xct_off <= sh_offset) {
4961 upx_uint32_t pos = xct_off + e_shnum * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr);
4962 //set_te32(&shdr->sh_addr, pos);
4963 set_te32(&shdr->sh_offset, pos);
4964 }
4965 }
4966 }; break; // end Elf32_Shdr::SHT_NOTE
4967 case Elf32_Shdr::SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES: {
4968 sec_arm_attr = shdr;
4969 }; break;
4970 } // end switch (sh_type)
4971 }
4972 // shstrndx will move
4973 set_te32(&shdro[get_te16(&ehdri.e_shstrndx)].sh_offset,
4974 len_notes + e_shnum * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr) + up8(pal_xct_top));
4975
4976 // Write all changes below pal_xct_top
4977 // FIXME: why is this any more than Ehdr + Phdrs?
4978 if (fo) {
4979 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
4980 fo->write(lowmem, pal_xct_top);
4981 }
4982 total_out = pal_xct_top;
4983 total_in = pal_xct_top;
4984
4985 // New copy of Shdr
4986 Elf32_Shdr blank; memset(&blank, 0, sizeof(blank));
4987 set_te32(&blank.sh_offset, xct_off); // hint for "upx -d"
4988 set_te32(&shdro->sh_offset, xct_off); // hint for "upx -d"
4989 total_out = fpad8(fo, total_out); // Shdr alignment
4990 unsigned arm_attr_off = 0;
4991 if (sec_arm_attr) {
4992 arm_attr_off = get_te32(&sec_arm_attr->sh_offset);
4993 set_te32(&sec_arm_attr->sh_offset,
4994 total_out + e_shnum*sizeof(Elf32_Shdr)
4995 + len_notes + sz_shstrtab);
4996 }
4997 if (fo) {
4998 fo->write(&blank, sizeof(blank));
4999 fo->write(&shdro[1], (-1+ e_shnum) * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr));
5000 if (len_notes) {
5001 fo->write(buf_notes, len_notes);
5002 }
5003 // New copy of Shdr[.e_shstrndx].[ sh_offset, +.sh_size )
5004 fo->write(shstrtab, sz_shstrtab);
5005
5006 if (sec_arm_attr) {
5007 fo->write(&file_image[arm_attr_off],
5008 get_te32(&sec_arm_attr->sh_size));
5009 }
5010 }
5011
5012 sz_elf_hdrs = fpad8(fo, total_out);
5013 total_out = sz_elf_hdrs;
5014 //xct_off += asl_delta; // wait until ::pack3
5015 total_out = fpadN(fo, asl_delta - (sz_elf_hdrs - pal_xct_top));
5016}
5017
5018void PackLinuxElf64::pack1(OutputFile * /*fo*/, Filter &ft)
5019{
5020 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
5021 fi->readx(&ehdri, sizeof(ehdri));
5022 assert(e_phoff == sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr)); // checked by canPack()
5023 sz_phdrs = e_phnum * get_te16(&ehdri.e_phentsize);
5024
5025// We compress separate pieces (usually each PT_LOAD, plus the gaps in the file
5026// that are not covered by any PT_LOAD), but currently at run time there can be
5027// only one decompressor method.
5028// Therefore we must plan ahead because Packer::compressWithFilters tries
5029// to find the smallest result among the available methods, for one piece only.
5030// In the future we may allow more than one decompression method at run time.
5031// For now we must choose only one, and force PackUnix::packExtent
5032// (==> compressWithFilters) to use it.
5033 int nfilters = 0;
5034 {
5035 int const *fp = getFilters();
5036 while (FT_END != *fp++) {
5037 ++nfilters;
5038 }
5039 }
5040 {
5041 int npieces = 1; // tail after highest PT_LOAD
5042 Elf64_Phdr *phdr = phdri;
5043 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
5044 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
5045 unsigned const flags = get_te32(&phdr->p_flags);
5046 unsigned offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
5047 if (!xct_off // not shlib
5048 // new-style shlib: PT_LOAD[0] has symbol table
5049 // which must not be compressed, but also lacks PF_X
5050 || (Elf64_Phdr::PF_X & flags)
5051 // Read-only, non-first PT_LOAD is _assumed_ to be compressible
5052 || (!(Elf64_Phdr::PF_W & flags) && 0!=offset))
5053 {
5054 ++npieces; // will attempt compression of this PT_LOAD
5055 }
5056 }
5057 }
5058 uip->ui_total_passes += npieces;
5059 }
5060 int methods[256];
5061 unsigned nmethods = prepareMethods(methods, ph.method, getCompressionMethods(M_ALL, ph.level));
5062 if (1 < nmethods) { // Many are available, but we must choose only one
5063 uip->ui_total_passes += 1; // the batch for output
5064 uip->ui_total_passes *= nmethods * (1+ nfilters); // finding smallest total
5065 PackHeader orig_ph = ph;
5066 Filter orig_ft = ft;
5067 unsigned max_offset = 0;
5068 unsigned sz_best= ~0u;
5069 int method_best = 0;
5070 for (unsigned k = 0; k < nmethods; ++k) { // FIXME: parallelize; cost: working space
5071 unsigned sz_this = 0;
5072 Elf64_Phdr *phdr = phdri;
5073 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
5074 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
5075 unsigned const flags = get_te32(&phdr->p_flags);
5076 unsigned offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
5077 unsigned filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
5078 max_offset = UPX_MAX(max_offset, filesz + offset);
5079 if (!xct_off // not shlib
5080 // new-style shlib: PT_LOAD[0] has symbol table
5081 // which must not be compressed, but also lacks PF_X
5082 || (Elf64_Phdr::PF_X & flags)
5083 // Read-only, non-first PT_LOAD is _assumed_ to be compressible
5084 || (!(Elf64_Phdr::PF_W & flags) && 0!=offset))
5085 {
5086 if (xct_off && 0==offset) { // old-style shlib
5087 offset = xct_off;
5088 filesz -= xct_off;
5089 }
5090 fi->seek(offset, SEEK_SET);
5091 fi->readx(ibuf, filesz);
5092 ft = orig_ft;
5093 ph = orig_ph;
5094 ph.method = ph_force_method(methods[k]);
5095 ph.u_len = filesz;
5096 compressWithFilters(&ft, OVERHEAD, NULL_cconf, 10, true);
5097 sz_this += ph.c_len;
5098 }
5099 }
5100 }
5101 unsigned const sz_tail = file_size - max_offset; // debuginfo, etc.
5102 if (sz_tail) {
5103 fi->seek(max_offset, SEEK_SET);
5104 fi->readx(ibuf, sz_tail);
5105 ft = orig_ft;
5106 ph = orig_ph;
5107 ph.method = ph_force_method(methods[k]);
5108 ph.u_len = sz_tail;
5109 compressWithFilters(&ft, OVERHEAD, NULL_cconf, 10, true);
5110 sz_this += ph.c_len;
5111 }
5112 // FIXME: loader size also depends on method
5113 if (sz_best > sz_this) {
5114 sz_best = sz_this;
5115 method_best = methods[k];
5116 }
5117 }
5118 ft = orig_ft;
5119 ph = orig_ph;
5120 ph.method = ph_force_method(method_best);
5121 }
5122
5123 Elf64_Phdr *phdr = phdri;
5124 for (unsigned j=0; j < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
5125 unsigned const type = get_te32(&phdr->p_type);
5126 if (PT_GNU_STACK64 == type || PT_NOTE64 == type) {
5127 add_phdrx(phdr); // PT_GNU_STACK64, PT_NOTE64
5128 }
5129 if (PT_LOAD == type) {
5130 unsigned x = get_te64(&phdr->p_align) >> lg2_page;
5131 while (x>>=1) {
5132 ++lg2_page;
5133 }
5134 }
5135 if (PT_GNU_RELRO64 == type
5136 && 16 < lg2_page) {
5137 // x86* allows 4K, 2M, 1G
5138 // arm32 and arm64 both allow 4K, 16K, 64K; Apple Silicon uses 16K
5139 // Oracle 5.4.17-2136.314.6.2.el8uek.aarch64 demands 64K
5140 // PowerPC and PowerPC64 has 4K, 64K, 1M (?), 16M (?)
5141 // MIPS allows any power of 2 from 4K through 64K
5142
5143 // If 64K < .p_align then we assume that 4K is also accepted.
5144 // .p_align can be like 2M, which is a huge over-estimate.
5145 // RELRO ends on a page boundary: usually close to actual page_size
5146 unsigned offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
5147 unsigned filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
5148 if (!(0xfff & (filesz + offset))) { // a 4KiB boundary
5149 unsigned b = 12;
5150 while (!(~(~0u << b) & (filesz + offset))) {
5151 ++b;
5152 }
5153 lg2_page = umin(lg2_page, -1+ b);
5154 }
5155 }
5156 }
5157 page_size = 1u <<lg2_page;
5158 page_mask = ~0ull<<lg2_page;
5159
5160 progid = 0; // getRandomId(); not useful, so do not clutter
5161 sz_elf_hdrs = sizeof(ehdri) + sz_phdrs;
5162
5163 // only execute if option present
5164 if (opt->o_unix.preserve_build_id) {
5165 // set this so we can use elf_find_section_name
5166 e_shnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_shnum);
5167 if (!shdri) {
5168 mb_shdr.alloc(e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
5169 shdri = (Elf64_Shdr *)mb_shdr.getVoidPtr();
5170 e_shoff = get_te64(&ehdri.e_shoff);
5171 fi->seek(e_shoff, SEEK_SET);
5172 fi->readx(shdri, e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
5173 }
5174 //set the shstrtab
5175 sec_strndx = &shdri[get_te16(&ehdri.e_shstrndx)];
5176
5177 upx_uint64_t sh_size = get_te64(&sec_strndx->sh_size);
5178 mb_shstrtab.alloc(sh_size); shstrtab = (char *)mb_shstrtab.getVoidPtr();
5179 fi->seek(0,SEEK_SET);
5180 fi->seek(sec_strndx->sh_offset,SEEK_SET);
5181 fi->readx(mb_shstrtab, sh_size);
5182
5183 Elf64_Shdr const *buildid = elf_find_section_name(".note.gnu.build-id");
5184 if (buildid) {
5185 unsigned bid_sh_size = get_te64(&buildid->sh_size); // UPX_RSIZE_MAX_MEM protects us
5186 buildid_data.alloc(bid_sh_size);
5187 buildid_data.clear();
5188 fi->seek(0,SEEK_SET);
5189 fi->seek(buildid->sh_offset,SEEK_SET);
5190 fi->readx((void *)buildid_data, bid_sh_size);
5191
5192 o_elf_shnum = 3;
5193 memset(&shdrout,0,sizeof(shdrout));
5194
5195 //setup the build-id
5196 memcpy(&shdrout.shdr[1], buildid, sizeof(shdrout.shdr[1]));
5197 set_te32(&shdrout.shdr[1].sh_name, 1);
5198
5199 //setup the shstrtab
5200 memcpy(&shdrout.shdr[2], sec_strndx, sizeof(shdrout.shdr[2]));
5201 set_te32(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_name, 20);
5202 set_te64(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_size, 29); //size of our static shstrtab; UPX_RSIZE_MAX_MEM
5203 }
5204 }
5205}

5222
5223// Determine length of gap between PT_LOAD phdr[k] and closest PT_LOAD
5224// which follows in the file (or end-of-file). Optimize for common case
5225// where the PT_LOAD are adjacent ascending by .p_offset. Assume no overlap.
5226
5227unsigned PackLinuxElf32::find_LOAD_gap(
5228 Elf32_Phdr const *const phdr,
5229 unsigned const k,
5230 unsigned const nph
5231)
5232{
5233 if (!is_LOAD(&phdr[k])) {
5234 return 0;
5235 }
5236 unsigned const hi = get_te32(&phdr[k].p_offset) +
5237 get_te32(&phdr[k].p_filesz);
5238 unsigned lo = ph.u_file_size;
5239 if (lo < hi)
5240 throwCantPack("bad input: PT_LOAD beyond end-of-file");
5241 unsigned j = k;
5242 for (;;) { // circular search, optimize for adjacent ascending
5243 ++j;
5244 if (nph==j) {
5245 j = 0;
5246 }
5247 if (k==j) {
5248 break;
5249 }
5250 if (is_LOAD(&phdr[j])) {
5251 unsigned const t = get_te32(&phdr[j].p_offset);
5252 if ((t - hi) < (lo - hi)) {
5253 lo = t;
5254 if (hi==lo) {
5255 break;
5256 }
5257 }
5258 }
5259 }
5260 return lo - hi;
5261}
5262
5263unsigned PackLinuxElf::pack2_shlib_overlay_init(OutputFile *fo)
5264{
5265 linfo.l_checksum = 0; // preliminary
5266 linfo.l_magic = UPX_MAGIC_LE32;
5267
5268 set_le16(&linfo.l_lsize, lsize); // preliminary (0)
5269 linfo.l_version = (unsigned char)ph.version;
5270 linfo.l_format = (unsigned char)ph.format;
5271 linfo_off = total_out;
5272 fo->write(&linfo, sizeof(linfo)); total_out += sizeof(linfo);
5273
5274 overlay_offset = total_out;
5275
5276 p_info hbuf;
5277 set_te32(&hbuf.p_progid, 0);
5278 set_te32(&hbuf.p_filesize, file_size);
5279 set_te32(&hbuf.p_blocksize, blocksize);
5280 fo->write(&hbuf, sizeof(hbuf)); total_out += sizeof(hbuf);
5281 return total_out;
5282}
5283
5284unsigned PackLinuxElf::pack2_shlib_overlay_write(OutputFile *fo, MemBuffer &mb,
5285 unsigned u_len, unsigned c_len)
5286{
5287 // Write mb with b_info header.
5288 b_info tmp;
5289 memset(&tmp, 0, sizeof(tmp));
5290 set_te32(&tmp.sz_unc, u_len);
5291 set_te32(&tmp.sz_cpr, c_len);
5292 tmp.b_method = (EM_ARM == e_machine) ? M_NRV2B_8 : M_NRV2B_LE32;
5293 tmp.b_extra = 0;
5294 fo->write(&tmp, sizeof(tmp)); total_out += sizeof(tmp);
5295 b_len += sizeof(b_info);
5296 fo->write(mb, c_len); total_out += c_len;
5297 return total_out;
5298}
5299
5300// Returns compressed size
5301unsigned PackLinuxElf::pack2_shlib_overlay_compress(
5302 MemBuffer &bufo,
5303 MemBuffer &bufi,
5304 unsigned u_len
5305)
5306{
5307 ph.saved_u_adler = ph.u_adler;
5308 ph.u_adler = upx_adler32(bufi, ph.u_len, ph.saved_u_adler);
5309
5310 unsigned const method = (EM_ARM == e_machine) ? M_NRV2B_8 : M_NRV2B_LE32;
5311 methods_used |= 1 << method;
5312 unsigned c_len = 0;
5313 int r = upx_compress(bufi, u_len, bufo, &c_len,
5314 /* &progress callback */ nullptr,
5315 method, 10,
5316 /* &config_t */ nullptr, /* &result_t */ nullptr);
5317 if (r != UPX_E_OK)
5318 throwInternalError("header compression failed");
5319 if (c_len >= u_len)
5320 throwInternalError("header compression size increase");
5321
5322 ph.saved_c_adler = ph.c_adler;
5323 ph.c_adler = upx_adler32(bufo, ph.c_len, ph.saved_c_adler);
5324 return c_len;
5325}
5326
5327// Layout for compressed shared library:
5328// 1. If first PT_LOAD is totally below xct_off
5329// (namely, (.p_memsz + .p_offset) <= xct_off )
5330// then it must be Ehdr+Phdrs followed only by PT_DYNAMIC (Dynamic
5331// section) and loader tables (DT_* data), and the order of output is:
5332// A. original first PT_LOAD (Ehdr+Phdrs will be overwritten later)
5333// B. compressed Ehdr+Phdrs (for de-compressor to restore); no filter
5334// C. compressed remaining PT_LOAD segments (except PT_WRITE),
5335// regardless of xct_off.
5336// Until xct_off is covered by some PT_LOAD, then there is a logical
5337// two-pass problem. The best compression algorithm is not chosen
5338// until the PT_LOAD which contains xct_off, but before that
5339// compression is desired anyway for any preceding PT_LOAD.
5340// So use NRV2B for the "early" PT_LOADs, and do not use packExtent
5341// which calls compressWithFilters and also creates a loader.
5342// Instead, do the compression "by hand" explicitly using upx_compress
5343// and write(). This may require ELF2 multi-decompressor (NRV2B
5344// on the early PT_LOADs, then something better).
5345//
5346// Example input Program Headers:
5347// Type Offset VirtAddr PhysAddr FileSiz MemSiz Flg Align
5348// LOAD 0x000000 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x003a4 0x003a4 R 0x1000 Elf hdrs, loader tables
5349// LOAD 0x001000 0x00001000 0x00001000 0x001d4 0x001d4 R E 0x1000 small code
5350// LOAD 0x002000 0x00002000 0x00002000 0x09d40 0x09d40 R 0x1000 large app consts
5351// LOAD 0x00bef0 0x0000cef0 0x0000cef0 0x00118 0x0011c RW 0x1000 writeable
5352//
5353// xct_off will have been increased artifically to point to
5354// the large compressable PT_LOAD (0x9d40==MemSiz), in order to avoid
5355// NotCompressable because the earlier PT_LOADs were too short (< 4KiB).
5356// 2. If the first PT_LOAD covers xct_off, then the order of output is:
5357// A. original Ehdr+Phdrs (overwritten later)
5358// B. other original content below xct_off [loader tables]
5359// C. compressed Ehdr+Phdrs (for de-compressor to restore); no filter.
5360// D. compressed content above xct_off in first PT_LOAD;
5361// use filter for executable code.
5362// E. compressed remaining PT_LOAD (except PT_WRITE); no filter.
5363//
5364
5365int PackLinuxElf32::pack2_shlib(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft, unsigned pre_xct_top)
5366{
5367 // prepare to alter Phdrs and Shdrs
5368 lowmem.alloc(up8(xct_off + (!is_asl
5369 ? 0
5370 : e_shnum * sizeof(Elf32_Shdr))));
5371 memcpy(lowmem, file_image, xct_off); // android omits Shdr from copy now
5372
5373 MemBuffer elf_buf;
5374 elf_buf.allocForCompression(sz_elf_hdrs);
5375 unsigned u_len = sz_elf_hdrs;
5376 unsigned c_len = pack2_shlib_overlay_compress(elf_buf, lowmem, u_len);
5377
5378 int n_ptload = 0;
5379 Elf32_Phdr *phdr = &phdri[0];
5380 for (unsigned k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++k)
5381 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
5382 unsigned p_offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
5383 unsigned p_filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
5384 if (!n_ptload) { // first PT_LOAD
5385 if (is_asl) { // Copy up to xct_off, then add 2nd copy of Shdrs
5386 asl_pack2_Shdrs(fo, pre_xct_top);
5387 }
5388 else {
5389 fi->seek(p_offset, SEEK_SET);
5390 fi->read(ibuf, sz_elf_hdrs); total_in += sz_elf_hdrs;
5391 fo->write(ibuf, sz_elf_hdrs); total_out += sz_elf_hdrs;
5392 fo->seek(sz_phdrx, SEEK_CUR); total_out += sz_phdrx;
5393
5394 // Compare PackUnix::packExtent, especially "if (u_len)" .
5395 //
5396
5397 unsigned const hi_offset = umin(xct_off, p_filesz + p_offset);
5398 if (sz_elf_hdrs < hi_offset) {
5399 // Loader tables in first PT_LOAD, and below xct_off.
5400 //
5401 fi->read(ibuf, hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs); total_in += hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs;
5402 fo->write(ibuf, hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs); total_out += hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs;
5403 Elf32_Phdr *lo_phdr = k + (Elf32_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf32_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5404 set_te32(&lo_phdr->p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_X | get_te32(&lo_phdr->p_flags));
5405 }
5406 }
5407 pack2_shlib_overlay_init(fo); // set overlay_offset
5408 // Compressed ELF headers go first.
5409 pack2_shlib_overlay_write(fo, elf_buf, u_len, c_len);
5410
5411 // The (compressible) remainder above xct_off in first PT_LOAD
5412 if ( p_filesz >= (xct_off - p_offset)) {
5413 Extent x;
5414 x.size = p_filesz - (xct_off - p_offset);
5415 x.offset = xct_off;
5416 packExtent(x, &ft, fo, 0, 0, true);
5417 }
5418 } // end first PT_LOAD
5419 else if ((p_filesz + p_offset) <= xct_off) {
5420 // Not first PT_LOAD, but below xct_offset. Thus "interloper" PT_LOAD,
5421 // below xct_off that was increased to a PT_LOAD large enough to compress.
5422 // "Manually" compress it, do not use PackExtent.
5423 fi->seek(p_offset, SEEK_SET);
5424 fi->read(ibuf, p_filesz); total_in += p_filesz;
5425 MemBuffer buf2; buf2.allocForCompression(p_filesz);
5426 c_len = pack2_shlib_overlay_compress(buf2, ibuf, p_filesz);
5427 pack2_shlib_overlay_write(fo, buf2, p_filesz, c_len);
5428 Elf32_Phdr *lo_phdr = k + (Elf32_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf32_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5429 set_te32(&lo_phdr->p_type, Elf32_Phdr::PT_NULL);
5430 }
5431 else if ((xct_off - p_offset) < p_filesz) {
5432 unsigned const len = xct_off - p_offset;
5433 // Loader tables in non-first PT_LOAD. (xct_off was increased.)
5434 // Bytes below xct_off belong to rtld, so cannot be compressed.
5435 // Note that asl_pack2_Shdrs() copies up to xct_off, then adds extra info.
5436 // Copy up to xct_off
5437 // FIXME: fo->write(&file_image[x.offset], x.size);
5438 if (len) {
5439 fi->read(ibuf, len); total_in += len;
5440 fo->write(ibuf, len); total_out += len;
5441
5442 // Compressed ELF headers FIXME: 1st PT_LOAD also did this!
5443 pack2_shlib_overlay_write(fo, elf_buf, u_len, c_len); // set overlay_offset
5444 }
5445 // The rest, above xct_off.
5446 Extent x;
5447 x.offset = xct_off;
5448 x.size = p_filesz - len;
5449 packExtent(x, &ft, fo, 0, 0, true);
5450 Elf32_Phdr *lo_phdr = k + (Elf32_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf32_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5451 set_te32(&lo_phdr->p_type, Elf32_Phdr::PT_NULL);
5452 }
5453 else { // definitely compressible unless writeable
5454 if (!(Elf32_Phdr::PF_W & get_te32(&phdr->p_flags))) {
5455 // Read-only PT_LOAD, assume not written by relocations.
5456 // Also assume not the source for R_*_COPY relocation,
5457 // therefore compress it.
5458 Extent x;
5459 x.offset = p_offset;
5460 x.size = p_filesz;
5461 packExtent(x, &ft, fo, 0, 0, true); // choose filter and method, then do it
5462 // De-compressing will re-create it, but otherwise ignore it.
5463 Elf32_Phdr *phdro = (Elf32_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf32_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5464 set_te32(&phdro[k].p_type, Elf32_Phdr::PT_NULL);
5465 }
5466 else {
5467 // Read-write PT_LOAD.
5468 // rtld might relocate, so we cannot compress.
5469 // (Could compress if not relocated; complicates run-time.)
5470 // Postpone writing until "slide", but account for its size.
5471 total_in += p_filesz;
5472 }
5473 }
5474 ++n_ptload;
5475 }
5476 return 0; // FIXME
5477}
5478
5479int PackLinuxElf32::pack2(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft)
5480{
5481 Extent x;
5482 unsigned k;
5483 is_asl = (!!opt->o_unix.android_shlib) << 1; // bit 1; see is_shlib
5484 unsigned const is_shlib = (0!=xct_off) | is_asl;
5485 unsigned pre_xct_top = 0; // offset of end of PT_LOAD _before_ xct_off
5486
5487 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM==get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine)) {
5488 sec_arm_attr = elf_find_section_type(Elf32_Shdr::SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES);
5489 }
5490 // count passes, set ptload vars
5491 uip->ui_total_passes = 0;
5492 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k) {
5493 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[k])) {
5494 if (!is_shlib) {
5495 uip->ui_total_passes++;
5496 }
5497 else {
5498 unsigned p_flags = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_flags);
5499 unsigned p_offset = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_offset);
5500 unsigned p_filesz = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
5501 if ((xct_off - p_offset) < p_filesz) { // PT_LOAD covers xct_off
5502 if (!pre_xct_top && xct_off != p_offset) {
5503 pre_xct_top = xct_off;
5504 }
5505 }
5506 else if (p_offset < xct_off) { // candidate for pre_xct_top
5507 unsigned top = p_filesz + p_offset;
5508 if (pre_xct_top < top) {
5509 pre_xct_top = top;
5510 }
5511 }
5512 if (Elf32_Phdr::PF_W & p_flags) {
5513 // rtld might write, so cannot compress
5514 }
5515 else {
5516 // First PT_LOAD (partial) only if has instructions
5517 if (k || xct_off < p_filesz) {
5518 uip->ui_total_passes++;
5519 }
5520 }
5521 }
5522 if (find_LOAD_gap(phdri, k, e_phnum)) {
5523 uip->ui_total_passes++;
5524 }
5525 }
5526 }
5527
5528 // compress extents
5529 unsigned hdr_u_len = sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + sz_phdrs;
5530
5531 total_in = 0;
5532 total_out = 0;
5533 uip->ui_pass = 0;
5534 ft.addvalue = 0;
5535
5536 unsigned nk_f = 0; upx_uint32_t xsz_f = 0;
5537 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k)
5538 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[k])
5539 && Elf32_Phdr::PF_X & get_te32(&phdri[k].p_flags)) {
5540 upx_uint32_t xsz = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
5541 if (xsz_f < xsz) {
5542 xsz_f = xsz;
5543 nk_f = k;
5544 }
5545 }
5546 if (is_shlib) {
5547 pack2_shlib(fo, ft, pre_xct_top);
5548 }
5549 else { // main program
5550 int n_ptload = 0;
5551 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k)
5552 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[k])) {
5553 if (ft.id < 0x40) {
5554 // FIXME: ?? ft.addvalue = phdri[k].p_vaddr;
5555 }
5556 unsigned p_offset = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_offset);
5557 unsigned p_filesz = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
5558 x.offset = p_offset;
5559 x.size = p_filesz;
5560 if ((u32_t)x.size < hdr_u_len) { // FIXME: main program, but how?
5561 total_in += x.size;
5562 }
5563 else { // main program, not shared library
5564 if (0 == n_ptload) { // 1st PT_LOAD must cover Ehdr at 0==p_offset
5565 unsigned const delta = hdr_u_len;
5566 if (ft.id < 0x40) {
5567 // FIXME: ?? ft.addvalue += asl_delta;
5568 }
5569 if ((off_t)delta == x.size) { // PT_LOAD[0] with ElfXX.Ehdr only
5570 // QBE backend - http://c9x.me/compile/
5571 hdr_u_len = 0; // no fiddling necessary!
5572 // &ft arg to packExtent will be zero because (k != nk_f)
5573 }
5574 else {
5575 total_in += delta - hdr_u_len;
5576 x.offset += delta;
5577 x.size -= delta;
5578 }
5579 }
5580 // compressWithFilters() always assumes a "loader", so would
5581 // throw NotCompressible for small .data Extents, which PowerPC
5582 // sometimes marks as PF_X anyway. So filter only first segment.
5583 packExtent(x,
5584 (k==nk_f ? &ft : nullptr ), fo, hdr_u_len, 0, true);
5585 hdr_u_len = 0;
5586 }
5587 ++n_ptload;
5588 }
5589 }
5590 sz_pack2a = fpad4(fo, total_out); // MATCH01
5591 total_out = up4(total_out);
5592
5593 // Accounting only; ::pack3 will do the compression and output
5594 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k) {
5595 total_in += find_LOAD_gap(phdri, k, e_phnum);
5596 }
5597
5598 if (total_in != (u32_t)file_size)
5599 throwEOFException();
5600
5601 return 0; // omit end-of-compression bhdr for now
5602}
5603
5604// Determine length of gap between PT_LOAD phdr[k] and closest PT_LOAD
5605// which follows in the file (or end-of-file). Optimize for common case
5606// where the PT_LOAD are adjacent ascending by .p_offset. Assume no overlap.
5607
5608unsigned PackLinuxElf64::find_LOAD_gap(
5609 Elf64_Phdr const *const phdr,
5610 unsigned const k,
5611 unsigned const nph
5612)
5613{
5614 if (!is_LOAD(&phdr[k])) {
5615 return 0;
5616 }
5617 unsigned const hi = get_te64(&phdr[k].p_offset) +
5618 get_te64(&phdr[k].p_filesz);
5619 unsigned lo = ph.u_file_size;
5620 if (lo < hi)
5621 throwCantPack("bad input: PT_LOAD beyond end-of-file");
5622 unsigned j = k;
5623 for (;;) { // circular search, optimize for adjacent ascending
5624 ++j;
5625 if (nph==j) {
5626 j = 0;
5627 }
5628 if (k==j) {
5629 break;
5630 }
5631 if (is_LOAD(&phdr[j])) {
5632 unsigned const t = get_te64(&phdr[j].p_offset);
5633 if ((t - hi) < (lo - hi)) {
5634 lo = t;
5635 if (hi==lo) {
5636 break;
5637 }
5638 }
5639 }
5640 }
5641 return lo - hi;
5642}
5643
5644int PackLinuxElf64::pack2_shlib(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft, unsigned pre_xct_top)
5645{
5646 // prepare to alter Phdrs and Shdrs
5647 lowmem.alloc(up8(xct_off + (!is_asl
5648 ? 0
5649 : e_shnum * sizeof(Elf64_Shdr))));
5650 memcpy(lowmem, file_image, xct_off); // android omits Shdr from copy now
5651
5652 MemBuffer elf_buf;
5653 elf_buf.allocForCompression(sz_elf_hdrs);
5654 unsigned u_len = sz_elf_hdrs;
5655 unsigned c_len = pack2_shlib_overlay_compress(elf_buf, lowmem, u_len);
5656
5657 int n_ptload = 0;
5658 Elf64_Phdr *phdr = &phdri[0];
5659 for (unsigned k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++phdr, ++k)
5660 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
5661 unsigned p_offset = get_te64_32(&phdr->p_offset);
5662 unsigned p_filesz = get_te64_32(&phdr->p_filesz);
5663 if (!n_ptload) { // first PT_LOAD
5664 if (is_asl) { // Copy up to xct_off, then add 2nd copy of Shdrs
5665 asl_pack2_Shdrs(fo, pre_xct_top);
5666 }
5667 else {
5668 fi->seek(p_offset, SEEK_SET);
5669 fi->read(ibuf, sz_elf_hdrs); total_in += sz_elf_hdrs;
5670 fo->write(ibuf, sz_elf_hdrs); total_out += sz_elf_hdrs;
5671 fo->seek(sz_phdrx, SEEK_CUR); total_out += sz_phdrx; // leave space
5672
5673 // Compare PackUnix::packExtent, especially "if (u_len)" .
5674 //
5675
5676 unsigned const hi_offset = umin(xct_off, (unsigned)(p_filesz + p_offset));
5677 if (sz_elf_hdrs < hi_offset) {
5678 // Loader tables in first PT_LOAD, and below xct_off.
5679 //
5680 fi->read(ibuf, hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs); total_in += hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs;
5681 fo->write(ibuf, hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs); total_out += hi_offset - sz_elf_hdrs;
5682 Elf64_Phdr *lo_phdr = k + (Elf64_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf64_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5683 set_te32(&lo_phdr->p_flags, Elf64_Phdr::PF_X | get_te32(&lo_phdr->p_flags));
5684 }
5685 }
5686 pack2_shlib_overlay_init(fo); // set overlay_offset
5687 // Compressed ELF headers go first.
5688 pack2_shlib_overlay_write(fo, elf_buf, u_len, c_len);
5689
5690 // The (compressible) remainder above xct_off in first PT_LOAD
5691 if ( p_filesz >= (xct_off - p_offset)) {
5692 Extent x;
5693 x.size = p_filesz - (xct_off - p_offset);
5694 x.offset = xct_off;
5695 packExtent(x, &ft, fo, 0, 0, true);
5696 }
5697 } // end first PT_LOAD
5698 else if ((p_filesz + p_offset) <= xct_off) {
5699 // Not first PT_LOAD, but below xct_offset. Thus "interloper" PT_LOAD,
5700 // below xct_off that was increased to a PT_LOAD large enough to compress.
5701 // "Manually" compress it, do not use PackExtent.
5702 fi->seek(p_offset, SEEK_SET);
5703 fi->read(ibuf, p_filesz); total_in += p_filesz;
5704 MemBuffer buf2; buf2.allocForCompression(p_filesz);
5705 c_len = pack2_shlib_overlay_compress(buf2, ibuf, p_filesz);
5706 pack2_shlib_overlay_write(fo, buf2, p_filesz, c_len);
5707 Elf64_Phdr *lo_phdr = k + (Elf64_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf64_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5708 set_te32(&lo_phdr->p_type, Elf64_Phdr::PT_NULL);
5709 }
5710 else if ((xct_off - p_offset) < p_filesz) {
5711 unsigned const len = xct_off - p_offset;
5712 // Loader tables in non-first PT_LOAD. (xct_off was increased.)
5713 // Bytes below xct_off belong to rtld, so cannot be compressed.
5714 // Note that asl_pack2_Shdrs() copies up to xct_off, then adds extra info.
5715 // Copy up to xct_off
5716 // FIXME: fo->write(&file_image[x.offset], x.size);
5717 if (len) {
5718 fi->read(ibuf, len); total_in += len;
5719 fo->write(ibuf, len); total_out += len;
5720
5721 // Compressed ELF headers FIXME: 1st PT_LOAD also did this!
5722 pack2_shlib_overlay_write(fo, elf_buf, u_len, c_len); // set overlay_offset
5723 }
5724 // The rest, above xct_off.
5725 Extent x;
5726 x.offset = xct_off;
5727 x.size = p_filesz - len;
5728 packExtent(x, &ft, fo, 0, 0, true);
5729 Elf64_Phdr *lo_phdr = k + (Elf64_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf64_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5730 set_te32(&lo_phdr->p_type, Elf64_Phdr::PT_NULL);
5731 }
5732 else { // definitely compressible unless writeable
5733 if (!(Elf64_Phdr::PF_W & get_te32(&phdr->p_flags))) {
5734 // Read-only PT_LOAD, assume not written by relocations.
5735 // Also assume not the source for R_*_COPY relocation,
5736 // therefore compress it.
5737 Extent x;
5738 x.offset = p_offset;
5739 x.size = p_filesz;
5740 packExtent(x, &ft, fo, 0, 0, true); // choose filter and method, then do it
5741 // De-compressing will re-create it, but otherwise ignore it.
5742 Elf64_Phdr *phdro = (Elf64_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf64_Ehdr *)&lowmem[0]);
5743 set_te32(&phdro[k].p_type, Elf32_Phdr::PT_NULL);
5744 }
5745 else {
5746 // Read-write PT_LOAD.
5747 // rtld might relocate, so we cannot compress.
5748 // (Could compress if not relocated; complicates run-time.)
5749 // Postpone writing until "slide", but account for its size.
5750 total_in += p_filesz;
5751 }
5752 }
5753 ++n_ptload;
5754 }
5755 return 0; // FIXME
5756}

5758int PackLinuxElf64::pack2(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft)
5759{
5760 Extent x;
5761 unsigned k;
5762 is_asl = (!!opt->o_unix.android_shlib) << 1; // bit 1; see is_shlib
5763 unsigned const is_shlib = (0!=xct_off) | is_asl;
5764 unsigned pre_xct_top = 0; // offset of end of PT_LOAD _before_ xct_off
5765
5766 if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_ARM==get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine)) {
5767 sec_arm_attr = elf_find_section_type(Elf64_Shdr::SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES);
5768 }
5769 // count passes, set ptload vars
5770 uip->ui_total_passes = 0;
5771 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k) {
5772 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[k])) {
5773 if (!is_shlib) {
5774 uip->ui_total_passes++;
5775 }
5776 else {
5777 unsigned p_flags = get_te32(&phdri[k].p_flags);
5778 unsigned p_offset = get_te64_32(&phdri[k].p_offset);
5779 unsigned p_filesz = get_te64_32(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
5780 if ((xct_off - p_offset) < p_filesz) { // PT_LOAD covers xct_off
5781 if (!pre_xct_top && xct_off != p_offset) {
5782 pre_xct_top = xct_off;
5783 }
5784 }
5785 else if (p_offset < xct_off) { // candidate for pre_xct_top
5786 unsigned top = p_filesz + p_offset;
5787 if (pre_xct_top < top) {
5788 pre_xct_top = top;
5789 }
5790 }
5791 if (Elf64_Phdr::PF_W & p_flags) {
5792 // rtld might write, so cannot compress
5793 }
5794 else {
5795 // First PT_LOAD (partial) only if has instructions
5796 if (k || xct_off < p_filesz) {
5797 uip->ui_total_passes++;
5798 }
5799 }
5800 }
5801 if (find_LOAD_gap(phdri, k, e_phnum)) {
5802 uip->ui_total_passes++;
5803 }
5804 }
5805 }
5806
5807 // compress extents
5808 unsigned hdr_u_len = sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + sz_phdrs;
5809
5810 total_in = 0;
5811 total_out = 0;
5812 uip->ui_pass = 0;
5813 ft.addvalue = 0;
5814
5815 unsigned nk_f = 0; upx_uint32_t xsz_f = 0;
5816 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k)
5817 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[k])
5818 && Elf32_Phdr::PF_X & get_te32(&phdri[k].p_flags)) {
5819 unsigned xsz = get_te64_32(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
5820 if (xsz_f < xsz) {
5821 xsz_f = xsz;
5822 nk_f = k;
5823 }
5824 }
5825 if (is_shlib) {
5826 pack2_shlib(fo, ft, pre_xct_top);
5827 }
5828 else { // main program
5829 int n_ptload = 0;
5830 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k)
5831 if (is_LOAD(&phdri[k])) {
5832 if (ft.id < 0x40) {
5833 // FIXME: ?? ft.addvalue = phdri[k].p_vaddr;
5834 }
5835 unsigned p_offset = get_te64_32(&phdri[k].p_offset);
5836 unsigned p_filesz = get_te64_32(&phdri[k].p_filesz);
5837 x.offset = p_offset;
5838 x.size = p_filesz;
5839 if ((u32_t)x.size < hdr_u_len) { // FIXME: main program, but how?
5840 total_in += x.size;
5841 }
5842 else { // main program, not shared library
5843 if (0 == n_ptload) { // 1st PT_LOAD must cover Ehdr at 0==p_offset
5844 unsigned const delta = hdr_u_len;
5845 if (ft.id < 0x40) {
5846 // FIXME: ?? ft.addvalue += asl_delta;
5847 }
5848 if ((off_t)delta == x.size) { // PT_LOAD[0] with ElfXX.Ehdr only
5849 // QBE backend - http://c9x.me/compile/
5850 hdr_u_len = 0; // no fiddling necessary!
5851 // &ft arg to packExtent will be zero because (k != nk_f)
5852 }
5853 else {
5854 total_in += delta - hdr_u_len;
5855 x.offset += delta;
5856 x.size -= delta;
5857 }
5858 }
5859 // compressWithFilters() always assumes a "loader", so would
5860 // throw NotCompressible for small .data Extents, which PowerPC
5861 // sometimes marks as PF_X anyway. So filter only first segment.
5862 packExtent(x,
5863 (k==nk_f ? &ft : nullptr ), fo, hdr_u_len, 0, true);
5864 hdr_u_len = 0;
5865 }
5866 ++n_ptload;
5867 }
5868 }
5869 sz_pack2a = fpad4(fo, total_out); // MATCH01
5870 total_out = up4(total_out);
5871
5872 // Accounting only; ::pack3 will do the compression and output
5873 for (k = 0; k < e_phnum; ++k) {
5874 total_in += find_LOAD_gap(phdri, k, e_phnum);
5875 }
5876
5877 if (total_in != (u32_t)file_size)
5878 throwEOFException();
5879
5880 return 0; // omit end-of-compression bhdr for now
5881}

5920// October 2011: QNX 6.3.0 has no unique signature?
5921int PackLinuxElf32::ARM_is_QNX(void)
5922{
5923 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM==get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine)
5924 && Elf32_Ehdr::ELFDATA2MSB== ehdri.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_DATA]
5925 && Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_ARM==ehdri.e_ident[Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI]
5926 && 0x100000==(page_mask & get_te32(&phdri[0].p_vaddr))) {
5927 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr = phdri;
5928 for (int j = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum); --j>=0; ++phdr) {
5929 if (Elf32_Phdr::PT_INTERP==get_te32(&phdr->p_type)) {
5930 char interp[64];
5931 unsigned const sz_interp = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
5932 unsigned const pos_interp = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
5933 if (sz_interp <= sizeof(interp)
5934 && (sz_interp + pos_interp) <= (unsigned)file_size) {
5935 fi->seek(pos_interp, SEEK_SET);
5936 fi->readx(interp, sz_interp);
5937 for (int k = sz_interp - 5; k>=0; --k) {
5938 if (0==memcmp("ldqnx", &interp[k], 5))
5939 return 1;
5940 }
5941 }
5942 }
5943 }
5944 }
5945 return 0;
5946}

5950 PackLinuxElf32::defineSymbols(ft);
5951
5952#define MAP_PRIVATE 2 /* UNIX standard */
5953#define MAP_FIXED 0x10 /* UNIX standard */
5954#define MAP_ANONYMOUS 0x20 /* UNIX standard */
5955#define MAP_PRIVANON 3 /* QNX anonymous private memory */
5956 unsigned mflg = MAP_PRIVATE | MAP_ANONYMOUS;
5957 if (ARM_is_QNX())
5958 mflg = MAP_PRIVANON;
5959 linker->defineSymbol("MFLG", mflg);
5960}
