5995
5996// ::forward_Shdrs adds info for the benefit of gdb and Android dlopen().
5997// De-compression (runtime and offline) ignores the added information
5998// because it uses the de-compressed Ehdr etc.
5999// All the added space is redundant; libbfd should take a hint:
6000// if no Shdrs, then use PT_DYNAMIC instead.
6001// (.ARM_attributes (ARM_ATTRIBUTES) is not redundant.)
6002//
6003// want_types_mask: SHT_PROGBITS is needed else gdb complains:
6004// /build/gdb-MVZsgD/gdb-10.1/gdb/symfile.c:878: internal-error: sect_index_text not initialized
6005// and Continuing is not reasonable.
6006// However, SHT_PROGBITS with compression gives:
6007// BFD: warning: ./libmain.so.upx has a section extending past end of file
6008// BFD: warning: ./libmain.so.upx has a section extending past end of file
6009// BFD: warning: ./libmain.so.upx has a section extending past end of file
6010// warning: Loadable section ".text" outside of ELF segments
6011// warning: Loadable section ".plt" outside of ELF segments
6012// because compression gives smaller extents, with no reasonable _Shdr fields.
6013// At least gdb can continue.
6014
6015unsigned PackLinuxElf32::forward_Shdrs(OutputFile *fo, Elf32_Ehdr *const eho)
6016{
6017 if (!fo) {
6018 return 0;
6019 }
6020 unsigned penalty = total_out;
6021 if (saved_opt_android_shlib) { // Forward select _Shdr
6022 // Keep _Shdr for rtld data (below xct_off).
6023 // Discard _Shdr for compressed regions, except ".text" for gdb.
6024 // Keep _Shdr for SHF_WRITE.
6025 // Discard _Shdr with (0==sh_addr), except _Shdr[0]
6026 // Keep ARM_ATTRIBUTES
6027 unsigned const want_types_mask = 0
6028 | 1u<<SHT_PROGBITS // see comment above, and special code below
6029 | 1u<<SHT_HASH
6030 | 1u<<SHT_DYNAMIC
6031 | 1u<<SHT_NOTE
6032 | 1u<<SHT_REL
6033 | 1u<<SHT_RELA
6034 | 1u<<SHT_RELR
6035 | 1u<<SHT_DYNSYM // but not SHT_SYMTAB because compression confuses gdb
6036 | 1u<<SHT_STRTAB // .shstrtab and DYNSYM.sh_link; not SYMTAB.sh_link
6037 | 1u<<SHT_INIT_ARRAY
6038 | 1u<<SHT_FINI_ARRAY
6039 | 1u<<SHT_PREINIT_ARRAY
6040 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_versym)
6041 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_verneed)
6042 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_verdef)
6043 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_HASH);
6044
6045 u32_t xct_off_hi = 0;
6046 Elf32_Phdr *ptr = phdri, *ptr_end = &phdri[e_phnum];
6047 for (; ptr < ptr_end; ++ptr) {
6048 if (is_LOAD(ptr)) {
6049 u32_t hi = get_te32(&ptr->p_filesz)
6050 + get_te32(&ptr->p_offset);
6051 if (xct_off < hi) {
6052 xct_off_hi = hi;
6053 break;
6054 }
6055 }
6056 }
6057
6058 MemBuffer mb_ask_for(e_shnum * sizeof(eho->e_shnum));
6059 memset(mb_ask_for, 0, mb_ask_for.getSize());
6060 unsigned short *const ask_for = (unsigned short *)mb_ask_for.getVoidPtr();
6061
6062 MemBuffer mb_shdro(e_shnum * sizeof(*shdri));
6063 Elf32_Shdr *sh_out0 = (Elf32_Shdr *)mb_shdro.getVoidPtr();
6064 Elf32_Shdr *sh_out = sh_out0;
6065 Elf32_Shdr *sh_in = shdri;
6066 Elf32_Shdr *n_shstrsec = nullptr;
6067
6068 // Some binutils does tail merging on section names; we don't.
6069 // ".plt" == (4+ ".rel.plt"); ".hash" == (4+ ".gnu.hash")
6070 MemBuffer mb_shstrings(100 + 2*get_te32(&sh_in[e_shstrndx].sh_size));
6071 char *ptr_shstrings = (char *)&mb_shstrings[0];
6072 *ptr_shstrings++ = '\0';
6073
6074 memset(sh_out, 0, sizeof(*sh_out)); // blank sh_out[0]
6075 ++sh_in; ++sh_out; unsigned n_sh_out = 1;
6076
6077 for (unsigned j = 1; j < e_shnum; ++j, ++sh_in) {
6078 unsigned sh_type = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_type);
6079 unsigned sh_info = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_info);
6080 unsigned sh_flags = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_flags);
6081 //unsigned sh_addr = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_addr);
6082 unsigned sh_offset = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_offset);
6083 unsigned sh_size = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_size);
6084 unsigned sh_name = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_name);
6085 char const *name = &shstrtab[sh_name];
6086 if (ask_for[j]) { // Some previous _Shdr requested me
6087 // Tell them my new index
6088 set_te32(&sh_out0[ask_for[j]].sh_info, n_sh_out); // sh_info vs st_shndx
6089 }
6090 if (sh_info < e_shnum) { // wild sh_info abounds!
6091 ask_for[sh_info] = j; // Enter my request, if any
6092 }
6093 if ( (sh_offset && sh_offset < xct_off)
6094 || (Elf32_Shdr::SHF_WRITE & sh_flags)
6095 || (j == e_shstrndx)
6096 || (sec_arm_attr == sh_in)
6097 || (want_types_mask & (1<<(0x1f & sh_type)))
6098 ) {
6099 *sh_out = *sh_in; // *sh_in is a candidate for fowarding
6100 if (sh_offset > xct_off) { // may slide down: earlier compression
6101 if (sh_offset >= xct_off_hi) { // easy: so_slide down
6102 if (sh_out->sh_addr) // change only if non-zero
6103 //set_te32(&sh_out->sh_addr, so_slide + sh_addr);
6104 set_te32(&sh_out->sh_offset, so_slide + sh_offset);
6105 }
6106 else { // somewhere in compressed; try proportional (aligned)
6107 // But note that PROGBITS without SHF_ALLOC
6108 // will be dropped below.
6109 u32_t const slice = xct_off + (~0xFu & (unsigned)(
6110 (sh_offset - xct_off) *
6111 ((sh_offset - xct_off) / (float)(xct_off_hi - xct_off))));
6112 //set_te32(&sh_out->sh_addr, slice);
6113 set_te32(&sh_out->sh_offset, slice);
6114 }
6115 u32_t const max_sz = total_out - get_te32(&sh_out->sh_offset);
6116 if (sh_size > max_sz) { // avoid complaint "extends beyond EOF"
6117 set_te32(&sh_out->sh_size, max_sz);
6118 }
6119 }
6120 if (j == e_shstrndx) { // changes Elf32_Ehdr itself
6121 set_te16(&eho->e_shstrndx, sh_out -
6122 (Elf32_Shdr *)mb_shdro.getVoidPtr());
6123 }
6124 if (sec_arm_attr == sh_in
6125 || (SHT_NOTE == sh_type && xct_off < sh_offset)
6126 ) { // append a copy
6127 set_te32(&sh_out->sh_offset, total_out);
6128 fi->seek((upx_off_t)sh_offset, SEEK_SET);
6129 fi->read(ibuf, sh_size);
6130 fo->write(ibuf, sh_size);
6131 total_out += sh_size;
6132 } else
6133 if (SHT_PROGBITS == sh_type) {
6134 if (!(Elf32_Shdr::SHF_ALLOC & sh_flags)) {
6135 // .debug_*, .gnu_debuglink etc. Typically compressed
6136 // but not in RAM, and gdb (BFD) gets confused.
6137 continue; // OMIT the commit: do not forward
6138 } else
6139 if (sh_offset <= xct_off
6140 && 0 == strcmp(".text", name) ) {
6141 // .text was compressed (but perhaps omitting some leading
6142 // portion, if less than 4 PT_LOAD)
6143 set_te32(&sh_out->sh_size, so_slide + sh_size);
6144 // FIXME: so_slide is negative; avoid negative result
6145 }
6146 } else
6147 if (SHT_STRTAB == sh_type) {
6148 if (j == e_shstrndx) {
6149 n_shstrsec = sh_out;
6150 } else
6151 if (strcmp(".dynstr", name)) {
6152 continue; // OMIT the commit of non-global symbol names
6153 }
6154 }
6155 set_te32(&sh_out->sh_name, ptr_shstrings - (char *)mb_shstrings.getVoidPtr());
6156 do { // stupid MSVC lacks stpcpy()
6157 *ptr_shstrings++ = *name;
6158 } while (*name++);
6159 ++sh_out; ++n_sh_out; // actually commit the fowarding
6160 }
6161 }
6162 unsigned len = ptr_shstrings - (char *)mb_shstrings.getVoidPtr();
6163 set_te32(&n_shstrsec->sh_offset, total_out);
6164 set_te32(&n_shstrsec->sh_size, len);
6165 fo->write(mb_shstrings, len);
6166 total_out += len;
6167
6168 total_out = fpad4(fo, total_out); // align _Shdr[]
6169 set_te32(&eho->e_shoff, total_out);
6170 len = (char *)sh_out - (char *)mb_shdro.getVoidPtr();
6171 set_te16(&eho->e_shnum, len / sizeof(*sh_out));
6172 set_te16(&eho->e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf32_Shdr));
6173 fo->write(mb_shdro, len);
6174 total_out += len;
6175
6176 // Try to pacify gdb (before DT_INIT) by making it look like
6177 // the compressed PT_LOAD extends all the way to the next PT_LOAD,
6178 // with no gap in address space. Thus gdb should not complain about
6179 // "Loadable section "..." [Shdr] outside of ELF segments [PT_LOAD]".
6180 // gdb still "warning: section ... not found in .gnu_debugdata"
6181 // because .gdb_debugdata is not present (or gets removed),
6182 // but that is separate and "just" a warning.
6183 ptr = (Elf32_Phdr *)(1+ eho);
6184 for (ptr_end = &ptr[e_phnum]; ptr < ptr_end; ++ptr) {
6185 if (is_LOAD(ptr)) {
6186 Elf32_Phdr *ptr2 = 1+ ptr;
6187 for (; ptr2 < ptr_end; ++ptr2) {
6188 if (is_LOAD(ptr2)) {
6189 unsigned pmask = 0u - get_te32(&ptr2->p_align);
6190 set_te32(&ptr->p_memsz,
6191 (pmask & get_te32(&ptr2->p_vaddr)) -
6192 (pmask & get_te32(&ptr ->p_vaddr)) );
6193 ptr = ptr_end; // force end of outer loop
6194 ptr2 = ptr_end; // force end of inner loop
6195 }
6196 }
6197 }
6198 }
6199
6200 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6201 fo->rewrite(eho, sizeof(*eho));
6202 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
6203 }
6204 else if (sec_arm_attr) {
6205 // Forward just ARM_ATTRIBUTES
6206 Elf32_Shdr shdr_aa[3];
6207 unsigned const attr_len = get_te32(&sec_arm_attr->sh_size);
6208 char const str_aa[] = "\x00" ".shstrtab\x00" ".ARM.attributes\x00";
6209
6210 memset(shdr_aa, 0, sizeof shdr_aa);
6211 // shstrtab
6212 set_te32(&shdr_aa[1].sh_name, 1);
6213 set_te32(&shdr_aa[1].sh_type, Elf32_Shdr::SHT_STRTAB);
6214 set_te32(&shdr_aa[1].sh_offset, total_out);
6215 set_te32(&shdr_aa[1].sh_size, sizeof(str_aa));
6216 set_te32(&shdr_aa[1].sh_addralign, 1);
6217 fo->write(str_aa, sizeof(str_aa)); total_out += sizeof(str_aa);
6218
6219 // ARM_ATTRIBUTES
6220 set_te32(&shdr_aa[2].sh_name, 11);
6221 set_te32(&shdr_aa[2].sh_type, Elf32_Shdr::SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES);
6222 set_te32(&shdr_aa[2].sh_offset, total_out);
6223 set_te32(&shdr_aa[2].sh_size, attr_len);
6224 set_te32(&shdr_aa[2].sh_addralign, 1);
6225 fo->write(&file_image[get_te32(&sec_arm_attr->sh_offset)], attr_len);
6226 total_out = fpad4(fo, total_out += attr_len);
6227
6228 set_te16(&eho->e_shnum, 3);
6229 set_te16(&eho->e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf32_Shdr));
6230 set_te32(&eho->e_shoff, total_out);
6231 set_te16(&eho->e_shstrndx, 1);
6232 fo->write(shdr_aa, sizeof(shdr_aa));
6233 total_out += sizeof(shdr_aa);
6234
6235 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6236 fo->rewrite(eho, sizeof(*eho));
6237 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
6238 }
6239 penalty = total_out - penalty;
6240 info("Android penalty = %d bytes", penalty);
6241 return penalty;
6242}
6243
6244unsigned PackLinuxElf64::forward_Shdrs(OutputFile *fo, Elf64_Ehdr *const eho)
6245{
6246 if (!fo) {
6247 return 0;
6248 }
6249 unsigned penalty = total_out;
6250 if (saved_opt_android_shlib) { // Forward select _Shdr
6251 // Keep _Shdr for rtld data (below xct_off).
6252 // Discard _Shdr for compressed regions, except ".text" for gdb.
6253 // Keep _Shdr for SHF_WRITE.
6254 // Discard _Shdr with (0==sh_addr), except _Shdr[0]
6255 // Keep ARM_ATTRIBUTES
6256 unsigned const want_types_mask =
6257 1u<<SHT_SYMTAB
6258 | 1u<<SHT_RELA
6259 | 1u<<SHT_PROGBITS // see comment above
6260 | 1u<<SHT_HASH
6261 | 1u<<SHT_DYNAMIC
6262 | 1u<<SHT_NOTE
6263 | 1u<<SHT_REL
6264 | 1u<<SHT_RELR
6265 | 1u<<SHT_DYNSYM
6266 | 1u<<SHT_STRTAB // .shstrtab and .dynstr
6267 | 1u<<SHT_INIT_ARRAY
6268 | 1u<<SHT_FINI_ARRAY
6269 | 1u<<SHT_PREINIT_ARRAY
6270 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_versym)
6271 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_verneed)
6272 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_verdef)
6273 | 1u<<(0x1f & SHT_GNU_HASH);
6274
6275 upx_uint64_t xct_off_hi = 0;
6276 Elf64_Phdr const *ptr = phdri, *ptr_end = &phdri[e_phnum];
6277 for (; ptr < ptr_end; ++ptr) {
6278 if (is_LOAD(ptr)) {
6279 upx_uint64_t hi = get_te64(&ptr->p_filesz)
6280 + get_te64(&ptr->p_offset);
6281 if (xct_off < hi) {
6282 xct_off_hi = hi;
6283 break;
6284 }
6285 }
6286 }
6287
6288 MemBuffer mb_ask_for(e_shnum * sizeof(eho->e_shnum));
6289 memset(mb_ask_for, 0, mb_ask_for.getSize());
6290 unsigned short *const ask_for = (unsigned short *)mb_ask_for.getVoidPtr();
6291
6292 MemBuffer mb_shdro(e_shnum * sizeof(*shdri));
6293 Elf64_Shdr *sh_out0 = (Elf64_Shdr *)mb_shdro.getVoidPtr();
6294 Elf64_Shdr *sh_out = sh_out0;
6295 Elf64_Shdr *sh_in = shdri;
6296
6297 memset(sh_out, 0, sizeof(*sh_out)); // blank sh_out[0]
6298 ++sh_in; ++sh_out; unsigned n_sh_out = 1;
6299
6300 for (unsigned j = 1; j < e_shnum; ++j, ++sh_in) {
6301 char const *sh_name = &shstrtab[get_te32(&sh_in->sh_name)];
6302 (void)sh_name; // debugging
6303 unsigned sh_type = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_type);
6304 unsigned sh_info = get_te32(&sh_in->sh_info);
6305 u64_t sh_flags = get_te64(&sh_in->sh_flags);
6306 u64_t sh_addr = get_te64(&sh_in->sh_addr);
6307 u64_t sh_offset = get_te64(&sh_in->sh_offset);
6308 u64_t sh_size = get_te64(&sh_in->sh_size);
6309 if (ask_for[j]) { // Some previous _Shdr requested me
6310 // Tell them my new index
6311 set_te32(&sh_out0[ask_for[j]].sh_info, n_sh_out); // sh_info vs st_shndx
6312 }
6313 if (sh_info < e_shnum) { // wild sh_info abounds!
6314 ask_for[sh_info] = j; // Enter my request, if any
6315 }
6316 if ( (sh_offset && sh_offset < xct_off)
6317 || (Elf64_Shdr::SHF_WRITE & sh_flags)
6318 || (j == e_shstrndx)
6319 || (sec_arm_attr == sh_in)
6320 || (want_types_mask & (1<<(0x1f & sh_type)))
6321 ) {
6322 *sh_out = *sh_in;
6323 if (sh_offset > xct_off) { // may slide down: earlier compression
6324 if (sh_offset >= xct_off_hi) { // easy: so_slide down
6325 if (sh_out->sh_addr) // change only if non-zero
6326 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, so_slide + sh_addr);
6327 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_offset, so_slide + sh_offset);
6328 }
6329 else { // somewhere in compressed; try proportional (aligned)
6330 u64_t const slice = xct_off + (~0xFu & (unsigned)(
6331 (sh_offset - xct_off) *
6332 ((sh_offset - xct_off) / (float)(xct_off_hi - xct_off))));
6333 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, slice);
6334 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_offset, slice);
6335 }
6336 u64_t const max_sz = total_out - get_te64(&sh_out->sh_offset);
6337 if (sh_size > max_sz) { // avoid complaint "extends beyond EOF"
6338 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_size, max_sz);
6339 }
6340 }
6341 if (j == e_shstrndx) { // changes Elf64_Ehdr itself
6342 set_te16(&eho->e_shstrndx, sh_out -
6343 (Elf64_Shdr *)mb_shdro.getVoidPtr());
6344 }
6345 if (j == e_shstrndx
6346 || sec_arm_attr == sh_in
6347 || (SHT_NOTE == sh_type && xct_off < sh_offset)
6348 ) { // append a copy
6349 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_offset, total_out);
6350 fi->seek((upx_off_t)sh_offset, SEEK_SET);
6351 fi->read(ibuf, sh_size);
6352 fo->write(ibuf, sh_size);
6353 total_out += sh_size;
6354 } else
6355 if (SHT_PROGBITS == sh_type) {
6356 if (sh_offset <= xct_off
6357 && 0 == strcmp(".text", shstrtab + get_te32(&sh_in->sh_name)) ) {
6358 // .text was compressed (but perhaps omitting some leading
6359 // portion, if less than 4 PT_LOAD)
6360 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_size, so_slide + sh_size);
6361 } else
6362 if (0 == sh_in->sh_addr) { // .gnu_debuglink etc
6363 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_offset, so_slide + sh_offset);
6364 }
6365 }
6366 // Exploration for updating Shdrs from Dynamic, to pacify Android.
6367 // Motivated by --force-pie with an input shared library;
6368 // see https://github.com/upx/upx/issues/694
6369 // But then realized that the pointed-to regions typically were
6370 // just above Elfhdrs (overlay_offset), so the data would be
6371 // incorrect because occupied by compressed PT_LOADS.
6372 // But don't lose the code, so comment-out via "if (0)".
6373 if (0) switch(sh_type) { // start {Shdr, Dynamic} pairs
6374 case SHT_DYNSYM: {
6375 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB));
6376 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6377 } break;
6378 case SHT_STRTAB: {
6379 if (e_shstrndx != j) {
6380 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB));
6381 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6382 }
6383 } break;
6384 case SHT_GNU_versym: {
6385 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERSYM));
6386 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6387 } break;
6388 case SHT_GNU_verneed: {
6389 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_VERNEED));
6390 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6391 } break;
6392 case SHT_GNU_HASH: {
6393 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH));
6394 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6395 } break;
6396 case SHT_HASH: {
6397 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_HASH));
6398 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6399 } break;
6400 case SHT_RELA: {
6401 if (0==strcmp(".rela.dyn", sh_name)) {
6402 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELA));
6403 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6404 }
6405 if (0==strcmp(".rela.plt", sh_name)) {
6406 set_te64(&sh_out->sh_addr, elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_JMPREL));
6407 sh_out->sh_offset = sh_out->sh_addr;
6408 }
6409 } break;
6410 } // end {Shdr, Dynamic} pairs
6411 ++sh_out; ++n_sh_out;
6412 }
6413 }
6414 total_out = fpad8(fo, total_out);
6415 set_te64(&eho->e_shoff, total_out);
6416 unsigned len = (char *)sh_out - (char *)mb_shdro.getVoidPtr();
6417 set_te16(&eho->e_shnum, len / sizeof(*sh_out));
6418 set_te16(&eho->e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
6419 fo->write(mb_shdro, len);
6420 total_out += len;
6421 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6422 fo->rewrite(eho, sizeof(*eho));
6423 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
6424 }
6425 else if (sec_arm_attr) {
6426 // Forward just ARM_ATTRIBUTES
6427 Elf64_Shdr shdr_aa[3];
6428 u64_t const attr_len = get_te64(&sec_arm_attr->sh_size);
6429 char const str_aa[] = "\x00" ".shstrtab\x00" ".ARM.attributes\x00";
6430
6431 memset(shdr_aa, 0, sizeof shdr_aa);
6432 // shstrtab
6433 set_te32(&shdr_aa[1].sh_name, 1);
6434 set_te32(&shdr_aa[1].sh_type, Elf64_Shdr::SHT_STRTAB);
6435 set_te64(&shdr_aa[1].sh_offset, total_out);
6436 set_te64(&shdr_aa[1].sh_size, sizeof(str_aa));
6437 set_te64(&shdr_aa[1].sh_addralign, 1);
6438 fo->write(str_aa, sizeof(str_aa)); total_out += sizeof(str_aa);
6439
6440 // ARM_ATTRIBUTES
6441 set_te32(&shdr_aa[2].sh_name, 11);
6442 set_te32(&shdr_aa[2].sh_type, Elf64_Shdr::SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES);
6443 set_te64(&shdr_aa[2].sh_offset, total_out);
6444 set_te64(&shdr_aa[2].sh_size, attr_len);
6445 set_te64(&shdr_aa[2].sh_addralign, 1);
6446 fo->write(&file_image[get_te64(&sec_arm_attr->sh_offset)], attr_len);
6447 total_out = fpad8(fo, total_out += attr_len);
6448
6449 set_te16(&eho->e_shnum, 3);
6450 set_te16(&eho->e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf64_Shdr));
6451 set_te64(&eho->e_shoff, total_out);
6452 set_te16(&eho->e_shstrndx, 1);
6453 fo->write(shdr_aa, sizeof(shdr_aa));
6454 total_out += sizeof(shdr_aa);
6455
6456 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6457 fo->rewrite(eho, sizeof(*eho));
6458 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
6459 }
6460 penalty = total_out - penalty;
6461 info("Android penalty = %d bytes", penalty);
6462 return penalty;
6463}
6464
6465void PackLinuxElf32::pack4(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft)
6466{
6467 if (!xct_off) {
6468 overlay_offset = sz_elf_hdrs + sizeof(linfo);
6469 }
6470
6471 cprElfHdr4 *eho = !xct_off
6472 ? (cprElfHdr4 *)(void *)&elfout // not shlib FIXME: ugly casting
6473 : (cprElfHdr4 *)lowmem.getVoidPtr(); // shlib
6474 unsigned penalty = forward_Shdrs(fo, &eho->ehdr); (void)penalty;
6475
6476 if (opt->o_unix.preserve_build_id) { // FIXME: co-ordinate with forward_Shdrs
6477 // calc e_shoff here and write shdrout, then o_shstrtab
6478 //NOTE: these are pushed last to ensure nothing is stepped on
6479 //for the UPX structure.
6480 total_out = fpad4(fo, total_out);
6481 set_te32(&eho->ehdr.e_shoff, total_out);
6482
6483 unsigned const ssize = sizeof(shdrout);
6484 unsigned const ssize1 = get_te32(&shdrout.shdr[1].sh_size);
6485 unsigned const ssize2 = get_te32(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_size);
6486
6487 set_te32(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_offset, ssize + total_out);
6488 set_te32(&shdrout.shdr[1].sh_offset, ssize2 + ssize + total_out);
6489
6490 fo->write(&shdrout, ssize); total_out += ssize;
6491
6492 fo->write(o_shstrtab, ssize2); total_out += ssize2;
6493 fo->write(buildid_data, ssize1); total_out += ssize1;
6494 }
6495
6496 // ph.u_len and ph.c_len are leftover from earliest days when there was
6497 // only one compressed extent. Use a good analogy for multiple extents.
6498 ph.u_len = file_size;
6499 ph.c_len = total_out;
6500 super::pack4(fo, ft); // write PackHeader and overlay_offset
6501
6502 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6503 if (0!=xct_off) { // shared library
6504 { // Shouldn't this special case be handled earlier?
6505 if (overlay_offset < xct_off) {
6506 Elf32_Phdr *phdro = (Elf32_Phdr *)&eho->phdr;
6507 set_te32(&phdro->p_flags, Elf32_Phdr::PF_X | get_te32(&phdro->p_flags));
6508 }
6509 }
6510 if (!sec_arm_attr && !saved_opt_android_shlib) {
6511 // Make it abundantly clear that there are no Elf32_Shdr in this shlib
6512 eho->ehdr.e_shoff = 0;
6513 set_te16(&eho->ehdr.e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf32_Shdr)); // Android bug: cannot use 0
6514 eho->ehdr.e_shnum = 0;
6515 eho->ehdr.e_shstrndx = 0;
6516 }
6517 fo->rewrite(eho, sizeof(ehdri) + e_phnum * sizeof(*phdri));
6518 fo->seek(linfo_off, SEEK_SET);
6519 fo->rewrite(&linfo, sizeof(linfo)); // new info: l_checksum, l_size
6520
6521 if (jni_onload_va) {
6522 unsigned tmp = sz_pack2 + get_te32(&eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr);
6523 tmp |= (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM==e_machine); // THUMB mode
6524 set_te32(&tmp, tmp);
6525 fo->seek(ptr_udiff_bytes(&jni_onload_sym->st_value, file_image), SEEK_SET);
6526 fo->rewrite(&tmp, sizeof(tmp));
6527 }
6528 }
6529 else { // not shlib
6530 // Cannot pre-round .p_memsz. If .p_filesz < .p_memsz, then kernel
6531 // tries to make .bss, which requires PF_W.
6532 // But strict SELinux (or PaX, grSecurity) disallows PF_W with PF_X.
6533 set_te32(&eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
6534 eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_memsz = eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz;
6535
6536 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6537 fo->rewrite(&eho->ehdr, sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + 2* sizeof(Elf32_Phdr)); // C_BASE, C_TEXT
6538 fo->seek(overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info), SEEK_SET);
6539 fo->rewrite(&linfo, sizeof(linfo));
6540 }
6541}
6542
6543void PackLinuxElf64::pack4(OutputFile *fo, Filter &ft)
6544{
6545 if (!xct_off) {
6546 overlay_offset = sz_elf_hdrs + sizeof(linfo);
6547 }
6548
6549 cprElfHdr4 *eho = !xct_off
6550 ? &elfout // not shlib
6551 : (cprElfHdr4 *)lowmem.getVoidPtr(); // shlib
6552 unsigned penalty = forward_Shdrs(fo, &eho->ehdr); (void)penalty;
6553
6554 if (opt->o_unix.preserve_build_id) { // FIXME: co-ordinate with forward_Shdrs
6555 // calc e_shoff here and write shdrout, then o_shstrtab
6556 //NOTE: these are pushed last to ensure nothing is stepped on
6557 //for the UPX structure.
6558 total_out = fpad4(fo, total_out);
6559 set_te64(&eho->ehdr.e_shoff, total_out);
6560
6561 unsigned const ssize = sizeof(shdrout);
6562 unsigned const ssize1 = get_te64(&shdrout.shdr[1].sh_size);
6563 unsigned const ssize2 = get_te64(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_size);
6564
6565 set_te64(&shdrout.shdr[2].sh_offset, ssize + total_out);
6566 set_te64(&shdrout.shdr[1].sh_offset, ssize2 + ssize + total_out);
6567
6568 fo->write(&shdrout, ssize); total_out += ssize;
6569
6570 fo->write(o_shstrtab, ssize2); total_out += ssize2;
6571 fo->write(buildid_data, ssize1); total_out += ssize1;
6572 }
6573
6574 // ph.u_len and ph.c_len are leftover from earliest days when there was
6575 // only one compressed extent. Use a good analogy for multiple extents.
6576 ph.u_len = file_size;
6577 ph.c_len = total_out;
6578 super::pack4(fo, ft); // write PackHeader and overlay_offset
6579
6580 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6581 if (0!=xct_off) { // shared library
6582 { // Shouldn't this special case be handled earlier?
6583 if (overlay_offset < xct_off) {
6584 Elf64_Phdr *phdro = (Elf64_Phdr *)(&eho->phdr);
6585 set_te32(&phdro->p_flags, Elf64_Phdr::PF_X | get_te32(&phdro->p_flags));
6586 }
6587 }
6588 if (!sec_arm_attr && !saved_opt_android_shlib) {
6589 // Make it abundantly clear that there are no Elf64_Shdr in this shlib
6590 eho->ehdr.e_shoff = 0;
6591 set_te16(&eho->ehdr.e_shentsize, sizeof(Elf64_Shdr)); // Android bug: cannot use 0
6592 eho->ehdr.e_shnum = 0;
6593 eho->ehdr.e_shstrndx = 0;
6594 }
6595
6596 fo->rewrite(eho, sizeof(ehdri) + e_phnum * sizeof(*phdri));
6597 fo->seek(linfo_off, SEEK_SET);
6598 fo->rewrite(&linfo, sizeof(linfo)); // new info: l_checksum, l_size
6599
6600 if (jni_onload_va) { // FIXME Does this apply to 64-bit, too?
6601 upx_uint64_t tmp = sz_pack2 + get_te64(&eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_vaddr);
6602 tmp |= (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_ARM==e_machine); // THUMB mode; no-op for 64-bit
6603 set_te64(&tmp, tmp);
6604 fo->seek(ptr_udiff_bytes(&jni_onload_sym->st_value, file_image), SEEK_SET);
6605 fo->rewrite(&tmp, sizeof(tmp));
6606 }
6607 }
6608 else { // not shlib
6609 // Cannot pre-round .p_memsz. If .p_filesz < .p_memsz, then kernel
6610 // tries to make .bss, which requires PF_W.
6611 // But strict SELinux (or PaX, grSecurity) disallows PF_W with PF_X.
6612 set_te64(&eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz, sz_pack2 + lsize);
6613 eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_memsz = eho->phdr[C_TEXT].p_filesz;
6614
6615 fo->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6616 fo->rewrite(&eho->ehdr, sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + 2* sizeof(Elf64_Phdr)); // C_BASE, C_TEXT
6617 fo->seek(overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info), SEEK_SET);
6618 fo->rewrite(&linfo, sizeof(linfo));
6619 }
6620}
6621
6622void
6623PackLinuxElf32::unRel32(
6624 unsigned dt_rel,
6625 Elf32_Rel *rel0,
6626 unsigned relsz,
6627 MemBuffer &ptload1,
6628 unsigned const load_off,
6629 OutputFile *fo
6630)
6631{
6632 Elf32_Rel *rel = rel0;
6633 for (int k = relsz / sizeof(Elf32_Rel); --k >= 0; ++rel) {
6634 unsigned r_offset = get_te32(&rel->r_offset);
6635 unsigned r_info = get_te32(&rel->r_info);
6636 unsigned r_type = ELF32_R_TYPE(r_info);
6637 if (xct_off <= r_offset) {
6638 set_te32(&rel->r_offset, r_offset - asl_delta);
6639 }
6640 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine) {
6641 if (R_ARM_RELATIVE == r_type) {
6642 unsigned d = r_offset - load_off - asl_delta;
6643 unsigned w = get_te32(&ptload1[d]);
6644 if (xct_off <= w) {
6645 set_te32(&ptload1[d], w - asl_delta);
6646 }
6647 }
6648 if (R_ARM_JUMP_SLOT == r_type) {
6649 ++n_jmp_slot;
6650 // .rel.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
6651 unsigned d = r_offset - load_off - asl_delta;
6652 if (plt_va > d) {
6653 plt_va = d;
6654 }
6655 unsigned w = get_te32(&ptload1[d]);
6656 if (xct_off <= w) {
6657 set_te32(&ptload1[d], w - asl_delta);
6658 }
6659 }
6660 }
6661 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386 == e_machine) {
6662 if (R_386_RELATIVE == r_type) {
6663 unsigned d = r_offset - load_off - asl_delta;
6664 unsigned w = get_te32(&ptload1[d]);
6665 if (xct_off <= w) {
6666 set_te32(&ptload1[d], w - asl_delta);
6667 }
6668 }
6669 if (R_386_JMP_SLOT == r_type) {
6670 ++n_jmp_slot;
6671 // .rel.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
6672 unsigned d = r_offset - load_off - asl_delta;
6673 if (plt_va > d) {
6674 plt_va = d;
6675 }
6676 unsigned w = get_te32(&ptload1[d]);
6677 if (xct_off <= w) {
6678 set_te32(&ptload1[d], w - asl_delta);
6679 }
6680 }
6681 }
6682 }
6683 fo->seek(dt_rel, SEEK_SET);
6684 fo->rewrite(rel0, relsz);
6685}
6686
6687void
6688PackLinuxElf64::unRela64(
6689 upx_uint64_t const dt_rela,
6690 Elf64_Rela *const rela0,
6691 unsigned const relasz,
6692 upx_uint64_t const old_dtinit,
6693 OutputFile *const fo
6694)
6695{
6696 Elf64_Rela *rela = rela0;
6697 for (int k = relasz / sizeof(Elf64_Rela); --k >= 0; ++rela) {
6698 upx_uint64_t r_addend = get_te64(&rela->r_addend);
6699 if (xct_off <= r_addend) {
6700 r_addend -= asl_delta;
6701 set_te64(&rela->r_addend, r_addend);
6702 }
6703
6704 upx_uint64_t r_offset = get_te64(&rela->r_offset);
6705 if (xct_off <= r_offset) {
6706 //r_offset -= asl_delta; // keep compressed value vs plt_va
6707 set_te64(&rela->r_offset, r_offset - asl_delta); // uncompressed value
6708 }
6709
6710 // ElfXX_Rela (used only on 64-bit) ignores the contents of memory
6711 // at the target designated by r_offset. The target is completely
6712 // overwritten by (r_addend + f_reloc(r_info)).
6713 //
6714 // Nevertheless, the existing targets of .rela.plt in the .got
6715 // seem to have values that matter to somebody. So restore original
6716 // values when is_asl.
6717 upx_uint64_t r_info = get_te64(&rela->r_info);
6718 unsigned r_type = ELF64_R_TYPE(r_info);
6719 if (is_asl && Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64 == e_machine) {
6720 if (R_AARCH64_RELATIVE == r_type) {
6721#if 0 //{ FIXME
6722 if (old_dtinit == r_addend) {
6723 set_te64(&ptload1[r_offset - plt_va], r_addend);
6724 }
6725#endif //}
6726 }
6727 if (R_AARCH64_JUMP_SLOT == r_type) {
6728 ++n_jmp_slot;
6729 // .rela.plt contains offset of the "first time" target
6730 if (jump_slots.getSize() < (r_offset - plt_va)) {
6731 throwInternalError("bad r_offset for jump_slots");
6732 }
6733 // really upx_uint64_t *, but clang makes it hard to say that
6734 unsigned char *slot = r_offset - plt_va
6735 + (unsigned char *)jump_slots.getVoidPtr();
6736 upx_uint64_t w = get_te64(slot);
6737 if (xct_off <= w) {
6738 set_te64(slot, w - asl_delta);
6739 }
6740 }
6741 }
6742 // FIXME: but what about old_dtinit?
6743 (void)old_dtinit;
6744
6745 } // end each RELA
6746 if (fo) {
6747 fo->seek(dt_rela, SEEK_SET);
6748 fo->rewrite(rela0, relasz);
6749 }
6750}
6751
6752void
6753PackLinuxElf64::un_asl_dynsym( // ibuf has the input
6754 unsigned orig_file_size,
6755 OutputFile *fo // else just leave in ibuf
6756)
6757{
6758 // un-Relocate dynsym (DT_SYMTAB) which is below xct_off
6759 dynstr = (char const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
6760 sec_dynsym = elf_find_section_type(Elf64_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
6761 if (dynstr && sec_dynsym) {
6762 upx_uint64_t const off_dynsym = get_te64(&sec_dynsym->sh_offset);
6763 upx_uint64_t const sz_dynsym = get_te64(&sec_dynsym->sh_size);
6764 if (orig_file_size < sz_dynsym
6765 || orig_file_size < off_dynsym
6766 || (orig_file_size - off_dynsym) < sz_dynsym) {
6767 throwCantUnpack("bad SHT_DYNSYM");
6768 }
6769 Elf64_Sym *const sym0 = (Elf64_Sym *)ibuf.subref(
6770 "bad dynsym", off_dynsym, sz_dynsym);
6771 Elf64_Sym *sym = sym0;
6772 for (int j = sz_dynsym / sizeof(Elf64_Sym); --j>=0; ++sym) {
6773 upx_uint64_t symval = get_te64(&sym->st_value);
6774 unsigned symsec = get_te16(&sym->st_shndx);
6775 if (Elf64_Sym::SHN_UNDEF != symsec
6776 && Elf64_Sym::SHN_ABS != symsec
6777 && xct_off <= symval) {
6778 set_te64(&sym->st_value, symval - asl_delta);
6779 }
6780 if (Elf64_Sym::SHN_ABS == symsec && xct_off <= symval) {
6781 adjABS(sym, 0ul - (unsigned long)asl_delta);
6782 }
6783 }
6784 if (fo) {
6785 unsigned pos = fo->tell();
6786 fo->seek(off_dynsym, SEEK_SET);
6787 fo->rewrite(sym0, sz_dynsym);
6788 fo->seek(pos, SEEK_SET);
6789 }
6790 }
6791}
6792
6793void
6794PackLinuxElf32::un_asl_dynsym( // ibuf has the input
6795 unsigned orig_file_size,
6796 OutputFile *fo // else just leave in ibuf
6797)
6798{
6799 // un-Relocate dynsym (DT_SYMTAB) which is below xct_off
6800 dynstr = (char const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_STRTAB);
6801 sec_dynsym = elf_find_section_type(Elf32_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
6802 if (dynstr && sec_dynsym) {
6803 upx_uint32_t const off_dynsym = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_offset);
6804 upx_uint32_t const sz_dynsym = get_te32(&sec_dynsym->sh_size);
6805 if (orig_file_size < sz_dynsym
6806 || orig_file_size < off_dynsym
6807 || (orig_file_size - off_dynsym) < sz_dynsym) {
6808 throwCantUnpack("bad SHT_DYNSYM");
6809 }
6810 Elf32_Sym *const sym0 = (Elf32_Sym *)ibuf.subref(
6811 "bad dynsym", off_dynsym, sz_dynsym);
6812 Elf32_Sym *sym = sym0;
6813 for (int j = sz_dynsym / sizeof(Elf32_Sym); --j>=0; ++sym) {
6814 upx_uint32_t symval = get_te32(&sym->st_value);
6815 unsigned symsec = get_te16(&sym->st_shndx);
6816 if (Elf32_Sym::SHN_UNDEF != symsec
6817 && Elf32_Sym::SHN_ABS != symsec
6818 && xct_off <= symval) {
6819 set_te32(&sym->st_value, symval - asl_delta);
6820 }
6821 if (Elf32_Sym::SHN_ABS == symsec && xct_off <= symval) {
6822 adjABS(sym, 0u - (unsigned)asl_delta);
6823 }
6824 }
6825 if (fo) {
6826 unsigned pos = fo->tell();
6827 fo->seek(off_dynsym, SEEK_SET);
6828 fo->rewrite(sym0, sz_dynsym);
6829 fo->seek(pos, SEEK_SET);
6830 }
6831 }
6832}
6833
6834// File layout of compressed .so (new-style: 3 or 4 PT_LOAD) shared library:
6835// 1. new Elf headers: Ehdr, PT_LOAD (r-x), PT_LOAD (rw-, if any), non-PT_LOAD Phdrs
6836// 2. Space for (original - 2) PT_LOAD Phdr
6837// 3. Remaining original contents of file below xct_off
6838// xct_off: (&lowest eXecutable Shdr section; in original PT_LOAD[0] or [1])
6839// 3a. If --android-shlib, then 4KiB page of Shdr copy, etc. (asl_pack2_Shdrs)
6840// And xct_off gets incremented by 4KiB at the right time.
6841// 4. l_info (12 bytes)
6842// overlay_offset:
6843// 5. p_info (12 bytes)
6844// 6. compressed original Elf headers (prefixed by b_info as usual)
6845// 6a. un-compressed copy of input after Elf headers until xct_off.
6846// *user_init_rp has been modified if no DT_INIT
6847// 7. compressed remainder of PT_LOAD above xct_off
6848// 8. compressed read-only PT_LOAD above xct_off (if any) // FIXME: check decompressor
6849// 9. uncompressed Read-Write PT_LOAD (slide down N pages)
6850// 10. int[6] tables for UPX runtime de-compressor
6851// (new) DT_INIT:
6852// 11. UPX runtime de-compressing loader
6853// 12. compressed gaps between PT_LOADs (and EOF) above xct_off
6854// 13. 32-byte pack header
6855// 14. 4-byte overlay_offset
6856
6857void PackLinuxElf64::un_shlib_1(
6858 OutputFile *const fo,
6859 MemBuffer &o_elfhdrs,
6860 unsigned &c_adler,
6861 unsigned &u_adler,
6862 unsigned const orig_file_size
6863)
6864{
6865 // xct_off [input side] was set by ::unpack when is_shlib
6866 // yct_off [output side] set here unless is_asl in next 'if' block
6867 unsigned yct_off = xct_off;
6868
6869 // Below xct_off is not compressed (for benefit of rtld.)
6870 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
6871 fi->readx(ibuf, umin(blocksize, file_size_u32));
6872
6873 // Determine if the extra page with copy of _Shdrs was spliced in.
6874 // This used to be the result of --android-shlib.
6875 // But in 2023-02 the forwarding of ARM_ATTRIBUTES (by appending)
6876 // takes care of this, so the 5th word before e_entry does not
6877 // have the low bit 1, so is_asl should not be set.
6878 // However, .so that were compressed before 2023-03
6879 // may be marked.
6880 e_shoff = get_te64(&ehdri.e_shoff);
6881 if (e_shoff && e_shnum
6882 // +36: (sizeof(PackHeader) + sizeof(overlay_offset))
6883 // after Shdrs for ARM_ATTRIBUTES
6884 && (((e_shoff + sizeof(Elf64_Shdr) * e_shnum) + 36) < file_size_u)
6885 ) { // possible --android-shlib
6886 unsigned x = get_te32(&file_image[get_te64(&ehdri.e_entry) - (1+ 4)*sizeof(int)]);
6887 if (1 & x) { // the clincher
6888 is_asl = 1;
6889 fi->seek(e_shoff, SEEK_SET);
6890 mb_shdr.alloc( sizeof(Elf64_Shdr) * e_shnum);
6891 shdri = (Elf64_Shdr *)mb_shdr.getVoidPtr();
6892 fi->readx(shdri, sizeof(Elf64_Shdr) * e_shnum);
6893 yct_off = get_te64(&shdri->sh_offset); // for the output file (de-compressed)
6894 xct_off = asl_delta + yct_off; // for the input file (compressed)
6895 }
6896 }
6897
6898 // Decompress first Extent. Old style covers [0, xct_off)
6899 // which includes rtld constant data and eXecutable app code below DT_INIT.
6900 // In old style, the first compressed Extent is redundant
6901 // except for the compressed original Elf headers.
6902 // New style covers just Elf headers: the rest below xct_off is
6903 // rtld constant data: DT_*HASH, DT_SYMTAB, DT_STRTAB, etc.
6904 // New style puts eXecutable app code in second PT_LOAD
6905 // in order to mark Elf headers and rtld data as non-eXecutable.
6906 fi->seek(overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info), SEEK_SET);
6907 struct {
6908 struct l_info l;
6909 struct p_info p;
6910 struct b_info b;
6911 } hdr;
6912 fi->readx(&hdr, sizeof(hdr));
6913 if (hdr.l.l_magic != UPX_MAGIC_LE32
6914 || get_te16(&hdr.l.l_lsize) != (unsigned)lsize
6915 || get_te32(&hdr.p.p_filesize) != ph.u_file_size
6916 || get_te32(&hdr.b.sz_unc) < sz_elf_hdrs // peek: 1st b_info covers Elf headers
6917 ) {
6918 throwCantUnpack("corrupt l_info/p_info/b_info");
6919 }
6920 fi->seek(-(off_t)sizeof(struct b_info), SEEK_CUR); // hdr.b_info was a peek
6921
6922// The default layout for a shared library created by binutils-2.29
6923// (Fedora 28; 2018) has two PT_LOAD: permissions r-x and rw-.
6924// xct_off (the lowest address of executable instructions;
6925// the highest address of read-only data used by rtld (ld-linux))
6926// will be somewhere in the first PT_LOAD.
6927//
6928// The default layout for a shared library created by binutils-2.31
6929// (Fedora 29; 2018) has four PT_LOAD: permissions r--, r-x, r--, rw-.
6930// xct_off will be the base of the second [r-x] PT_LOAD.
6931//
6932// Bytes below xct_off cannot be compressed because they are used
6933// by rtld *before* the UPX run-time de-compression stub gets control
6934// via DT_INIT. Bytes in a Writeable PT_LOAD cannot be compressed
6935// because they may be relocated by rtld, again before stub execution.
6936//
6937// We need to know which layout of PT_LOAD. It seems risky to steal
6938// bits in the input ElfXX_Ehdr or ElfXX_Phdr, so we decompress
6939// the first compressed block. For an old-style shared library
6940// the first compressed block covers [0, xct_off) which is redundant
6941// with the interval [sz_elf_hdrs, xct_off) because those bytes
6942// must be present for use by rtl (So that is a large inefficiency.)
6943// Fortunately p_info.p_blocksize fits in ibuf, and unpackExtent
6944// will just decompress it all. For new style, the first compressed
6945// block covers [0, sz_elf_hdrs).
6946
6947 // Peek: unpack into ibuf, but do not write
6948 unsigned const sz_block1 = unpackExtent(sz_elf_hdrs, nullptr,
6949 c_adler, u_adler, false, -1);
6950 if (sz_block1 < sz_elf_hdrs) {
6951 throwCantUnpack("corrupt b_info");
6952 }
6953 memcpy(o_elfhdrs, ibuf, sz_elf_hdrs); // save de-compressed Elf headers
6954 Elf64_Ehdr const *const ehdro = (Elf64_Ehdr const *)(void const *)o_elfhdrs;
6955 if (ehdro->e_type !=ehdri.e_type
6956 || ehdro->e_machine!=ehdri.e_machine
6957 || ehdro->e_version!=ehdri.e_version
6958 // less strict for EM_PPC64 to workaround earlier bug
6959 || !( ehdro->e_flags==ehdri.e_flags
6960 || Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64 == get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine))
6961 || ehdro->e_ehsize !=ehdri.e_ehsize
6962 // check EI_MAG[0-3], EI_CLASS, EI_DATA, EI_VERSION
6963 || memcmp(ehdro->e_ident, ehdri.e_ident, Elf64_Ehdr::EI_OSABI)) {
6964 throwCantUnpack("ElfXX_Ehdr corrupted");
6965 }
6966 if (fo) {
6967 fo->write(ibuf, sz_block1);
6968 total_out = sz_block1;
6969 }
6970 Elf64_Phdr const *o_phdr = (Elf64_Phdr const *)(1+ ehdro);
6971 // Handle compressed PT_LOADs (must not have PF_W)
6972 unsigned not_first_LOAD = 0;
6973 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++o_phdr) {
6974 unsigned type = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_type);
6975 unsigned flags = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_flags);
6976 if (PT_LOAD != type || Elf64_Phdr::PF_W & flags) {
6977 continue;
6978 }
6979 unsigned p_offset = get_te64(&o_phdr->p_offset);
6980 unsigned p_filesz = get_te64(&o_phdr->p_filesz);
6981 unsigned wanted = p_filesz;
6982 if (!not_first_LOAD++) { // first PT_LOAD
6983 wanted -= sz_block1;
6984 if (sz_block1 > sz_elf_hdrs) { // old style
6985 if (is_asl) {
6986 un_asl_dynsym(orig_file_size, fo);
6987 }
6988 p_offset += sz_block1;
6989 }
6990 if (sz_block1 == sz_elf_hdrs) { // new style
6991 unsigned const len = (yct_off ? yct_off : xct_off) - sz_elf_hdrs;
6992 unsigned const ipos = fi->tell();
6993 fi->seek(sz_elf_hdrs, SEEK_SET);
6994 fi->readx(&ibuf[sz_elf_hdrs], len);
6995 if (is_asl) {
6996 un_asl_dynsym(orig_file_size, nullptr);
6997 }
6998 if (fo) {
6999 fo->write(&ibuf[sz_elf_hdrs], len);
7000 }
7001 total_out += len;
7002
7003// github-issue629: (overlay_offset = 0xa500), so initially (xct_off = 0xa494).
7004// But "yct_off = get_te64(&shdri->sh_offset)" so if _Shdrs are aligned (??)
7005// then (0x10500 == (xct_off = asl_delta + yct_off)), and we read+write
7006// more than we need.
7007// So assume the excess just lives there, or is overwritten later by seek+write.
7008 if (wanted < len) { // FIXME: why does this happen?
7009 wanted = 0;
7010 }
7011 else {
7012 wanted -= len;
7013 }
7014 fi->seek(ipos, SEEK_SET);
7015 if (total_out == p_filesz) {
7016 continue; // already entirely re-generated
7017 }
7018 p_offset = total_out;
7019 }
7020 }
7021 if (fo) {
7022 fo->seek(p_offset, SEEK_SET);
7023 }
7024 unpackExtent(wanted, fo, c_adler, u_adler, false);
7025 }
7026 funpad4(fi);
7027 loader_offset = fi->tell();
7028
7029 // Handle PT_LOAD with PF_W: writeable, so not compressed. "Slide"
7030 o_phdr = (Elf64_Phdr const *)(1+ ehdro);
7031 Elf64_Phdr const *i_phdr = phdri;
7032 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++o_phdr, ++i_phdr) {
7033 unsigned type = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_type);
7034 unsigned flags = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_flags);
7035 if (PT_LOAD != type || !(Elf64_Phdr::PF_W & flags)) {
7036 continue;
7037 }
7038 unsigned filesz = get_te64(&o_phdr->p_filesz);
7039 unsigned o_offset = get_te64(&o_phdr->p_offset);
7040 unsigned i_offset = get_te64(&i_phdr->p_offset);
7041 fi->seek(i_offset, SEEK_SET);
7042 fi->readx(ibuf, filesz);
7043 total_in += filesz;
7044 if (fo) {
7045 fo->seek(o_offset, SEEK_SET);
7046 fo->write(ibuf, filesz);
7047 }
7048 total_out = filesz + o_offset; // high-water mark
7049 }
7050
7051 // Gaps between PT_LOAD will be handled by ::unpack()
7052
7053 // position fi at loader offset
7054 fi->seek(loader_offset, SEEK_SET);
7055}
7056
7057void PackLinuxElf32::un_shlib_1(
7058 OutputFile *const fo,
7059 MemBuffer &o_elfhdrs,
7060 unsigned &c_adler,
7061 unsigned &u_adler,
7062 unsigned const orig_file_size
7063)
7064{
7065 // xct_off [input side] was set by ::unpack when is_shlib
7066 // yct_off [output side] set here unless is_asl in next 'if' block
7067 unsigned yct_off = xct_off;
7068
7069 // Below xct_off is not compressed (for benefit of rtld.)
7070 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
7071 fi->readx(ibuf, umin(blocksize, file_size_u32));
7072
7073 // Determine if the extra page with copy of _Shdrs was spliced in.
7074 // This used to be the result of --android-shlib.
7075 // But in 2023-02 the forwarding of ARM_ATTRIBUTES (by appending)
7076 // takes care of this, so the 5th word before e_entry does not
7077 // have the low bit 1, so is_asl should not be set.
7078 // However, .so that were compressed before 2023-03
7079 // may be marked.
7080 e_shoff = get_te32(&ehdri.e_shoff);
7081 if (e_shoff && e_shnum
7082 // +36: (sizeof(PackHeader) + sizeof(overlay_offset))
7083 // after Shdrs for ARM_ATTRIBUTES
7084 && (((e_shoff + sizeof(Elf32_Shdr) * e_shnum) + 36) < file_size_u32)
7085 ) { // possible --android-shlib
7086 unsigned x = get_te32(&file_image[get_te32(&ehdri.e_entry) - (1+ 4)*sizeof(int)]);
7087 if (1 & x) { // the clincher
7088 is_asl = 1;
7089 fi->seek(e_shoff, SEEK_SET);
7090 mb_shdr.alloc( sizeof(Elf32_Shdr) * e_shnum);
7091 shdri = (Elf32_Shdr *)mb_shdr.getVoidPtr();
7092 fi->readx(shdri, sizeof(Elf32_Shdr) * e_shnum);
7093 yct_off = get_te32(&shdri->sh_offset); // for the output file (de-compressed)
7094 xct_off = asl_delta + yct_off; // for the input file (compressed)
7095 }
7096 }
7097
7098 // Decompress first Extent. Old style covers [0, xct_off)
7099 // which includes rtld constant data and eXecutable app code below DT_INIT.
7100 // In old style, the first compressed Extent is redundant
7101 // except for the compressed original Elf headers.
7102 // New style covers just Elf headers: the rest below xct_off is
7103 // rtld constant data: DT_*HASH, DT_SYMTAB, DT_STRTAB, etc.
7104 // New style puts eXecutable app code in second PT_LOAD
7105 // in order to mark Elf headers and rtld data as non-eXecutable.
7106 fi->seek(overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info), SEEK_SET);
7107 struct {
7108 struct l_info l;
7109 struct p_info p;
7110 struct b_info b;
7111 } hdr;
7112 fi->readx(&hdr, sizeof(hdr));
7113 if (hdr.l.l_magic != UPX_MAGIC_LE32
7114 || get_te16(&hdr.l.l_lsize) != (unsigned)lsize
7115 || get_te32(&hdr.p.p_filesize) != ph.u_file_size
7116 || get_te32(&hdr.b.sz_unc) < sz_elf_hdrs // peek: 1st b_info covers Elf headers
7117 ) {
7118 throwCantUnpack("corrupt l_info/p_info/b_info");
7119 }
7120 fi->seek(-(off_t)sizeof(struct b_info), SEEK_CUR); // hdr.b_info was a peek
7121
7122// The default layout for a shared library created by binutils-2.29
7123// (Fedora 28; 2018) has two PT_LOAD: permissions r-x and rw-.
7124// xct_off (the lowest address of executable instructions;
7125// the highest address of read-only data used by rtld (ld-linux))
7126// will be somewhere in the first PT_LOAD.
7127//
7128// The default layout for a shared library created by binutils-2.31
7129// (Fedora 29; 2018) has four PT_LOAD: permissions r--, r-x, r--, rw-.
7130// xct_off will be the base of the second [r-x] PT_LOAD.
7131//
7132// Bytes below xct_off cannot be compressed because they are used
7133// by rtld *before* the UPX run-time de-compression stub gets control
7134// via DT_INIT. Bytes in a Writeable PT_LOAD cannot be compressed
7135// because they may be relocated by rtld, again before stub execution.
7136//
7137// We need to know which layout of PT_LOAD. It seems risky to steal
7138// bits in the input ElfXX_Ehdr or ElfXX_Phdr, so we decompress
7139// the first compressed block. For an old-style shared library
7140// the first compressed block covers [0, xct_off) which is redundant
7141// with the interval [sz_elf_hdrs, xct_off) because those bytes
7142// must be present for use by rtl (So that is a large inefficiency.)
7143// Fortunately p_info.p_blocksize fits in ibuf, and unpackExtent
7144// will just decompress it all. For new style, the first compressed
7145// block covers [0, sz_elf_hdrs).
7146
7147 // Peek: unpack into ibuf, but do not write
7148 unsigned const sz_block1 = unpackExtent(sz_elf_hdrs, nullptr,
7149 c_adler, u_adler, false, -1);
7150 if (sz_block1 < sz_elf_hdrs) {
7151 throwCantUnpack("corrupt b_info");
7152 }
7153 memcpy(o_elfhdrs, ibuf, sz_elf_hdrs); // save de-compressed Elf headers
7154 Elf32_Ehdr const *const ehdro = (Elf32_Ehdr const *)(void const *)o_elfhdrs;
7155 if (ehdro->e_type !=ehdri.e_type
7156 || ehdro->e_machine!=ehdri.e_machine
7157 || ehdro->e_version!=ehdri.e_version
7158 // less strict for EM_PPC to workaround earlier bug
7159 || !( ehdro->e_flags==ehdri.e_flags
7160 || Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC == get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine))
7161 || ehdro->e_ehsize !=ehdri.e_ehsize
7162 // check EI_MAG[0-3], EI_CLASS, EI_DATA, EI_VERSION
7163 || memcmp(ehdro->e_ident, ehdri.e_ident, Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI)) {
7164 throwCantUnpack("ElfXX_Ehdr corrupted");
7165 }
7166 if (fo) {
7167 fo->write(ibuf, sz_block1);
7168 total_out = sz_block1;
7169 }
7170 Elf32_Phdr const *o_phdr = (Elf32_Phdr const *)(1+ ehdro);
7171 // Handle compressed PT_LOADs (must not have PF_W)
7172 unsigned not_first_LOAD = 0;
7173 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++o_phdr) {
7174 unsigned type = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_type);
7175 unsigned flags = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_flags);
7176 if (PT_LOAD != type || Elf32_Phdr::PF_W & flags) {
7177 continue;
7178 }
7179 unsigned p_offset = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_offset);
7180 unsigned p_filesz = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_filesz);
7181 unsigned wanted = p_filesz;
7182 if (!not_first_LOAD++) { // first PT_LOAD
7183 wanted -= sz_block1;
7184 if (sz_block1 > sz_elf_hdrs) { // old style
7185 if (is_asl) {
7186 un_asl_dynsym(orig_file_size, fo);
7187 }
7188 p_offset += sz_block1;
7189 }
7190 if (sz_block1 == sz_elf_hdrs) { // new style
7191 unsigned const len = (yct_off ? yct_off : xct_off) - sz_elf_hdrs;
7192 unsigned const ipos = fi->tell();
7193 fi->seek(sz_elf_hdrs, SEEK_SET);
7194 fi->readx(&ibuf[sz_elf_hdrs], len);
7195 if (is_asl) {
7196 un_asl_dynsym(orig_file_size, nullptr);
7197 }
7198 if (fo) {
7199 fo->write(&ibuf[sz_elf_hdrs], len);
7200 }
7201 total_out += len;
7202
7203// github-issue629: (overlay_offset = 0xa500), so initially (xct_off = 0xa494).
7204// But "yct_off = get_te32(&shdri->sh_offset)" so if _Shdrs are aligned (??)
7205// then (0x10500 == (xct_off = asl_delta + yct_off)), and we read+write
7206// more than we need.
7207// So assume the excess just lives there, or is overwritten later by seek+write.
7208 if (wanted < len) { // FIXME: why does this happen?
7209 wanted = 0;
7210 }
7211 else {
7212 wanted -= len;
7213 }
7214 fi->seek(ipos, SEEK_SET);
7215 if (total_out == p_filesz) {
7216 continue; // already entirely re-generated
7217 }
7218 p_offset = total_out;
7219 }
7220 }
7221 if (fo) {
7222 fo->seek(p_offset, SEEK_SET);
7223 }
7224 unpackExtent(wanted, fo, c_adler, u_adler, false);
7225 }
7226 funpad4(fi);
7227 loader_offset = fi->tell();
7228
7229 // Handle PT_LOAD with PF_W: writeable, so not compressed. "Slide"
7230 o_phdr = (Elf32_Phdr const *)(1+ ehdro);
7231 Elf32_Phdr const *i_phdr = phdri;
7232 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++o_phdr, ++i_phdr) {
7233 unsigned type = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_type);
7234 unsigned flags = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_flags);
7235 if (PT_LOAD != type || !(Elf32_Phdr::PF_W & flags)) {
7236 continue;
7237 }
7238 unsigned filesz = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_filesz);
7239 unsigned o_offset = get_te32(&o_phdr->p_offset);
7240 unsigned i_offset = get_te32(&i_phdr->p_offset);
7241 fi->seek(i_offset, SEEK_SET);
7242 fi->readx(ibuf, filesz);
7243 total_in += filesz;
7244 if (fo) {
7245 fo->seek(o_offset, SEEK_SET);
7246 fo->write(ibuf, filesz);
7247 }
7248 total_out = filesz + o_offset; // high-water mark
7249 }
7250
7251 // Gaps between PT_LOAD will be handled by ::unpack()
7252
7253 // position fi at loader offset
7254 fi->seek(loader_offset, SEEK_SET);
7255}
7256
7257void PackLinuxElf32::un_DT_INIT(
7258 unsigned old_dtinit,
7259 Elf32_Phdr const *const phdro,
7260 Elf32_Phdr const *const dynhdr, // in phdri
7261 OutputFile *fo
7262)
7263{
7264 // DT_INIT must be restored.
7265 // If android_shlib, then the asl_delta relocations must be un-done.
7266 unsigned n_plt = 0;
7267 upx_uint32_t dt_pltrelsz(0), dt_jmprel(0), dt_pltgot(0);
7268 upx_uint32_t dt_relsz(0), dt_rel(0);
7269 upx_uint32_t const dyn_len = get_te32(&dynhdr->p_filesz);
7270 upx_uint32_t const dyn_off = get_te32(&dynhdr->p_offset);
7271 if (file_size_u32 < (dyn_len + dyn_off)) {
7272 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
7273 "bad PT_DYNAMIC .p_filesz %#lx", (long unsigned)dyn_len);
7274 throwCantUnpack(msg);
7275 }
7276 fi->seek(dyn_off, SEEK_SET);
7277 fi->readx(ibuf, dyn_len);
7278 Elf32_Dyn *dyn = (Elf32_Dyn *)(void *)ibuf;
7279 dynseg = dyn; invert_pt_dynamic(dynseg,
7280 umin(dyn_len, file_size_u32 - dyn_off));
7281 for (unsigned j2= 0; j2 < dyn_len; ++dyn, j2 += sizeof(*dyn)) {
7282 upx_uint32_t const tag = get_te32(&dyn->d_tag);
7283 upx_uint32_t val = get_te32(&dyn->d_val);
7284 if (is_asl) switch (tag) {
7285 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_RELASZ: { dt_relsz = val; } break;
7286 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_RELA: { dt_rel = val; } break;
7287 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_JMPREL: { dt_jmprel = val; } break;
7288 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_PLTRELSZ: { dt_pltrelsz = val;
7289 n_plt = dt_pltrelsz / sizeof(Elf32_Rel);
7290 if (is_asl) {
7291 n_plt += 3; // FIXME
7292 }
7293 }; break;
7294
7295 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_PLTGOT: { plt_va = dt_pltgot = val; (void)dt_pltgot; }
7296 // FALL THROUGH
7297 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY:
7298 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY:
7299 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_FINI_ARRAY:
7300 case Elf32_Dyn::DT_FINI: if (is_asl) {
7301 set_te32(&dyn->d_val, val - asl_delta);
7302 }; break;
7303 } // end switch() on tag when is_asl
7304 if (upx_dt_init == tag) {
7305 if (Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT == tag) { // the easy case
7306 set_te32(&dyn->d_val, old_dtinit);
7307 if (!old_dtinit) { // compressor took the slot
7308 dyn->d_tag = Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL;
7309 dyn->d_val = 0;
7310 }
7311 }
7312 // Apparently the hard case is common for some Android IDEs.
7313 else if (Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY == tag
7314 || Elf32_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY == tag) {
7315 // 'val' is the RVA of the first slot, which is the slot that
7316 // the compressor changed to be the entry to the run-time stub.
7317 Elf32_Rel *rp = (Elf32_Rel *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL);
7318 ((Elf32_Dyn *)elf_find_dynptr(Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL))->d_val = 0;
7319 if (rp) {
7320 // Compressor saved the original *rp in dynsym[0]
7321 Elf32_Rel *rp_unc = (Elf32_Rel *)&dynsym[0]; // pointer
7322 rp->r_info = rp_unc->r_info; // restore original r_info; r_offset not touched
7323
7324 unsigned e_entry = get_te32(&ehdri.e_entry);
7325 unsigned init_rva = get_te32(&file_image[e_entry - 3*sizeof(unsigned)]);
7326 unsigned arr_rva = get_te32(&rp_unc->r_offset);
7327 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(arr_rva, phdro, e_phnum);
7328 unsigned arr_off = (arr_rva - get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr)) + get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
7329
7330 rp_unc->r_offset = 0; rp_unc->r_info = 0;
7331 if (fo) {
7332 fo->seek(elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB), SEEK_SET);
7333 fo->rewrite(rp_unc, sizeof(Elf32_Rel)); // clear dynsym[0]
7334
7335 fo->seek((char *)rp - (char *)&file_image[0], SEEK_SET);
7336 fo->rewrite(rp, sizeof(*rp)); // restore original *rp
7337 }
7338
7339 // Set arr[0] to the first user init routine.
7340 unsigned r_info = get_te32(&rp->r_info);
7341 unsigned r_type = ELF32_R_TYPE(r_info);
7342 unsigned word;
7343 if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM == e_machine) {
7344 if (R_ARM_RELATIVE == r_type) {
7345 set_te32(&word, init_rva);
7346 }
7347 else if (R_ARM_ABS32 == r_type) {
7348 word = 0;
7349 }
7350 else {
7351 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "unknown relocation: %#x",
7352 r_type);
7353 throwCantUnpack(msg);
7354 }
7355 }
7356 else if (Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386 == e_machine) {
7357 if (R_386_RELATIVE == r_type) {
7358 }
7359 else if (R_386_32 == r_type) {
7360 }
7361 if (R_386_RELATIVE == r_type) {
7362 set_te32(&word, init_rva);
7363 }
7364 else if (R_386_32 == r_type) {
7365 word = 0;
7366 }
7367 else {
7368 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "unknown relocation: %#x",
7369 r_type);
7370 throwCantUnpack(msg);
7371 }
7372 }
7373 if (fo) {
7374 fo->seek(arr_off, SEEK_SET);
7375 fo->rewrite(&word, sizeof(unsigned));
7376 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
7377 }
7378 }
7379 }
7380 }
7381 }
7382 if (fo) { // Write updated dt_*.val
7383 upx_uint32_t dyn_offo = get_te32(&phdro[dynhdr - phdri].p_offset);
7384 fo->seek(dyn_offo, SEEK_SET);
7385 fo->rewrite(ibuf, dyn_len);
7386 }
7387 if (is_asl) {
7388 MemBuffer ptload1; // FIXME. file_image has the whole file; ibuf is available
7389 lowmem.alloc(xct_off);
7390 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
7391 fi->read(lowmem, xct_off); // contains relocation tables
7392 if (dt_relsz && dt_rel) {
7393 Elf32_Rel *const rel0 = (Elf32_Rel *)lowmem.subref(
7394 "bad Rel offset", dt_rel, dt_relsz);
7395 unRel32(dt_rel, rel0, dt_relsz, ptload1, old_dtinit, fo);
7396 }
7397 if (dt_pltrelsz && dt_jmprel) { // FIXME: overlap w/ DT_REL ?
7398 Elf32_Rel *const jmp0 = (Elf32_Rel *)lowmem.subref(
7399 "bad Jmprel offset", dt_jmprel, dt_pltrelsz);
7400 jump_slots.alloc(n_plt * sizeof(upx_uint32_t));
7401 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr = phdri;
7402 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
7403 upx_uint32_t vaddr = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
7404 upx_uint32_t filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
7405 upx_uint32_t d = plt_va - vaddr;
7406 if (d < filesz) {
7407 upx_uint32_t offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
7408 fi->seek(d + offset, SEEK_SET);
7409 fi->readx(jump_slots, n_plt * sizeof(upx_uint32_t));
7410 break;
7411 }
7412 }
7413 unRel32(dt_jmprel, jmp0, dt_pltrelsz, ptload1, old_dtinit, fo);
7414
7415 Elf32_Ehdr const *const o_ehdr = (Elf32_Ehdr const *)(void *)lowmem;
7416 unsigned const o_phnum = o_ehdr->e_phnum;
7417 phdr = phdro;
7418 for (unsigned j = 0; j < o_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
7419 upx_uint32_t vaddr = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
7420 upx_uint32_t filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
7421 upx_uint32_t d = plt_va - vaddr - asl_delta;
7422 if (d < filesz) {
7423 upx_uint32_t offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
7424 if (fo) {
7425 fo->seek(d + offset, SEEK_SET);
7426 fo->rewrite(jump_slots, n_plt * sizeof(upx_uint32_t));
7427 }
7428 break;
7429 }
7430 }
7431 }
7432 // Modified relocation tables are re-written by unRel32
7433 }
7434}
7435
7436void PackLinuxElf64::un_DT_INIT(
7437 unsigned old_dtinit,
7438 Elf64_Phdr const *const phdro,
7439 Elf64_Phdr const *const dynhdr, // in phdri
7440 OutputFile *fo
7441)
7442{
7443 // DT_INIT must be restored.
7444 // If android_shlib, then the asl_delta relocations must be un-done.
7445 unsigned n_plt = 0;
7446 upx_uint64_t dt_pltrelsz(0), dt_jmprel(0), dt_pltgot(0);
7447 upx_uint64_t dt_relasz(0), dt_rela(0);
7448 upx_uint64_t const dyn_len = get_te64(&dynhdr->p_filesz);
7449 upx_uint64_t const dyn_off = get_te64(&dynhdr->p_offset);
7450 if (file_size_u < (dyn_len + dyn_off)) {
7451 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
7452 "bad PT_DYNAMIC .p_filesz %#lx", (long unsigned)dyn_len);
7453 throwCantUnpack(msg);
7454 }
7455 fi->seek(dyn_off, SEEK_SET);
7456 fi->readx(ibuf, dyn_len);
7457 Elf64_Dyn *dyn = (Elf64_Dyn *)(void *)ibuf;
7458 dynseg = dyn; invert_pt_dynamic(dynseg,
7459 umin(dyn_len, file_size_u - dyn_off));
7460 for (unsigned j2= 0; j2 < dyn_len; ++dyn, j2 += sizeof(*dyn)) {
7461 upx_uint64_t const tag = get_te64(&dyn->d_tag);
7462 upx_uint64_t val = get_te64(&dyn->d_val);
7463 if (is_asl) switch (tag) {
7464 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELASZ: { dt_relasz = val; } break;
7465 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_RELA: { dt_rela = val; } break;
7466 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_JMPREL: { dt_jmprel = val; } break;
7467 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_PLTRELSZ: { dt_pltrelsz = val;
7468 n_plt = dt_pltrelsz / sizeof(Elf32_Rel);
7469 if (is_asl) {
7470 n_plt += 3; // FIXME
7471 }
7472 }; break;
7473
7474 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_PLTGOT: { plt_va = dt_pltgot = val; (void)dt_pltgot;}
7475 // FALL THROUGH
7476 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY:
7477 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY:
7478 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_FINI_ARRAY:
7479 case Elf64_Dyn::DT_FINI: if (is_asl) {
7480 set_te64(&dyn->d_val, val - asl_delta);
7481 }; break;
7482 } // end switch() on tag when is_asl
7483 if (upx_dt_init == tag) { // the easy case
7484 if (Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT == tag) {
7485 set_te64(&dyn->d_val, old_dtinit);
7486 if (!old_dtinit) { // compressor took the slot
7487 dyn->d_tag = Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL;
7488 dyn->d_val = 0;
7489 }
7490 }
7491 // Apparently the hard case is common for some Android IDEs.
7492 else if (Elf32_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY == tag
7493 || Elf64_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY == tag) {
7494 // 'val' is the RVA of the first slot, which is the slot that
7495 // the compressor changed to be the entry to the run-time stub.
7496 Elf64_Rela *rp = (Elf64_Rela *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL);
7497 ((Elf64_Dyn *)elf_find_dynptr(Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL))->d_val = 0;
7498 if (rp) {
7499 // Compressor saved the original *rp in dynsym[0]
7500 Elf64_Rela *rp_unc = (Elf64_Rela *)&dynsym[0]; // pointer
7501 rp->r_info = rp_unc->r_info; // restore original r_info; r_offset not touched
7502 rp->r_addend = rp_unc->r_addend;
7503
7504 unsigned e_entry = get_te64(&ehdri.e_entry);
7505 unsigned init_rva = get_te64(&file_image[e_entry - 3*sizeof(unsigned)]);
7506 unsigned arr_rva = get_te64(&rp_unc->r_offset);
7507 Elf64_Phdr const *phdr = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(arr_rva, phdro, e_phnum);
7508 unsigned arr_off = (arr_rva - get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr)) + get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
7509
7510 memset(rp_unc, 0, sizeof(*rp_unc));
7511 if (fo) {
7512 fo->seek(elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB), SEEK_SET);
7513 fo->rewrite(rp_unc, sizeof(Elf64_Rela)); // clear dynsym[0]
7514
7515 fo->seek((char *)rp - (char *)&file_image[0], SEEK_SET);
7516 fo->rewrite(rp, sizeof(*rp)); // restore original *rp
7517 }
7518
7519 // Set arr[0] to the first user init routine.
7520 // Elf64_Rela overwrites anyway, so this is a redundancy
7521 // or a Don't Care.
7522 unsigned r_info = get_te64(&rp->r_info);
7523 unsigned r_type = ELF64_R_TYPE(r_info);
7524 u64_t word;
7525 if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_ARM64 == e_machine) {
7526 if (R_AARCH64_RELATIVE == r_type) {
7527 set_te64(&word, init_rva); // old_dtinit ?
7528 }
7529 else if (R_AARCH64_ABS64 == r_type) {
7530 word = 0;
7531 }
7532 else {
7533 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "unknown relocation: %#x",
7534 r_type);
7535 throwCantUnpack(msg);
7536 }
7537 }
7538 else if (Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AMD64 == e_machine) {
7539 if (R_X86_64_RELATIVE == r_type) {
7540 set_te64(&word, init_rva);
7541 }
7542 else if (R_X86_64_64 == r_type) {
7543 word = 0;
7544 }
7545 else {
7546 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "unknown relocation: %#x",
7547 r_type);
7548 throwCantUnpack(msg);
7549 }
7550 }
7551 if (fo) {
7552 fo->seek(arr_off, SEEK_SET);
7553 fo->rewrite(&word, sizeof(word));
7554 fo->seek(0, SEEK_END);
7555 }
7556 }
7557 }
7558 }
7559 }
7560 if (fo) { // Write updated dt_*.val
7561 upx_uint64_t dyn_offo = get_te64(&phdro[dynhdr - phdri].p_offset);
7562 fo->seek(dyn_offo, SEEK_SET);
7563 fo->rewrite(ibuf, dyn_len);
7564 }
7565 if (is_asl) {
7566 lowmem.alloc(xct_off);
7567 fi->seek(0, SEEK_SET);
7568 fi->read(lowmem, xct_off); // contains relocation tables
7569 if (dt_relasz && dt_rela) {
7570 Elf64_Rela *const rela0 = (Elf64_Rela *)lowmem.subref(
7571 "bad Rela offset", dt_rela, dt_relasz);
7572 unRela64(dt_rela, rela0, dt_relasz, old_dtinit, fo);
7573 }
7574 if (dt_pltrelsz && dt_jmprel) { // FIXME: overlap w/ DT_REL ?
7575 Elf64_Rela *const jmp0 = (Elf64_Rela *)lowmem.subref(
7576 "bad Jmprel offset", dt_jmprel, dt_pltrelsz);
7577 jump_slots.alloc(n_plt * sizeof(upx_uint64_t));
7578 Elf64_Phdr const *phdr = phdri;
7579 for (unsigned j = 0; j < e_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
7580 upx_uint64_t vaddr = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr);
7581 upx_uint64_t filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
7582 upx_uint64_t d = plt_va - vaddr;
7583 if (d < filesz) {
7584 upx_uint64_t offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
7585 fi->seek(d + offset, SEEK_SET);
7586 fi->readx(jump_slots, n_plt * sizeof(upx_uint64_t));
7587 break;
7588 }
7589 }
7590 unRela64(dt_jmprel, jmp0, dt_pltrelsz, old_dtinit, fo);
7591
7592 Elf64_Ehdr const *const o_ehdr = (Elf64_Ehdr const *)(void *)lowmem;
7593 unsigned const o_phnum = o_ehdr->e_phnum;
7594 phdr = phdro;
7595 for (unsigned j = 0; j < o_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
7596 upx_uint64_t vaddr = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr);
7597 upx_uint64_t filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
7598 upx_uint64_t d = plt_va - vaddr - asl_delta;
7599 if (d < filesz) {
7600 upx_uint64_t offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
7601 if (fo) {
7602 fo->seek(d + offset, SEEK_SET);
7603 fo->rewrite(jump_slots, n_plt * sizeof(upx_uint64_t));
7604 }
7605 break;
7606 }
7607 }
7608 }
7609 // Modified relocation tables are re-written by unRela64
7610 }
7611}
7612
7613void PackLinuxElf64::unpack(OutputFile *fo)
7614{
7615 if (e_phoff != sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr)) {// Phdrs not contiguous with Ehdr
7616 throwCantUnpack("bad e_phoff");
7617 }
7618 unsigned const c_phnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum);
7619 unsigned u_phnum = 0;
7620 upx_uint64_t old_dtinit = 0;
7621
7622 if (Elf64_Ehdr::ET_EXEC == get_te16(&ehdri.e_type)) {
7623// 40fddf17153ee3db73a04ff1bf288b91676138d6 2001-02-01 ph.version 11; b_info 12 bytes
7624// df9db96bd1c013c07da1d7ec740021d588ab2815 2001-01-17 ph.version 11; no b_info (==> 8 bytes)
7625 if (ph.version <= 11
7626 && get_te64(&ehdri.e_entry) < 0x401180
7627 && get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine)==Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64) {
7628 // old style, 8-byte b_info:
7629 // sizeof(b_info.sz_unc) + sizeof(b_info.sz_cpr);
7630 szb_info = 2*sizeof(unsigned);
7631 }
7632 }
7633
7634 fi->seek(overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info), SEEK_SET);
7635 fi->readx(&linfo, sizeof(linfo));
7636 if (UPX_MAGIC_LE32 != get_le32(&linfo.l_magic)) {
7637 NE32 const *const lp = (NE32 const *)(void const *)&linfo;
7638 // Workaround for bug of extra linfo by some asl_pack2_Shdrs().
7639 if (0==lp[0] && 0==lp[1] && 0==lp[2]) { // looks like blank extra
7640 fi->readx(&linfo, sizeof(linfo));
7641 if (UPX_MAGIC_LE32 == get_le32(&linfo.l_magic)) {
7642 overlay_offset += sizeof(linfo);
7643 }
7644 else {
7645 throwCantUnpack("l_info corrupted");
7646 }
7647 }
7648 else {
7649 throwCantUnpack("l_info corrupted");
7650 }
7651 }
7652 lsize = get_te16(&linfo.l_lsize);
7653 p_info hbuf; fi->readx(&hbuf, sizeof(hbuf));
7654 unsigned orig_file_size = get_te32(&hbuf.p_filesize);
7655 blocksize = get_te32(&hbuf.p_blocksize);
7656 if ((u32_t)file_size > orig_file_size || blocksize > orig_file_size
7657 || !mem_size_valid(1, blocksize, OVERHEAD))
7658 throwCantUnpack("p_info corrupted");
7659
7660 ibuf.alloc(blocksize + OVERHEAD);
7661 b_info bhdr; memset(&bhdr, 0, sizeof(bhdr));
7662 fi->readx(&bhdr, szb_info);
7663 ph.u_len = get_te32(&bhdr.sz_unc);
7664 ph.c_len = get_te32(&bhdr.sz_cpr);
7665 if (ph.c_len > file_size_u || ph.c_len == 0 || ph.u_len == 0
7666 || ph.u_len > orig_file_size)
7667 throwCantUnpack("b_info corrupted");
7668 ph.filter_cto = bhdr.b_cto8;
7669 prev_method = bhdr.b_method; // FIXME if multiple de-compressors
7670
7671 MemBuffer u(ph.u_len);
7672 Elf64_Ehdr *const ehdr = (Elf64_Ehdr *)&u[0];
7673 Elf64_Phdr const *phdr = nullptr;
7674 total_in = 0;
7675 total_out = 0;
7676 unsigned c_adler = upx_adler32(nullptr, 0);
7677 unsigned u_adler = upx_adler32(nullptr, 0);
7678
7679 unsigned is_shlib = 0;
7680 loader_offset = 0;
7681 MemBuffer o_elfhdrs;
7682 Elf64_Phdr const *const dynhdr = elf_find_ptype(Elf64_Phdr::PT_DYNAMIC, phdri, c_phnum);
7683 // dynseg was set by PackLinuxElf64help1
7684 if (dynhdr && !(Elf64_Dyn::DF_1_PIE & elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_FLAGS_1))) {
7685 // Packed shlib? (ET_DYN without -fPIE)
7686 is_shlib = 1;
7687 xct_off = overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info);
7688 u_phnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum);
7689 o_elfhdrs.alloc(sz_elf_hdrs);
7690 un_shlib_1(fo, o_elfhdrs, c_adler, u_adler, orig_file_size);
7691 *ehdr = ehdri;
7692 }
7693 else { // main executable
7694 // Uncompress Ehdr and Phdrs: info for control of unpacking
7695 if (ibuf.getSize() < ph.c_len)
7696 throwCompressedDataViolation();
7697
7698 fi->readx(ibuf, ph.c_len);
7699 // "clickhouse" ET_EXEC for amd64 has 0x200000 <= .e_entry
7700 // instead of 0x400000 that we checked earlier.
7701 if (8 == szb_info
7702 && Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64 == e_machine
7703 && Elf64_Ehdr::ET_EXEC == e_type
7704 && ph.u_len <= MAX_ELF_HDR_64
7705 ) {
7706 unsigned b_method = ibuf[0];
7707 unsigned b_extra = ibuf[3];
7708 if (M_ZSTD >= b_method && 0 == b_extra) {
7709 fi->seek( -(upx_off_t)(ph.c_len + szb_info), SEEK_CUR);
7710 szb_info = 12;
7711 fi->readx(&bhdr, szb_info);
7712 ph.filter_cto = bhdr.b_cto8;
7713 prev_method = bhdr.b_method; // FIXME if multiple de-compressors
7714 fi->readx(ibuf, ph.c_len);
7715 }
7716 }
7717 decompress(ibuf, (upx_byte *)ehdr, false);
7718 if (ehdr->e_type !=ehdri.e_type
7719 || ehdr->e_machine!=ehdri.e_machine
7720 || ehdr->e_version!=ehdri.e_version
7721 // less strict for EM_PPC64 to workaround earlier bug
7722 || !( ehdr->e_flags==ehdri.e_flags
7723 || Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64 == get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine))
7724 || ehdr->e_ehsize !=ehdri.e_ehsize
7725 // check EI_MAG[0-3], EI_CLASS, EI_DATA, EI_VERSION
7726 || memcmp(ehdr->e_ident, ehdri.e_ident, Elf64_Ehdr::EI_OSABI)) {
7727 throwCantUnpack("ElfXX_Ehdr corrupted");
7728 }
7729 // Rewind: prepare for data phase
7730 fi->seek(- (off_t) (szb_info + ph.c_len), SEEK_CUR);
7731
7732 u_phnum = get_te16(&ehdr->e_phnum);
7733 if ((umin(MAX_ELF_HDR_64, ph.u_len) - sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr))/sizeof(Elf64_Phdr) < u_phnum) {
7734 throwCantUnpack("bad compressed e_phnum");
7735 }
7736 o_elfhdrs.alloc(sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr) + u_phnum * sizeof(Elf64_Phdr));
7737 memcpy(o_elfhdrs, ehdr, o_elfhdrs.getSize());
7738
7739 // Decompress each PT_LOAD.
7740 bool first_PF_X = true;
7741 phdr = (Elf64_Phdr *) (void *) (1+ ehdr); // uncompressed
7742 for (unsigned j=0; j < u_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
7743 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
7744 unsigned const filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
7745 unsigned const offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
7746 if (fo) {
7747 fo->seek(offset, SEEK_SET);
7748 if (total_out < offset) {
7749 total_out = offset; // FIXME: can it be re-write?
7750 }
7751 }
7752 if (Elf64_Phdr::PF_X & get_te32(&phdr->p_flags)) {
7753 unpackExtent(filesz, fo,
7754 c_adler, u_adler, first_PF_X);
7755 first_PF_X = false;
7756 }
7757 else {
7758 unpackExtent(filesz, fo,
7759 c_adler, u_adler, false);
7760 }
7761 }
7762 }
7763 }
7764
7765 upx_uint64_t const e_entry = get_te64(&ehdri.e_entry);
7766 unsigned off_entry = 0;
7767 phdr = phdri;
7768 load_va = 0;
7769 for (unsigned j=0; j < c_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
7770 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
7771 upx_uint64_t offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
7772 upx_uint64_t vaddr = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr);
7773 upx_uint64_t filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz);
7774 if (!load_va) {
7775 load_va = vaddr;
7776 }
7777 if ((e_entry - vaddr) < filesz) {
7778 off_entry = (e_entry - vaddr) + offset;
7779 break;
7780 }
7781 }
7782 }
7783 unsigned d_info[6];
7784 unsigned sz_d_info = sizeof(d_info);
7785 if (!is_shlib) {
7786 if (get_te32(&phdri[0].p_flags) & Elf64_Phdr::PF_X) {
7787 // Old style, such as upx-3.91 thru upx-3.95
7788 switch (this->e_machine) {
7789 default: {
7790 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
7791 "Unknown architecture %d", this->e_machine);
7792 throwCantUnpack(msg);
7793 }; break;
7794 case Elf64_Ehdr::EM_AARCH64: sz_d_info = 4 * sizeof(unsigned); break;
7795 case Elf64_Ehdr::EM_PPC64: sz_d_info = 3 * sizeof(unsigned); break;
7796 case Elf64_Ehdr::EM_X86_64: sz_d_info = 2 * sizeof(unsigned); break;
7797 }
7798 }
7799 loader_offset = off_entry - sz_d_info;
7800 }
7801
7802 if (0x1000==get_te64(&phdri[0].p_filesz) // detect C_BASE style
7803 && 0==get_te64(&phdri[1].p_offset)
7804 && 0==get_te64(&phdri[0].p_offset)
7805 && get_te64(&phdri[1].p_filesz) == get_te64(&phdri[1].p_memsz)) {
7806 fi->seek(up4(get_te64(&phdri[1].p_memsz)), SEEK_SET); // past the loader
7807 }
7808 else if (is_shlib
7809 || (off_entry + up4(lsize) + ph.getPackHeaderSize() + sizeof(overlay_offset))
7810 < up4(file_size)) {
7811 // Loader is not at end; skip past it.
7812 if (loader_offset) {
7813 fi->seek(loader_offset, SEEK_SET);
7814 }
7815 else {
7816 funpad4(fi); // MATCH01
7817 }
7818 fi->readx(d_info, sz_d_info);
7819 if (is_shlib && 0==old_dtinit) {
7820 old_dtinit = get_te32(&d_info[2 + (0==d_info[0])]);
7821 is_asl = 1u& get_te32(&d_info[0 + (0==d_info[0])]);
7822 }
7823 fi->seek(lsize - sz_d_info, SEEK_CUR);
7824 }
7825
7826 // The gaps between PT_LOAD and after last PT_LOAD
7827 phdr = (Elf64_Phdr const *)(1+ (Elf64_Ehdr const *)(void const *)o_elfhdrs);
7828 upx_uint64_t hi_offset(0);
7829 for (unsigned j = 0; j < u_phnum; ++j) {
7830 upx_uint64_t const offset = get_te64(&phdr[j].p_offset);
7831 if (is_LOAD(&phdr[j])
7832 && hi_offset < offset) {
7833 hi_offset = offset;
7834 }
7835 }
7836 for (unsigned j = 0; j < u_phnum; ++j) {
7837 unsigned const size = find_LOAD_gap(phdr, j, u_phnum);
7838 if (size) {
7839 unsigned const where = get_te64(&phdr[j].p_offset) +
7840 get_te64(&phdr[j].p_filesz);
7841 if (fo)
7842 fo->seek(where, SEEK_SET);
7843 { // Recover from some piracy [also serves as error tolerance :-) ]
7844 // Getting past the loader is problematic, due to unintended
7845 // variances between released versions:
7846 // l_info.l_lsize might be rounded up by 8 instead of by 4, and
7847 // sz_d_info might have changed.
7848 b_info b_peek, *bp = &b_peek;
7849 fi->readx(bp, sizeof(b_peek));
7850 upx_off_t pos = fi->seek(-(off_t)sizeof(b_peek), SEEK_CUR);
7851 unsigned sz_unc = get_te32(&bp->sz_unc);
7852 unsigned sz_cpr = get_te32(&bp->sz_cpr);
7853 unsigned word3 = get_te32(&bp->b_method);
7854 unsigned method = bp->b_method;
7855 unsigned ftid = bp->b_ftid;
7856 unsigned cto8 = bp->b_cto8;
7857 if (!( ((sz_cpr == sz_unc) && (0 == word3) && (size == sz_unc)) // incompressible literal
7858 || ((sz_cpr < sz_unc) && (method == prev_method) && (0 == ftid) && (0 == cto8)))
7859 ) {
7860 opt->info_mode++;
7861 infoWarning("bad b_info at %#zx", (size_t)pos);
7862 unsigned const N_PEEK(16 * sizeof(int)), H_PEEK(N_PEEK >> 1);
7863 unsigned char peek_arr[N_PEEK];
7864 fi->seek(pos - H_PEEK, SEEK_SET);
7865 fi->readx(peek_arr, sizeof(peek_arr));
7866 fi->seek(pos, SEEK_SET);
7867 bool const is_be = ELFDATA2MSB == ehdri.e_ident[EI_DATA];
7868 if (is_be) {
7869 // Does the right thing for sz_unc and sz_cpr,
7870 // but swaps b_method and b_extra. Need find_be32() :-)
7871 for (unsigned k = 0; k < N_PEEK; k += sizeof(int)) {
7872 set_le32(&peek_arr[k], get_be32(&peek_arr[k]));
7873 }
7874 }
7875 int boff = find_le32(peek_arr, sizeof(peek_arr), size);
7876 if (boff < 0
7877 || sizeof(peek_arr) < (boff + sizeof(b_info))) {
7878 throwCantUnpack("b_info corrupted");
7879 }
7880 bp = (b_info *)(void *)&peek_arr[boff];
7881
7882 sz_unc = get_le32(&bp->sz_unc);
7883 sz_cpr = get_le32(&bp->sz_cpr);
7884 word3 = get_le32(&bp->b_method);
7885 ftid = bp->b_ftid;
7886 cto8 = bp->b_cto8;
7887 if (0 <= boff // found
7888 && ( ((sz_cpr == sz_unc) && (0 == word3) && (size == sz_unc)) // incompressible literal
7889 || ((sz_cpr < sz_unc) && (0 == ftid) && (0 == cto8)
7890 && ((is_be ? bp->b_extra : bp->b_method) == prev_method)) )
7891 ) {
7892 pos -= H_PEEK;
7893 pos += boff;
7894 infoWarning("... recovery at %#zx", (size_t)pos);
7895 fi->seek(pos, SEEK_SET);
7896 }
7897 opt->info_mode--;
7898 }
7899 }
7900 unpackExtent(size, fo,
7901 c_adler, u_adler, false,
7902 (hi_offset != get_te64(&phdr[j].p_offset)));
7903 }
7904 }
7905
7906 // check for end-of-file
7907 fi->readx(&bhdr, szb_info);
7908 unsigned const sz_unc = ph.u_len = get_te32(&bhdr.sz_unc);
7909
7910 if (sz_unc == 0) { // uncompressed size 0 -> EOF
7911 // note: magic is always stored le32
7912 unsigned const sz_cpr = get_le32(&bhdr.sz_cpr);
7913 if (sz_cpr != UPX_MAGIC_LE32) // sz_cpr must be h->magic
7914 throwCompressedDataViolation();
7915 }
7916 else { // extra bytes after end?
7917 throwCompressedDataViolation();
7918 }
7919
7920 if (is_shlib) {
7921 un_DT_INIT(old_dtinit, (Elf64_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf64_Ehdr *)(void *)o_elfhdrs), dynhdr, fo);
7922 }
7923
7924 // update header with totals
7925 ph.c_len = total_in;
7926 ph.u_len = total_out;
7927
7928 // all bytes must be written
7929 if (fo && total_out != orig_file_size)
7930 throwEOFException();
7931
7932 // finally test the checksums
7933 if (ph.c_adler != c_adler || ph.u_adler != u_adler)
7934 throwChecksumError();
7935}
7936

7938
7942PackLinuxElf32x86::PackLinuxElf32x86(InputFile *f) : super(f)
7943{
7944 e_machine = Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386;
7945 ei_class = Elf32_Ehdr::ELFCLASS32;
7946 ei_data = Elf32_Ehdr::ELFDATA2LSB;
7947 ei_osabi = Elf32_Ehdr::ELFOSABI_LINUX;
7948}
7949
7950PackLinuxElf32x86::~PackLinuxElf32x86()
7951{
7952}
7953
7954tribool PackLinuxElf32x86::canUnpack() // bool, except -1: format known, but not packed
7955{
7956 if (super::canUnpack()) {
7957 return true;
7958 }
7959 return false;
7960}
7961
7962Linker* PackLinuxElf32x86::newLinker() const
7963{
7964 return new ElfLinkerX86;
7965}
7966
7967PackBSDElf32x86::PackBSDElf32x86(InputFile *f) : super(f)
7968{
7969 e_machine = Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386;

8006
8007int const *
8008PackLinuxElf32x86::getFilters() const
8009{
8010 static const int filters[] = {
8011 // 0x49 is 5-byte CALL or JMP, and 6-byte Jxx
8012 // 0x46 is 5-byte CALL or JMP
8013 0x49, 0x46,
8014// FIXME 2002-11-11: We use stub/fold_elf86.asm, which calls the
8015// decompressor multiple times, and unfilter is independent of decompress.
8016// Currently only filters 0x49, 0x46, 0x80..0x87 can handle this;
8017// and 0x80..0x87 are regarded as "untested".
8018#if 0
8019 0x26, 0x24, 0x11, 0x14, 0x13, 0x16, 0x25, 0x15, 0x12,
8020#endif
8021#if 0
8022 0x83, 0x36, 0x26,
8023 0x86, 0x80,
8024 0x84, 0x87, 0x81,
8025 0x82, 0x85,
8026 0x24, 0x16, 0x13, 0x14, 0x11, 0x25, 0x15, 0x12,
8027#endif
8028 FT_END };
8029 return filters;
8030}

8099
8100unsigned
8101PackLinuxElf32::elf_get_offset_from_address(unsigned addr) const
8102{
8103 return elf_get_offset_from_Phdrs(addr, phdri);
8104}
8105
8106unsigned
8107PackLinuxElf32::elf_get_offset_from_Phdrs(unsigned addr, Elf32_Phdr const *phdr0) const
8108{
8109 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr = phdr0;
8110 int j = e_phnum;
8111 for (; --j>=0; ++phdr) if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
8112 unsigned const t = addr - get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
8113 if (t < get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz)) {
8114 unsigned const p_offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
8115 if (file_size_u <= p_offset) { // FIXME: weak
8116 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
8117 "bad Elf32_Phdr[%d].p_offset %x",
8118 -1+ e_phnum - j, p_offset);
8119 throwCantPack(msg);
8120 }
8121 return t + p_offset;
8122 }
8123 }
8124 return 0;
8125}
8126
8127u32_t // returns .p_offset
8128PackLinuxElf32::check_pt_load(Elf32_Phdr const *const phdr)
8129{
8130 u32_t filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
8131 u32_t offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset), offend = filesz + offset;
8132 u32_t vaddr = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
8133 u32_t paddr = get_te32(&phdr->p_paddr);
8134 u32_t align = get_te32(&phdr->p_align);
8135
8136 if ((-1+ align) & (paddr ^ vaddr)
8137 || file_size_u32 <= (u32_t)offset
8138 || file_size_u32 < (u32_t)offend
8139 || file_size_u32 < (u32_t)filesz) {
8140 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad PT_LOAD phdr[%u]",
8141 (unsigned)(phdr - phdri));
8142 throwCantPack(msg);
8143 }
8144 return offset;
8145}
8146
8147Elf32_Dyn const *
8148PackLinuxElf32::elf_has_dynamic(unsigned int key) const
8149{
8150 Elf32_Dyn const *dynp= dynseg;
8151 if (dynp)
8152 for (; Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL!=dynp->d_tag; ++dynp) if (get_te32(&dynp->d_tag)==key) {
8153 return dynp;
8154 }
8155 return nullptr;
8156}
8157
8158unsigned // checked .p_offset; sz_dynseg set
8159PackLinuxElf32::check_pt_dynamic(Elf32_Phdr const *const phdr)
8160{
8161 unsigned t = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset), s = sizeof(Elf32_Dyn) + t;
8162 unsigned vaddr = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
8163 unsigned filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz), memsz = get_te32(&phdr->p_memsz);
8164 unsigned align = get_te32(&phdr->p_align);
8165 if (file_size_u < t || s < t
8166 || file_size_u < filesz
8167 || file_size_u < (filesz + t)
8168 || t < (e_phnum*sizeof(Elf32_Phdr) + sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr))
8169 || (3 & t) || (7 & (filesz | memsz)) // .balign 4; 8==sizeof(Elf32_Dyn)
8170 || (-1+ align) & (t ^ vaddr)
8171 || file_size_u <= memsz
8172 || filesz < sizeof(Elf32_Dyn)
8173 || memsz < sizeof(Elf32_Dyn)
8174 || filesz < memsz) {
8175 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad PT_DYNAMIC phdr[%u]",
8176 (unsigned)(phdr - phdri));
8177 throwCantPack(msg);
8178 }
8179 sz_dynseg = memsz;
8180 return t;
8181}
8182
8183Elf32_Dyn *PackLinuxElf32::elf_find_dynptr(unsigned int key) const
8184{
8185 Elf32_Dyn *dynp= dynseg;
8186 if (dynp) {
8187 Elf32_Dyn *const last = (Elf32_Dyn *)(sz_dynseg + (char *)dynseg);
8188 for (; dynp < last; ++dynp) {
8189 if (get_te32(&dynp->d_tag)==key) {
8190 return dynp;
8191 }
8192 if (Elf32_Dyn::DT_NULL == dynp->d_tag) {
8193 return nullptr;
8194 }
8195 }
8196 }
8197 return nullptr;
8198}
8199
8200Elf64_Dyn *PackLinuxElf64::elf_find_dynptr(unsigned int key) const
8201{
8202 Elf64_Dyn *dynp= dynseg;
8203 if (dynp) {
8204 Elf64_Dyn *const last = (Elf64_Dyn *)(sz_dynseg + (char *)dynseg);
8205 for (; dynp < last; ++dynp) {
8206 if (get_te64(&dynp->d_tag)==key) {
8207 return dynp;
8208 }
8209 if (Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL == dynp->d_tag) {
8210 return nullptr;
8211 }
8212 }
8213 }
8214 return nullptr;
8215}
8216
8217void *
8218PackLinuxElf32::elf_find_dynamic(unsigned int key) const
8219{
8220 Elf32_Dyn const *dynp= elf_find_dynptr(key);
8221 if (dynp) {
8222 unsigned const t= elf_get_offset_from_address(get_te32(&dynp->d_val));
8223 if (t && t < file_size_u) {
8224 return t + file_image;
8225 }
8226 }
8227 return nullptr;
8228}

8230void *
8231PackLinuxElf64::elf_find_dynamic(unsigned int key) const
8232{
8233 Elf64_Dyn const *dynp= elf_find_dynptr(key);

8235 upx_uint64_t const t= elf_get_offset_from_address(get_te64(&dynp->d_val));
8236 if (t && t < file_size_u) {
8237 return t + file_image;
8238 }
8239 }
8240 return nullptr;
8241}

8251}

8261}

8263upx_uint64_t
8264PackLinuxElf64::elf_get_offset_from_address(upx_uint64_t addr) const
8265{
8266 Elf64_Phdr const *phdr = phdri;
8267 int j = e_phnum;
8268 for (; --j>=0; ++phdr) if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
8269 upx_uint64_t const t = addr - get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr);
8270 if (t < get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz)) {
8271 upx_uint64_t const p_offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
8272 if (file_size_u <= p_offset) { // FIXME: weak
8273 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
8274 "bad Elf64_Phdr[%d].p_offset %#lx",
8275 -1+ e_phnum - j, (long unsigned)p_offset);
8276 throwCantPack(msg);
8277 }
8278 return t + p_offset;
8279 }
8280 }
8281 return 0;
8282}
