8288 u64_t offset = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset), offend = filesz + offset;
8289 u64_t vaddr = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr);
8290 u64_t paddr = get_te64(&phdr->p_paddr);
8291 u64_t align = get_te64(&phdr->p_align);
8292
8293 if ((-1+ align) & (paddr ^ vaddr)
8294 || file_size_u <= (u64_t)offset
8295 || file_size_u < (u64_t)offend
8296 || file_size_u < (u64_t)filesz) {
8297 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad PT_LOAD phdr[%u]",
8298 (unsigned)(phdr - phdri));

8302}

8304Elf64_Dyn const *

8306{
8307 Elf64_Dyn const *dynp= dynseg;
8308 if (dynp)
8309 for (; Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL!=dynp->d_tag; ++dynp) if (get_te64(&dynp->d_tag)==key) {
8310 return dynp;

8314
8315upx_uint64_t // checked .p_offset; sz_dynseg set
8316PackLinuxElf64::check_pt_dynamic(Elf64_Phdr const *const phdr)
8317{
8318 upx_uint64_t t = get_te64(&phdr->p_offset), s = sizeof(Elf64_Dyn) + t;
8319 upx_uint64_t vaddr = get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr);
8320 upx_uint64_t filesz = get_te64(&phdr->p_filesz), memsz = get_te64(&phdr->p_memsz);
8321 upx_uint64_t align = get_te64(&phdr->p_align);
8322 if (file_size_u < t || s < t
8323 || file_size_u < filesz
8324 || file_size_u < (filesz + t)
8325 || t < (e_phnum*sizeof(Elf64_Phdr) + sizeof(Elf64_Ehdr))
8326 || (7 & t) || (0xf & (filesz | memsz)) // .balign 8; 16==sizeof(Elf64_Dyn)
8327 || (-1+ align) & (t ^ vaddr)
8328 || file_size_u <= memsz
8329 || filesz < sizeof(Elf64_Dyn)
8330 || memsz < sizeof(Elf64_Dyn)
8331 || filesz < memsz) {
8332 char msg[50]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad PT_DYNAMIC phdr[%u]",
8333 (unsigned)(phdr - phdri));
8334 throwCantPack(msg);
8335 }
8336 sz_dynseg = memsz;
8337 return t;
8338}
8339
8340void
8341PackLinuxElf64::sort_DT64_offsets(Elf64_Dyn const *const dynp0)
8342{
8343 mb_dt_offsets.alloc(sizeof(unsigned) * sizeof(dt_keys)/sizeof(dt_keys[0]));
8344 mb_dt_offsets.clear();
8345 dt_offsets = (unsigned *)mb_dt_offsets.getVoidPtr();
8346 unsigned n_off = 0, k;
8347 for (unsigned j=0; ((k = dt_keys[j]), k); ++j) {
8348 dt_offsets[n_off] = 0; // default to "not found"
8349 u64_t rva = 0;
8350 if (k < DT_NUM) { // in range of easy table
8351 if (!dt_table[k]) {
8352 continue;
8353 }
8354 rva = get_te64(&dynp0[-1+ dt_table[k]].d_val);
8355 }
8356 else if (file_image) { // why is this guard necessary?
8357 rva = elf_unsigned_dynamic(k); // zero if not found
8358 }
8359 if (!rva) { // not present in input
8360 continue;
8361 }
8362 Elf64_Phdr const *const phdr = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(rva, phdri, e_phnum);
8363 if (!phdr) {
8364 char msg[60]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad DT_{%#x} = %#llx (no Phdr)",
8365 k, rva);
8366 throwCantPack(msg);
8367 }
8368 dt_offsets[n_off] = (rva - get_te64(&phdr->p_vaddr)) + get_te64(&phdr->p_offset);
8369
8370 if (file_size <= dt_offsets[n_off]) {
8371 char msg[60]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg), "bad DT_{%#x} = %#x (beyond EOF)",
8372 k, dt_offsets[n_off]);
8373 throwCantPack(msg);
8374 }
8375 n_off += !!dt_offsets[n_off];
8376 }
8377 dt_offsets[n_off++] = file_size; // sentinel
8378 upx_qsort(dt_offsets, n_off, sizeof(dt_offsets[0]), qcmp_unsigned);
8379}
8380
8381unsigned PackLinuxElf64::find_dt_ndx(u64_t rva)
8382{
8383 unsigned *const dto = (unsigned *)mb_dt_offsets.getVoidPtr();
8384 unsigned const dto_size = mb_dt_offsets.getSize() / sizeof(*dto);
8385 for (unsigned j = 0; j < dto_size && dto[j]; ++j) { // linear search of short table
8386 if (rva == dto[j]) {
8387 return j;
8388 }
8389 }
8390 return ~0u;
8391}
8392
8393unsigned PackLinuxElf64::elf_find_table_size(unsigned dt_type, unsigned sh_type)
8394{
8395 Elf64_Shdr const *sec = elf_find_section_type(sh_type);
8396 if (sec) { // Cheat the easy way: use _Shdr. (No _Shdr anyway for de-compression)
8397 return get_te64(&sec->sh_size);
8398 }
8399 // Honest hard work: use _Phdr
8400 unsigned x_rva;
8401 if (dt_type < DT_NUM) {
8402 unsigned const x_ndx = dt_table[dt_type];
8403 if (!x_ndx) { // no such entry
8404 return 0;
8405 }
8406 x_rva = get_te64(&dynseg[-1+ x_ndx].d_val);
8407 }
8408 else {
8409 x_rva = elf_unsigned_dynamic(dt_type);
8410 }
8411 Elf64_Phdr const *const x_phdr = elf_find_Phdr_for_va(x_rva, phdri, e_phnum);
8412 unsigned const d_off = x_rva - get_te64(&x_phdr->p_vaddr);
8413 unsigned const y_ndx = find_dt_ndx(d_off + get_te64(&x_phdr->p_offset));
8414 if (~0u != y_ndx) {
8415 return dt_offsets[1+ y_ndx] - dt_offsets[y_ndx];
8416 }
8417 return ~0u;
8418}
8419
8420void
8421PackLinuxElf64::invert_pt_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn const *dynp, upx_uint64_t headway)
8422{
8423 if (dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL]) {
8424 return; // not 1st time; do not change upx_dt_init
8425 }
8426 Elf64_Dyn const *const dynp0 = dynp;
8427 unsigned ndx = 0;
8428 unsigned const limit = headway / sizeof(*dynp);
8429 if (dynp)
8430 for (; ; ++ndx, ++dynp) {
8431 if (limit <= ndx) {
8432 throwCantPack("DT_NULL not found");
8433 }
8434 upx_uint64_t const d_tag = get_te64(&dynp->d_tag);
8435 if (d_tag>>32) { // outrageous
8436 throwCantPack("bad Elf64_Dyn[%d].d_tag %#lx",
8437 ndx, (long unsigned)d_tag);
8438 }
8439 if (d_tag < DT_NUM) {
8440 if (Elf64_Dyn::DT_NEEDED != d_tag
8441 && dt_table[d_tag]
8442 && get_te64(&dynp->d_val)
8443 != get_te64(&dynp0[-1+ dt_table[d_tag]].d_val)) {
8444 throwCantPack("duplicate DT_%#x: [%#x] [%#x]",
8445 (unsigned)d_tag, -1+ dt_table[d_tag], ndx);
8446 }
8447 dt_table[d_tag] = 1+ ndx;
8448 }
8449 if (Elf64_Dyn::DT_NULL == d_tag) {
8450 break; // check here so that dt_table[DT_NULL] is set
8451 }
8452 }
8453 sort_DT64_offsets(dynp0);
8454
8455 upx_dt_init = 0;
8456 if (dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT]) upx_dt_init = Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT;
8457 else if (dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY]) upx_dt_init = Elf64_Dyn::DT_PREINIT_ARRAY;
8458 else if (dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY]) upx_dt_init = Elf64_Dyn::DT_INIT_ARRAY;
8459
8460 unsigned const z_str = dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRSZ];
8461 strtab_max = !z_str ? 0 : get_te64(&dynp0[-1+ z_str].d_val);
8462 unsigned const z_tab = dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_STRTAB];
8463 unsigned const tmp1 = get_te64(&dynp0[-1+ z_tab].d_val);
8464 if (tmp1 < sz_elf_hdrs) {
8465 throwCantPack("bad DT_STRTAB %#x", tmp1);
8466 }
8467 unsigned const strtab_beg = !z_tab ? 0 : elf_get_offset_from_address(tmp1);
8468
8469 if (!z_str || !z_tab
8470 || (this->file_size - strtab_beg) < strtab_max // strtab overlaps EOF
8471 // last string in table must have terminating NUL
8472 || '\0' != ((char *)file_image.getVoidPtr())[-1+ strtab_max + strtab_beg]
8473 ) {
8474 throwCantPack("bad DT_STRSZ %#x", strtab_max);
8475 }
8476
8477 // Find end of DT_SYMTAB
8478 unsigned const tmp2 = elf_find_table_size(Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB,
8479 Elf64_Shdr::SHT_DYNSYM);
8480 symnum_max = (~0u == tmp2) ? 0 : tmp1 / sizeof(Elf64_Sym);
8481
8482 unsigned v_sym = dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_SYMTAB];
8483 if (v_sym) {
8484 v_sym = elf_get_offset_from_address(get_te64(&dynp0[-1+ v_sym].d_val));
8485 }
8486
8487 unsigned v_hsh = dt_table[Elf64_Dyn::DT_HASH];
8488 if (v_hsh) {
8489 v_hsh = elf_get_offset_from_address(get_te64(&dynp0[-1+ v_hsh].d_val));
8490 }
8491 if (v_hsh && file_image) {
8492 hashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_HASH);
8493 if (!hashtab) {
8494 throwCantPack("bad DT_HASH %#x", v_hsh);
8495 }
8496 // Find end of DT_HASH
8497 hashend = (unsigned const *)(void const *)(elf_find_table_size(
8498 Elf64_Dyn::DT_HASH, Elf64_Shdr::SHT_HASH) + (char const *)hashtab);
8499
8500 unsigned const nbucket = get_te32(&hashtab[0]);
8501 unsigned const *const buckets = &hashtab[2];
8502 unsigned const *const chains = &buckets[nbucket]; (void)chains;
8503 if ((unsigned)(file_size - ((char const *)buckets - (char const *)(void const *)file_image))
8504 <= sizeof(unsigned)*nbucket ) {
8505 throwCantPack("bad nbucket %#x\n", nbucket);
8506 }
8507
8508 if ((unsigned)(hashend - buckets) < nbucket
8509 || !v_sym || file_size_u <= v_sym
8510 || ((v_hsh < v_sym) && (v_sym - v_hsh) < sizeof(*buckets)*(2+ nbucket))
8511 ) {
8512 throwCantPack("bad DT_HASH nbucket=%#x len=%#x",
8513 nbucket, (v_sym - v_hsh));
8514 }
8515 unsigned chmax = 0;
8516 for (unsigned j= 0; j < nbucket; ++j) {
8517 unsigned x = get_te32(&buckets[j]);
8518 if (chmax < x) {
8519 chmax = x;
8520 }
8521 }
8522 if ((v_hsh < v_sym) && (v_sym - v_hsh) <
8523 (sizeof(*buckets)*(2+ nbucket) + sizeof(*chains)*(1+ chmax))) {
8524 throwCantPack("bad DT_HASH nbucket=%#x len=%#x",
8525 nbucket, (v_sym - v_hsh));
8526 }
8527 }
8528 unsigned const v_gsh = elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
8529 if (v_gsh && file_image) {
8530 // Not similar to DT_HASH because DT_GNU_HASH is not small (0x6ffffef5).
8531 gashtab = (unsigned const *)elf_find_dynamic(Elf64_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH);
8532 if (!gashtab) {
8533 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH %#x", v_gsh);
8534 }
8535 gashend = (unsigned const *)(void const *)(elf_find_table_size(
8536 Elf64_Dyn::DT_GNU_HASH, Elf64_Shdr::SHT_GNU_HASH) + (char const *)gashtab);
8537 unsigned const n_bucket = get_te32(&gashtab[0]);
8538 unsigned const symbias = get_te32(&gashtab[1]);
8539 unsigned const n_bitmask = get_te32(&gashtab[2]);
8540 unsigned const gnu_shift = get_te32(&gashtab[3]);
8541 upx_uint64_t const *const bitmask = (upx_uint64_t const *)(void const *)&gashtab[4];
8542 unsigned const *const buckets = (unsigned const *)&bitmask[n_bitmask];
8543 unsigned const *const hasharr = &buckets[n_bucket]; (void)hasharr;
8544 if (!n_bucket || (1u<<31) <= n_bucket /* fie on fuzzers */
8545 || (unsigned)(gashend - buckets) < n_bucket
8546 || (file_size + file_image) <= (void const *)hasharr) {
8547 throwCantPack("bad n_bucket %#x\n", n_bucket);
8548 }
8549 // It would be better to detect zeroes shifted into low 6 bits of:
8550 // (077 & (hash_32 >> gnu_shift))
8551 // but compilers can be stupid.
8552 if (31 < gnu_shift) {
8553 throwCantPack("bad gnu_shift %#x", gnu_shift);
8554 }
8555 // unsigned const *const gashend = &hasharr[n_bucket];
8556 // minimum, except:
8557 // Rust and Android trim unused zeroes from high end of hasharr[]
8558 unsigned bmax = 0;
8559 for (unsigned j= 0; j < n_bucket; ++j) {
8560 unsigned bj = get_te32(&buckets[j]);
8561 if (bj) {
8562 if (bj < symbias) {
8563 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH bucket[%d] < symbias{%#x}\n",
8564 bj, symbias);
8565 }
8566 if (bmax < bj) {
8567 bmax = bj;
8568 }
8569 }
8570 }
8571 if (1==n_bucket && 0==buckets[0]
8572 && 1==n_bitmask && 0==bitmask[0]) {
8573 // 2021-09-11 Rust on RaspberryPi apparently uses this to minimize space.
8574 // But then the DT_GNU_HASH symbol lookup algorithm always fails?
8575 // https://github.com/upx/upx/issues/525
8576 } else
8577 if (bmax) {
8578 if ((1+ bmax) < symbias) {
8579 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH (1+ max_bucket)=%#x < symbias=%#x",
8580 1+ bmax, symbias);
8581 }
8582 bmax -= symbias;
8583 }
8584
8585 unsigned r = 0;
8586 if (!n_bucket || !n_bitmask || !v_sym
8587 || (r=1, ((-1+ n_bitmask) & n_bitmask)) // not a power of 2
8588 || (r=2, (8*sizeof(upx_uint64_t) <= gnu_shift)) // shifted result always == 0
8589 || (r=3, (n_bucket>>30)) // fie on fuzzers
8590 || (r=4, (n_bitmask>>30))
8591 || (r=5, ((file_size/sizeof(unsigned))
8592 <= ((sizeof(*bitmask)/sizeof(unsigned))*n_bitmask + 2*n_bucket))) // FIXME: weak
8593 || (r=6, ((v_gsh < v_sym) && (v_sym - v_gsh) < (sizeof(unsigned)*4 // headers
8594 + sizeof(*bitmask)*n_bitmask // bitmask
8595 + sizeof(*buckets)*n_bucket // buckets
8596 + sizeof(*hasharr)*(!bmax ? 0 : (1+ bmax)) // hasharr
8597 )) )
8598 ) {
8599 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH n_bucket=%#x n_bitmask=%#x len=%#lx r=%d",
8600 n_bucket, n_bitmask, (long unsigned)(v_sym - v_gsh), r);
8601 }
8602 }
8603 e_shstrndx = get_te16(&ehdri.e_shstrndx); // who omitted this?
8604 if (e_shnum <= e_shstrndx
8605 && !(0==e_shnum && 0==e_shstrndx) ) {
8606 throwCantPack("bad .e_shstrndx %d >= .e_shnum %d", e_shstrndx, e_shnum);
8607 }
8608}
8609
8610unsigned PackLinuxElf::gnu_hash(char const *q)
8611{
8612 unsigned char const *p = (unsigned char const *)q;
8613 unsigned h;
8614
8615 for (h= 5381; 0!=*p; ++p) {
8616 h += *p + (h << 5);
8617 }
8618 return h;
8619}
8620
8621unsigned PackLinuxElf::elf_hash(char const *p)
8622{
8623 unsigned h;
8624 for (h= 0; 0!=*p; ++p) {
8625 h = *p + (h<<4);
8626 {
8627 unsigned const t = 0xf0000000u & h;
8628 h &= ~t;
8629 h ^= t>>24;
8630 }
8631 }
8632 return h;
8633}
8634
8635Elf32_Sym const *PackLinuxElf32::elf_lookup(char const *name) const
8636{
8637 if (hashtab && dynsym && dynstr) {
8638 unsigned const nbucket = get_te32(&hashtab[0]);
8639 unsigned const *const buckets = &hashtab[2];
8640 unsigned const *const chains = &buckets[nbucket];
8641 if (nbucket) {
8642 unsigned const m = elf_hash(name) % nbucket;
8643 unsigned nvisit = 0;
8644 unsigned si;
8645 for (si= get_te32(&buckets[m]); si; ) {
8646 char const *const p= get_dynsym_name(si, (unsigned)-1);
8647 if (p && 0==strcmp(name, p)) {
8648 return &dynsym[si];
8649 }
8650 if (nbucket <= ++nvisit) {
8651 throwCantPack("circular DT_HASH chain %d\n", si);
8652 }
8653 si= get_te32(&chains[si]);
8654 if (nbucket <= si) { // bad hashtab
8655 break;
8656 }
8657 }
8658 }
8659 }
8660 if (gashtab && dynsym && dynstr) {
8661 unsigned const n_bucket = get_te32(&gashtab[0]);
8662 unsigned const symbias = get_te32(&gashtab[1]);
8663 unsigned const n_bitmask = get_te32(&gashtab[2]);
8664 unsigned const gnu_shift = get_te32(&gashtab[3]);
8665 unsigned const *const bitmask = &gashtab[4];
8666 unsigned const *const buckets = &bitmask[n_bitmask];
8667 unsigned const *const hasharr = &buckets[n_bucket];
8668 if (31 < gnu_shift) {
8669 throwCantPack("bad gnu_shift %#x", gnu_shift);
8670 }
8671 if ((file_size + file_image) <= (void const *)hasharr) {
8672 throwCantPack("bad n_bucket %#x\n", n_bucket);
8673 }
8674 if (!n_bitmask
8675 || (unsigned)(file_size - ((char const *)bitmask - (char const *)(void const *)file_image))
8676 <= sizeof(unsigned)*n_bitmask ) {
8677 throwCantPack("bad n_bitmask %#x\n", n_bitmask);
8678 }
8679 if (n_bucket) { // -rust-musl can have "empty" hashtab
8680 unsigned const h = gnu_hash(name);
8681 unsigned const hbit1 = 037& h;
8682 unsigned const hbit2 = 037& (h>>gnu_shift);
8683 unsigned const w = get_te32(&bitmask[(n_bitmask -1) & (h>>5)]);
8684
8685 if (1& (w>>hbit1) & (w>>hbit2)) {
8686 unsigned const hhead = get_te32(&buckets[h % n_bucket]);
8687 if (n_bucket <= (hhead - symbias)) {
8688 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH n_bucket{%#x} <= buckets[%d]{%#x} - symbias{%#x}\n",
8689 n_bucket, h % n_bucket, hhead, symbias);
8690 }
8691 if (hhead) {
8692 Elf32_Sym const *dsp = &dynsym[hhead];
8693 unsigned const *hp = &hasharr[hhead - symbias];
8694 unsigned k;
8695 do {
8696 if (gashend <= hp) {
8697 throwCantPack("bad DT_GNU_HASH[%#x] head=%u",
8698 (unsigned)(hp - hasharr), hhead);
8699 }
8700 k = get_te32(hp);
8701 if (0==((h ^ k)>>1)) {
8702 unsigned const st_name = get_te32(&dsp->st_name);
8703 char const *const p = get_str_name(st_name, (unsigned)-1);
8704 if (0==strcmp(name, p)) {
8705 return dsp;
8706 }
8707 }
8708 } while (++dsp, ++hp, 0==(1u& k));
8709 }
8710 }
8711 }
8712 }
8713 // 2021-12-25 FIXME: Some Rust programs use
8714 // (1==n_bucket && 0==buckets[0] && 1==n_bitmask && 0==bitmask[0])
8715 // to minimize space in DT_GNU_HASH. This causes the fancy lookup to fail.
8716 // Is a fallback to linear search assumed?
8717 // 2022-03-12 Some Rust programs have 0==n_bucket.
8718 return nullptr;
8719
8720}
8721
8722Elf64_Sym const *PackLinuxElf64::elf_lookup(char const *name) const
8723{
8724 if (hashtab && dynsym && dynstr) {
8725 unsigned const nbucket = get_te32(&hashtab[0]);
8726 unsigned const *const buckets = &hashtab[2];
8727 unsigned const *const chains = &buckets[nbucket];
8728 if (nbucket) { // -rust-musl can have "empty" hashtab
8729 unsigned const m = elf_hash(name) % nbucket;
8730 unsigned nvisit = 0;
8731 unsigned si;
8732 for (si= get_te32(&buckets[m]); si; ) {
8733 char const *const p= get_dynsym_name(si, (unsigned)-1);
8734 if (p && 0==strcmp(name, p)) {
8735 return &dynsym[si];
8736 }
8737 if (nbucket <= ++nvisit) {
8738 throwCantPack("circular DT_HASH chain %d\n", si);
8739 }
8740 si = get_te32(&chains[si]);
8741 if (nbucket <= si) { // bad hashtab
8742 break;
8743 }
8744 }
8745 }
8746 }
8747 if (gashtab && dynsym && dynstr) {
8748 unsigned const n_bucket = get_te32(&gashtab[0]);
8749 unsigned const symbias = get_te32(&gashtab[1]);
8750 unsigned const n_bitmask = get_te32(&gashtab[2]);
8751 unsigned const gnu_shift = get_te32(&gashtab[3]);
8752 upx_uint64_t const *const bitmask = (upx_uint64_t const *)(void const *)&gashtab[4];
8753 unsigned const *const buckets = (unsigned const *)&bitmask[n_bitmask];
8754 unsigned const *const hasharr = &buckets[n_bucket];
8755
8756 if (31 < gnu_shift) {
8757 throwCantPack("bad gnu_shift %#x", gnu_shift);
8758 }
8759 if ((file_size + file_image) <= (void const *)hasharr) {
8760 throwCantPack("bad n_bucket %#x\n", n_bucket);
8761 }
8762 if (!n_bitmask
8763 || (unsigned)(file_size - ((char const *)bitmask - (char const *)(void const *)file_image))
8764 <= sizeof(unsigned)*n_bitmask ) {
8765 throwCantPack("bad n_bitmask %#x\n", n_bitmask);
8766 }
8767 if (n_bucket) { // -rust-musl can have "empty" gashtab
8768 unsigned const h = gnu_hash(name);
8769 unsigned const hbit1 = 077& h;
8770 unsigned const hbit2 = 077& (h>>gnu_shift);
8771 upx_uint64_t const w = get_te64(&bitmask[(n_bitmask -1) & (h>>6)]);
8772 if (1& (w>>hbit1) & (w>>hbit2)) {
8773 unsigned hhead = get_te32(&buckets[h % n_bucket]);
8774 if (hhead) {
8775 Elf64_Sym const *dsp = &dynsym[hhead];
8776 unsigned const *hp = &hasharr[hhead - symbias];
8777 unsigned k;
8778 do {
8779 if (gashend <= hp) {
8780 throwCantPack("bad gnu_hash[%#tx] head=%u",
8781 hp - hasharr, hhead);
8782 }
8783 k = get_te32(hp);
8784 if (0==((h ^ k)>>1)) {
8785 unsigned const st_name = get_te32(&dsp->st_name);
8786 char const *const p = get_str_name(st_name, (unsigned)-1);
8787 if (0==strcmp(name, p)) {
8788 return dsp;
8789 }
8790 }
8791 } while (++dsp, ++hp, 0==(1u& k));
8792 }
8793 }
8794 }
8795 }
8796 // 2021-12-25 FIXME: Some Rust programs use
8797 // (1==n_bucket && 0==buckets[0] && 1==n_bitmask && 0==bitmask[0])
8798 // to minimize space in DT_GNU_HASH. This causes the fancy lookup to fail.
8799 // Is a fallback to linear search assumed?
8800 // 2022-03-12 Some Rust programs have 0==n_bucket.
8801 return nullptr;
8802
8803}
8804
8805void PackLinuxElf32::unpack(OutputFile *fo)
8806{
8807 if (e_phoff != sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr)) {// Phdrs not contiguous with Ehdr
8808 throwCantUnpack("bad e_phoff");
8809 }
8810 unsigned const c_phnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum);
8811 unsigned u_phnum = 0;
8812 upx_uint32_t old_dtinit = 0;
8813
8814 if (Elf32_Ehdr::ET_EXEC == get_te16(&ehdri.e_type)) {
8815// 40fddf17153ee3db73a04ff1bf288b91676138d6 2001-02-01 ph.version 11; b_info 12 bytes
8816// df9db96bd1c013c07da1d7ec740021d588ab2815 2001-01-17 ph.version 11; no b_info (==> 8 bytes)
8817 if (ph.version <= 11
8818 && get_te32(&ehdri.e_entry) < 0x401180
8819 && get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine)==Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386) {
8820 // old style, 8-byte b_info:
8821 // sizeof(b_info.sz_unc) + sizeof(b_info.sz_cpr);
8822 szb_info = 2*sizeof(unsigned);
8823 }
8824 }
8825
8826 fi->seek(overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info), SEEK_SET);
8827 fi->readx(&linfo, sizeof(linfo));
8828 if (UPX_MAGIC_LE32 != get_le32(&linfo.l_magic)) {
8829 NE32 const *const lp = (NE32 const *)(void const *)&linfo;
8830 // Workaround for bug of extra linfo by some asl_pack2_Shdrs().
8831 if (0==lp[0] && 0==lp[1] && 0==lp[2]) { // looks like blank extra
8832 fi->readx(&linfo, sizeof(linfo));
8833 if (UPX_MAGIC_LE32 == get_le32(&linfo.l_magic)) {
8834 overlay_offset += sizeof(linfo);
8835 }
8836 else {
8837 throwCantUnpack("l_info corrupted");
8838 }
8839 }
8840 else {
8841 throwCantUnpack("l_info corrupted");
8842 }
8843 }
8844 lsize = get_te16(&linfo.l_lsize);
8845 p_info hbuf; fi->readx(&hbuf, sizeof(hbuf));
8846 unsigned orig_file_size = get_te32(&hbuf.p_filesize);
8847 blocksize = get_te32(&hbuf.p_blocksize);
8848 if ((u32_t)file_size > orig_file_size || blocksize > orig_file_size
8849 || !mem_size_valid(1, blocksize, OVERHEAD))
8850 throwCantUnpack("p_info corrupted");
8851
8852 ibuf.alloc(blocksize + OVERHEAD);
8853 b_info bhdr; memset(&bhdr, 0, sizeof(bhdr));
8854 fi->readx(&bhdr, szb_info);
8855 ph.u_len = get_te32(&bhdr.sz_unc);
8856 ph.c_len = get_te32(&bhdr.sz_cpr);
8857 if (ph.c_len > (unsigned)file_size || ph.c_len == 0 || ph.u_len == 0
8858 || ph.u_len > orig_file_size)
8859 throwCantUnpack("b_info corrupted");
8860 ph.filter_cto = bhdr.b_cto8;
8861 prev_method = bhdr.b_method; // FIXME if multiple de-compressors
8862
8863 MemBuffer u(ph.u_len);
8864 Elf32_Ehdr *const ehdr = (Elf32_Ehdr *)&u[0];
8865 Elf32_Phdr const *phdr = nullptr;
8866 total_in = 0;
8867 total_out = 0;
8868 unsigned c_adler = upx_adler32(nullptr, 0);
8869 unsigned u_adler = upx_adler32(nullptr, 0);
8870
8871 unsigned is_shlib = 0;
8872 loader_offset = 0;
8873 MemBuffer o_elfhdrs;
8874 Elf32_Phdr const *const dynhdr = elf_find_ptype(Elf32_Phdr::PT_DYNAMIC, phdri, c_phnum);
8875 // dynseg was set by PackLinuxElf32help1
8876 if (dynhdr && !(Elf32_Dyn::DF_1_PIE & elf_unsigned_dynamic(Elf32_Dyn::DT_FLAGS_1))) {
8877 // Packed shlib? (ET_DYN without -fPIE)
8878 is_shlib = 1;
8879 xct_off = overlay_offset - sizeof(l_info);
8880 u_phnum = get_te16(&ehdri.e_phnum);
8881 o_elfhdrs.alloc(sz_elf_hdrs);
8882 un_shlib_1(fo, o_elfhdrs, c_adler, u_adler, orig_file_size);
8883 *ehdr = ehdri;
8884 }
8885 else { // main executable
8886 // Uncompress Ehdr and Phdrs: info for control of unpacking
8887 if (ibuf.getSize() < ph.c_len)
8888 throwCompressedDataViolation();
8889 fi->readx(ibuf, ph.c_len);
8890 decompress(ibuf, (upx_byte *)ehdr, false);
8891 if (ehdr->e_type !=ehdri.e_type
8892 || ehdr->e_machine!=ehdri.e_machine
8893 || ehdr->e_version!=ehdri.e_version
8894 // less strict for EM_PPC to workaround earlier bug
8895 || !( ehdr->e_flags==ehdri.e_flags
8896 || Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC == get_te16(&ehdri.e_machine))
8897 || ehdr->e_ehsize !=ehdri.e_ehsize
8898 // check EI_MAG[0-3], EI_CLASS, EI_DATA, EI_VERSION
8899 || memcmp(ehdr->e_ident, ehdri.e_ident, Elf32_Ehdr::EI_OSABI)) {
8900 throwCantUnpack("ElfXX_Ehdr corrupted");
8901 }
8902 // Rewind: prepare for data phase
8903 fi->seek(- (off_t) (szb_info + ph.c_len), SEEK_CUR);
8904
8905 u_phnum = get_te16(&ehdr->e_phnum);
8906 if ((umin(MAX_ELF_HDR_32, ph.u_len) - sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr))/sizeof(Elf32_Phdr) < u_phnum) {
8907 throwCantUnpack("bad compressed e_phnum");
8908 }
8909 o_elfhdrs.alloc(sizeof(Elf32_Ehdr) + u_phnum * sizeof(Elf32_Phdr));
8910 memcpy(o_elfhdrs, ehdr, o_elfhdrs.getSize());
8911
8912 // Decompress each PT_LOAD.
8913 bool first_PF_X = true;
8914 phdr = (Elf32_Phdr *) (void *) (1+ ehdr); // uncompressed
8915 for (unsigned j=0; j < u_phnum; ++phdr, ++j) {
8916 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
8917 unsigned const filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
8918 unsigned const offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
8919 if (fo) {
8920 fo->seek(offset, SEEK_SET);
8921 if (total_out < offset) {
8922 total_out = offset; // FIXME: can it be re-write?
8923 }
8924 }
8925 if (Elf32_Phdr::PF_X & get_te32(&phdr->p_flags)) {
8926 unpackExtent(filesz, fo,
8927 c_adler, u_adler, first_PF_X);
8928 first_PF_X = false;
8929 }
8930 else {
8931 unpackExtent(filesz, fo,
8932 c_adler, u_adler, false);
8933 }
8934 }
8935 }
8936 }
8937
8938 upx_uint32_t const e_entry = get_te32(&ehdri.e_entry);
8939 unsigned off_entry = 0;
8940 phdr = phdri;
8941 load_va = 0;
8942 for (unsigned j=0; j < c_phnum; ++j, ++phdr) {
8943 if (is_LOAD(phdr)) {
8944 upx_uint32_t offset = get_te32(&phdr->p_offset);
8945 upx_uint32_t vaddr = get_te32(&phdr->p_vaddr);
8946 upx_uint32_t filesz = get_te32(&phdr->p_filesz);
8947 if (!load_va) {
8948 load_va = vaddr;
8949 }
8950 if ((e_entry - vaddr) < filesz) {
8951 off_entry = (e_entry - vaddr) + offset;
8952 break;
8953 }
8954 }
8955 }
8956 unsigned d_info[6];
8957 unsigned sz_d_info = sizeof(d_info);
8958 if (!is_shlib) {
8959 if (get_te32(&phdri[0].p_flags) & Elf32_Phdr::PF_X) {
8960 // Old style, such as upx-3.91 thru upx-3.95
8961 switch (this->e_machine) {
8962 default: {
8963 char msg[40]; snprintf(msg, sizeof(msg),
8964 "Unknown architecture %d", this->e_machine);
8965 throwCantUnpack(msg);
8966 }; break;
8967 case Elf32_Ehdr::EM_MIPS:sz_d_info = 1 * sizeof(unsigned); break;
8968 case Elf32_Ehdr::EM_ARM: sz_d_info = 4 * sizeof(unsigned); break;
8969 case Elf32_Ehdr::EM_PPC: sz_d_info = 3 * sizeof(unsigned); break;
8970 case Elf32_Ehdr::EM_386: sz_d_info = 2 * sizeof(unsigned); break;
8971 }
8972 }
8973 loader_offset = off_entry - sz_d_info;
8974 }
8975
8976 if (0x1000==get_te32(&phdri[0].p_filesz) // detect C_BASE style
8977 && 0==get_te32(&phdri[1].p_offset)
8978 && 0==get_te32(&phdri[0].p_offset)
8979 && get_te32(&phdri[1].p_filesz) == get_te32(&phdri[1].p_memsz)) {
8980 fi->seek(up4(get_te32(&phdri[1].p_memsz)), SEEK_SET); // past the loader
8981 }
8982 else if (is_shlib
8983 || (off_entry + up4(lsize) + ph.getPackHeaderSize() + sizeof(overlay_offset))
8984 < up4(file_size)) {
8985 // Loader is not at end; skip past it.
8986 if (loader_offset) {
8987 fi->seek(loader_offset, SEEK_SET);
8988 }
8989 else {
8990 funpad4(fi); // MATCH01
8991 }
8992 fi->readx(d_info, sz_d_info);
8993 if (is_shlib && 0==old_dtinit) {
8994 old_dtinit = get_te32(&d_info[2 + (0==d_info[0])]);
8995 is_asl = 1u& get_te32(&d_info[0 + (0==d_info[0])]);
8996 }
8997 fi->seek(lsize - sz_d_info, SEEK_CUR);
8998 }
8999
9000 // The gaps between PT_LOAD and after last PT_LOAD
9001 phdr = (Elf32_Phdr const *)(1+ (Elf32_Ehdr const *)(void const *)o_elfhdrs);
9002 upx_uint32_t hi_offset(0);
9003 for (unsigned j = 0; j < u_phnum; ++j) {
9004 if (is_LOAD(&phdr[j])
9005 && hi_offset < get_te32(&phdr[j].p_offset))
9006 hi_offset = get_te32(&phdr[j].p_offset);
9007 }
9008 for (unsigned j = 0; j < u_phnum; ++j) {
9009 unsigned const size = find_LOAD_gap(phdr, j, u_phnum);
9010 if (size) {
9011 unsigned const where = get_te32(&phdr[j].p_offset) +
9012 get_te32(&phdr[j].p_filesz);
9013 if (fo)
9014 fo->seek(where, SEEK_SET);
9015 { // Recover from some piracy [also serves as error tolerance :-) ]
9016 // Getting past the loader is problematic, due to unintended
9017 // variances between released versions:
9018 // l_info.l_lsize might be rounded up by 8 instead of by 4, and
9019 // sz_d_info might have changed.
9020 b_info b_peek, *bp = &b_peek;
9021 fi->readx(bp, sizeof(b_peek));
9022 upx_off_t pos = fi->seek(-(off_t)sizeof(b_peek), SEEK_CUR);
9023 unsigned sz_unc = get_te32(&bp->sz_unc);
9024 unsigned sz_cpr = get_te32(&bp->sz_cpr);
9025 unsigned word3 = get_te32(&bp->b_method);
9026 unsigned method = bp->b_method;
9027 unsigned ftid = bp->b_ftid;
9028 unsigned cto8 = bp->b_cto8;
9029 if (!( ((sz_cpr == sz_unc) && (0 == word3) && (size == sz_unc)) // incompressible literal
9030 || ((sz_cpr < sz_unc) && (method == prev_method) && (0 == ftid) && (0 == cto8)))
9031 ) {
9032 opt->info_mode++;
9033 infoWarning("bad b_info at %#zx", (size_t)pos);
9034 unsigned const N_PEEK(16 * sizeof(int)), H_PEEK(N_PEEK >> 1);
9035 unsigned char peek_arr[N_PEEK];
9036 fi->seek(pos - H_PEEK, SEEK_SET);
9037 fi->readx(peek_arr, sizeof(peek_arr));
9038 fi->seek(pos, SEEK_SET);
9039 bool const is_be = ELFDATA2MSB == ehdri.e_ident[EI_DATA];
9040 if (is_be) {
9041 // Does the right thing for sz_unc and sz_cpr,
9042 // but swaps b_method and b_extra. Need find_be32() :-)
9043 for (unsigned k = 0; k < N_PEEK; k += sizeof(int)) {
9044 set_le32(&peek_arr[k], get_be32(&peek_arr[k]));
9045 }
9046 }
9047 int boff = find_le32(peek_arr, sizeof(peek_arr), size);
9048 if (boff < 0 || sizeof(peek_arr) < (sizeof(*bp) + boff)) {
9049 throwCantUnpack("b_info corrupted");
9050 }
9051 bp = (b_info *)(void *)&peek_arr[boff];
9052
9053 sz_unc = get_le32(&bp->sz_unc);
9054 sz_cpr = get_le32(&bp->sz_cpr);
9055 word3 = get_le32(&bp->b_method);
9056 ftid = bp->b_ftid;
9057 cto8 = bp->b_cto8;
9058 if (0 <= boff // found
9059 && ( ((sz_cpr == sz_unc) && (0 == word3) && (size == sz_unc)) // incompressible literal
9060 || ((sz_cpr < sz_unc) && (0 == ftid) && (0 == cto8)
9061 && ((is_be ? bp->b_extra : bp->b_method) == prev_method)) )
9062 ) {
9063 pos -= H_PEEK;
9064 pos += boff;
9065 infoWarning("... recovery at %#zx", (size_t)pos);
9066 fi->seek(pos, SEEK_SET);
9067 }
9068 opt->info_mode--;
9069 }
9070 }
9071 unpackExtent(size, fo,
9072 c_adler, u_adler, false,
9073 (hi_offset != get_te32(&phdr[j].p_offset)));
9074 }
9075 }
9076
9077 // check for end-of-file
9078 fi->readx(&bhdr, szb_info);
9079 unsigned const sz_unc = ph.u_len = get_te32(&bhdr.sz_unc);
9080
9081 if (sz_unc == 0) { // uncompressed size 0 -> EOF
9082 // note: magic is always stored le32
9083 unsigned const sz_cpr = get_le32(&bhdr.sz_cpr);
9084 if (sz_cpr != UPX_MAGIC_LE32) // sz_cpr must be h->magic
9085 throwCompressedDataViolation();
9086 }
9087 else { // extra bytes after end?
9088 throwCompressedDataViolation();
9089 }
9090
9091 if (is_shlib) {
9092 un_DT_INIT(old_dtinit, (Elf32_Phdr *)(1+ (Elf32_Ehdr *)(void *)o_elfhdrs), dynhdr, fo);
9093 }
9094
9095 // update header with totals
9096 ph.c_len = total_in;
9097 ph.u_len = total_out;
9098
9099 // all bytes must be written
9100 if (fo && total_out != orig_file_size)
9101 throwEOFException();
9102
9103 // finally test the checksums
9104 if (ph.c_adler != c_adler || ph.u_adler != u_adler)
9105 throwChecksumError();
9106}
9107
9108void PackLinuxElf::unpack(OutputFile * /*fo*/)
9109{
9110 throwCantUnpack("internal error");
9111}
